UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '墓室',
  name_en = 'Coffin Chamber',
  body = '<p>The Coffin Chamber lies behind the Sacrificial Hall and is the most sacred space within the mausoleum, completed in 1929. It features a hemispherical dome approximately 18 meters in diameter and 11 meters in height, with marble flooring throughout. At its center is Dr. Sun''s tomb, surmounted by a white marble reclining statue sculpted by Czech artist Bohuslav Koci, remarkably lifelike in detail. Dr. Sun''s sarcophagus rests directly beneath the statue. Railings surround the tomb, allowing visitors to walk around and pay their respects. The dim, solemn atmosphere makes this the most important site for honoring Dr. Sun''s memory. The chamber is closed on Mondays for preservation purposes.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'nanjing_sun_yat_sen_mausoleum_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '退思园',
  name_en = 'Tuisi Garden (Retreat & Reflection Garden)',
  body = '<p>Built in the Guangxu era of the Qing dynasty, the garden was constructed by Ren Lansheng after his dismissal from office, named after the Zuo Zhuan phrase "Advance to serve with loyalty, retreat to reflect and mend faults." Though only 9.8 mu in area, its masterly layout creates infinite poetic resonance within limited space — pavilions, towers, pools, rockeries, flowers, trees, corridors, and bridges. All buildings are constructed flush against the water, forming a "water-hugging" architectural ensemble including Spring View Tower, Cool Arrowroot Rain Pavilion, and Osmanthus Hall. The mirror-like water reflects pavilions, merging reality and illusion. As a UNESCO World Heritage site and Tongli''s core attraction, its "seeing the vast in the small" design philosophy is hailed as the paradigm of Jiangnan gardens. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇退思园 / Tuisi Garden, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 含在古镇联票内（联票100元） / Included in the ancient town combo ticket (combo ticket ¥100) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30 / 7:30-17:30 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线同里站转乘705路公交至同里古镇；或从苏州汽车南站乘大巴至同里 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, then bus 705 to the ancient town; or take a coach from Suzhou South Bus Station to Tongli</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tongli_ancient_town_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '珍珠塔',
  name_en = 'Pearl Tower',
  body = '<p>The Pearl Tower is not a physical tower, but the combined name of a long-celebrated opera story in Tongli and the associated Chen family mansion. The tale tells of Fang Qing, a Tongli noble fallen into poverty, seeking help from his aunt Chen Cuie; the Chen family pretended to gift a pearl tower but actually hid silver within it to aid Fang Qing, eventually leading to a happy ending. This "Pearl Tower" legend has been adapted into Suzhou pingtan (storytelling) and opera, becoming Tongli''s most famous folk narrative. The restored Chen mansion is now open to visitors, with displays and scene reconstructions related to the story, allowing guests to relive this tale of Jiangnan loyalty and deep affection spanning centuries. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇珍珠塔景点 / Pearl Tower Scenic Spot, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 含在古镇联票内（联票100元） / Included in the ancient town combo ticket (combo ticket ¥100) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30 / 7:30-17:30 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线同里站转乘705路公交至同里古镇 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, then bus 705 to the ancient town</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tongli_ancient_town_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '三桥',
  name_en = 'Three Bridges',
  body = '<p>The Three Bridges are Tongli''s most iconic landscape — three ancient stone bridges spanning the town''s central waterways: Taiping (Peace), Jili (Good Fortune), and Changqing (Lasting Celebration). Arranged in a "品" (pin) pattern close together, they form the visual focal point of Tongli''s waterside space. In local tradition, newlyweds must walk the three bridges for blessings of peace, fortune, and lasting joy; residents also stroll the bridges during festivals to pray for good luck — a custom sustained for centuries. Below the bridges, emerald water flows gently; on both banks, white walls and black tiles; on the bridges, pedestrians stream; beneath them, boats pass — the most vivid frame of Tongli''s waterside life scroll, and photographers'' favorite angle. - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市吴江区同里镇中心河道三桥区域 / Three Bridges area, central waterway, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 古镇公共区域，无需单独购票（进入古镇需联票100元） / Public area within the ancient town; no separate ticket needed (entry to the ancient town requires combo ticket ¥100) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30 / 7:30-17:30 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线同里站转乘705路公交至同里古镇 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, then bus 705 to the ancient town</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tongli_ancient_town_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '崇本堂',
  name_en = 'Chongben Hall',
  body = '<p>Built in the Xuantong era of the Qing dynasty, Chongben Hall was the residence of wealthy Tongli merchant Qian Youqin, named for the principle of "honoring roots and reflecting on origins." Though modest in scale, it stands out among Tongli''s ancient architecture for its exceptionally refined brick-carved gate towers and wood-carved decorations. The gate tower''s brick carvings are richly layered, depicting theatrical tales and auspicious motifs with meticulous knife work; interior wood-carved doors and windows render scenes from The Romance of the Western Chamber and other operas with lifelike figures. Built along the river in three progressive courtyards — from entrance hall to main hall to inner quarters — it embodies the typical Jiangnan residential pattern of "front hall, rear dwelling," a precious case study of Tongli merchant-class life. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇崇本堂 / Chongben Hall, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 含在古镇联票内（联票100元） / Included in the ancient town combo ticket (combo ticket ¥100) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30 / 7:30-17:30 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线同里站转乘705路公交至同里古镇 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, then bus 705 to the ancient town</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tongli_ancient_town_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '嘉荫堂',
  name_en = 'Jiayin Hall',
  body = '<p>Built in the early Republic of China era, Jiayin Hall was the mansion of wealthy Tongli merchant Liu Bingnan. Grand in scale, its five progressive courtyards unfold sequentially — entrance hall, sedan hall, main hall, inner hall, and rear garden — fully reproducing the spatial sequence of a great Jiangnan household. The main hall is called the纱帽 (Gauze-Hat) Hall because its roof-beam structure resembles the wings of a Ming official''s gauze hat; inside, carved beams and painted pillars showcase superb craftsmanship. Jiayin Hall is laid out along the river, its main gate facing the water with a private pier on the side — a clear imprint of the merchant lifestyle of traveling by boat. The complex balances official dignity with commercial practicality, an excellent window into Tongli''s modern business-social class structure. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇嘉荫堂 / Jiayin Hall, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 含在古镇联票内（联票100元） / Included in the ancient town combo ticket (combo ticket ¥100) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30 / 7:30-17:30 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线同里站转乘705路公交至同里古镇 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, then bus 705 to the ancient town</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tongli_ancient_town_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '耕乐堂',
  name_en = 'Gengle Hall',
  body = '<p>Gengle Hall was built by Ming-era recluse Zhu Xiang, named for the ideal of "farming and studying as family tradition, joy within" — one of Tongli''s oldest surviving dwellings. Zhu Xiang refused official career all his life, finding joy in farming and reading; his residence and garden thus carry the plain, serene character of a literati-scholar. Four progressive courtyards with an attached small garden planted with osmanthus and white-bark pine, its winding paths and corridors embody the austere aesthetics of Ming literati garden-living. Compared with Tongli''s merchant mansions, Gengle Hall has few ornate carvings — instead, plain brick walls and bare wooden beams reveal their natural beauty, preserving the authentic appearance of Ming Jiangnan dwellings and providing precious physical specimens for studying Ming vernacular architecture. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇耕乐堂 / Gengle Hall, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 含在古镇联票内（联票100元） / Included in the ancient town combo ticket (combo ticket ¥100) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30 / 7:30-17:30 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线同里站转乘705路公交至同里古镇 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, then bus 705 to the ancient town</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tongli_ancient_town_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '明清街',
  name_en = 'Ming-Qing Street',
  body = '<p>Ming-Qing Street is Tongli''s main commercial lane, roughly 300 meters long, with Ming-Qing-era shop layouts and street-front character preserved on both sides. Gloss from centuries of foot traffic still gleams on the flagstone pavement. Shops sell Su embroidery, Lake Tai pearls, Tongli''s signature pickled vegetables and "champion''s trotter" braised pork — old brands and new stalls mixing into a unique marketplace atmosphere interweaving past and present. Occasional langpeng (roofed corridors) span the street overhead, sheltering pedestrians from sun and rain — a hallmark of Jiangnan waterside commercial streets. Strolling Ming-Qing Street, the eyes take in the scroll of white walls and black tiles; the nose catches the sweet scent of pickles and lotus-root sweets; the hands feel flagstones'' warmth — senses converge into a complete Tongli memory. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇明清街 / Ming-Qing Street, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 古镇公共区域，无需单独购票（进入古镇需联票100元） / Public area within the ancient town; no separate ticket needed (entry to the ancient town requires combo ticket ¥100) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30 / 7:30-17:30 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线同里站转乘705路公交至同里古镇 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, then bus 705 to the ancient town</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tongli_ancient_town_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '南园茶社',
  name_en = 'Nanyuan Tea House',
  body = '<p>Founded in the late Qing dynasty, Nanyuan Tea House is Tongli''s most iconic traditional tea house, set along the river with two floors of wood-windowed, water-facing Suzhou-style spaces. The house features Biluochun tea and local snacks; afternoon sessions often host Suzhou pingtan performers — plucked strings ringing, melodic voices soaring, particularly moving in the waterside tea-house context. Sitting by the window with a pot of clear tea, watching boats pass on the river outside, pingtan melodies drifting into the ears, time seems to slow its pace. Nanyuan Tea House is more than a place for tea — it is a living specimen of Tongli''s waterside lifestyle, allowing visitors, in a brief pause, to touch the century-long pulse of Jiangnan tea-house culture. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇南园茶社 / Nanyuan Tea House, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 古镇公共区域，无需单独购票；茶饮消费另计（进入古镇需联票100元） / Public area; no separate ticket; tea and snacks charged separately (entry to the ancient town requires combo ticket ¥100) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30（茶社通常营业至晚间） / 7:30-17:30 (tea house generally open into the evening) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线同里站转乘705路公交至同里古镇 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, then bus 705 to the ancient town</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tongli_ancient_town_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '陈去病故居',
  name_en = 'Chen Qubai''s Former Residence',
  body = '<p>Chen Qubai''s Former Residence is the old home of the renowned modern revolutionary and Nanshe (Southern Society) co-founder in Tongli. Chen Qubai (1874–1933) was a pivotal revolutionary literatus of the late Qing and early Republic, co-founding Nanshe with Liu Yazi and others, wielding literature as a weapon to advocate anti-Qing revolution and democratic ideals. The residence follows a traditional Jiangnan dwelling layout; inside, an exhibition of Chen''s life uses letters, photographs, and manuscripts to trace his journey from Tongli scholar to revolutionary pioneer. The quiet, deep old alley where the house sits contrasts sharply with Chen''s turbulent revolutionary career, revealing a truth: modern China''s upheavals often began in an unremarkable room in a small Jiangnan town. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇陈去病故居 / Chen Qubai''s Former Residence, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 含在古镇联票内（联票100元） / Included in the ancient town combo ticket (combo ticket ¥100) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30 / 7:30-17:30 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线同里站转乘705路公交至同里古镇 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, then bus 705 to the ancient town</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tongli_ancient_town_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '罗星洲',
  name_en = 'Luoxing Island',
  body = '<p>Luoxing Island is a small island in Tongli Lake, reached by roughly a ten-minute boat ride from the ancient town pier. Existing structures include the Guanyin Hall, Wenchang Pavilion, and Doumu Pavilion, where Buddhist, Daoist, and Confucian faiths coexist — reflecting Jiangnan folk religion''s inclusive tradition. A small garden on the island features winding paths, lush plantings, and panoramic lake-and-hill views; gazing across the water, Tongli''s black-tiled rooftops appear faintly in the distance. Luoxing Island has been destroyed and rebuilt multiple times through war and disaster; current buildings are largely modern reconstructions, but ancient trees and ruins preserve memories of past turmoil. The boat journey — wind on the water, shimmering waves — makes arriving at the island feel like entering an otherworld paradise, the most ritual-laden segment of any Tongli visit. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇同里湖罗星洲 / Luoxing Island, Tongli Lake, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 含在古镇联票内；需另购船票约10元往返 / Included in the ancient town combo ticket; boat fare approximately ¥10 round trip - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30（受天气影响，大风天气可能停航） / 7:30-17:30 (boat service may be suspended in strong winds) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 同里古镇码头乘船约10分钟抵达 / Boat ride approximately 10 minutes from Tongli ancient town pier</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tongli_ancient_town_sa_10';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '古戏台',
  name_en = 'Ancient Stage',
  body = '<p>The Ancient Stage is located near the entrance of Zhouzhuang and is a classic example of a traditional Jiangnan theatrical stage. First built during the Qing Dynasty and later restored, it retains its original timber-frame structure. The stage faces north, with its back to the water. The front stage features a gable-and-hip roof with upturned flying eaves, while the backstage dressing area is separated from the front by a wooden screen. The stone-pillar foundation raises the stage about one meter above ground, allowing viewing from all four sides. Wood carvings adorn the beams, brackets, and lintels — depicting opera scenes and auspicious motifs with exquisite craftsmanship, making this stage an important artifact for the study of Jiangnan folk carving art. In centuries past, opera troupes were invited to perform Kunqu, Yueju, and Xiju during festivals, with townsfolk gathering at the water''s edge to watch — a cherished memory of Zhouzhuang''s cultural life. Today, the stage still hosts regular performances of Kunqu and other traditional operas, open to all visitors at no additional charge. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市昆山市周庄镇全福路古戏台 / Ancient Stage, Quanfu Road, Zhouzhuang Town, Kunshan, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 包含在周庄古镇联票内（100元）；戏台内观演免费。 / Included in the Zhouzhuang combined ticket (100 RMB); performances inside are free to watch. - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30（古镇开放时间）；演出时间以现场公告为准 / 7:30 AM – 5:30 PM (town opening hours); performance times vary — check on-site announcements. - 交通信息 / Transportation： 进入古镇主入口后步行约3分钟即可到达。 / After entering the main entrance of the town, walk about 3 minutes to reach the stage.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_zhouzhuang_ancient_town_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '双桥',
  name_en = 'Twin Bridges',
  body = '<p>The Twin Bridges — Shide Bridge and Yong''an Bridge — are so named because they intersect at right angles, one arched and one straight, together resembling an ancient Chinese key. Hence they are also called "Key Bridge" (钥匙桥). Shide Bridge is a stone arch bridge built during the Wanli era of the Ming Dynasty (1573–1620); Yong''an Bridge, a stone beam bridge, dates from the same period. The two bridges span the confluence of Yinzi Stream and the North-South River. Water murmurs below; whitewashed houses with dark-tiled roofs line the banks, their reflections creating a natural ink-wash painting. In 1984, the renowned painter Chen Yifei created the oil painting "Memory of Hometown" featuring the Twin Bridges. Recommended by Armand Hammer, the painting was selected by the United Nations for a first-day cover — launching Zhouzhuang onto the world stage and making the Twin Bridges the most recognizable cultural symbol of Jiangnan water towns. At dawn, when mist rises from the river, or at dusk, when golden light floods the scene, the Twin Bridges reveal their most breathtaking beauty — an unmissable subject for photographers. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市昆山市周庄镇银子浜与南北市河交汇处 / Confluence of Yinzi Stream and North-South River, Zhouzhuang Town, Kunshan, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 桥梁本身为公共通道，随时可免费观赏；进入古镇区域需购买联票100元。 / The bridges are public walkways and can be viewed at any time free of charge; entering the town area requires the combined ticket at 100 RMB. - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全天可外观赏（古镇区域7:30-17:30需验票进入） / Viewable from outside at all hours; the town area requires ticket entry from 7:30 AM to 5:30 PM. - 交通信息 / Transportation： 进入古镇后沿南市河方向步行约10分钟即到，沿途可欣赏水乡风貌。 / After entering the town, walk along the South River for about 10 minutes; the route itself offers beautiful water-town scenery.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_zhouzhuang_ancient_town_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '沈厅',
  name_en = 'Shen Hall',
  body = '<p>Shen Hall is the largest private residence in Zhouzhuang, built in 1742 (the seventh year of the Qianlong reign) by Shen Benren, a descendant of the legendary "richest man in Jiangnan" — Shen Wansan. Covering over 2,000 square meters with more than 100 rooms, the complex faces west and comprises seven courtyards with five gateways along a central axis — front hall, main hall, rear hall, and more — flanked by side chambers and connecting corridors in a rigorously ordered layout. The main hall, "Songmao Hall," spans five bays with massive beams and columns. Its nanmu-wood carved floor-to-ceiling latticed windows are works of art, and the brick carvings on the gateways — depicting scenes from "Dream of the Red Chamber" and "Romance of the Western Chamber" — are masterpieces of Jiangnan residential brick sculpture. The layout reflects the classic merchant-family pattern of "shop in front, residence in the middle, garden behind," offering a vital window into the rise and fall of Ming-Qing commercial dynasties. Today, the hall houses an exhibition on Shen Wansan''s life, telling the dramatic story of this legendary merchant. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市昆山市周庄镇南市街85号 / No. 85 Nanshi Street, Zhouzhuang Town, Kunshan, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 包含在周庄古镇联票内（100元）。 / Included in the Zhouzhuang combined ticket (100 RMB). - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30 / 7:30 AM – 5:30 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 进入古镇后沿南市街方向步行约15分钟可达。 / After entering the town, walk along Nanshi Street for about 15 minutes to reach the hall.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_zhouzhuang_ancient_town_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '张厅',
  name_en = 'Zhang Hall',
  body = '<p>Zhang Hall, originally named "Yuyan Hall," was built during the Zhengtong era of the Ming Dynasty (1436–1449) by descendants of Xu Mengqing, brother of the Prince of Zhongshan, Xu Da. It later passed to the Zhang family, hence its current name. The residence faces west, with six courtyards, over 1,000 square meters of floor area, and more than 70 rooms. Its most distinctive feature is that the Mingjing River — a canal running through the town — flows directly through the courtyard, complete with a private mooring where boats could dock. This spatial arrangement, in which "sedans enter through the front gate and boats pass through the house," is one of the most representative layouts of Jiangnan water-town residences. Inside, nanmu-wood columns and intricately carved window lattices remain well preserved. The rear courtyard contains a miniature water garden with banana palms and bamboo — combining the dignity of an official''s mansion with the warmth and vitality of a riverside home. Visiting Zhang Hall is the best way to understand the centuries-old wisdom of "living by the water." - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市昆山市周庄镇西市街 / Xishi Street, Zhouzhuang Town, Kunshan, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 包含在周庄古镇联票内（100元）。 / Included in the Zhouzhuang combined ticket (100 RMB). - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30 / 7:30 AM – 5:30 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 进入古镇后沿西市街方向步行约10分钟可达。 / After entering the town, walk along Xishi Street for about 10 minutes to reach the hall.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_zhouzhuang_ancient_town_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '富安桥',
  name_en = 'Fu''an Bridge',
  body = '<p>First built during the Zhizheng era of the Yuan Dynasty (1341–1368), Fu''an Bridge was funded by Shen Wansi, the younger brother of the legendary merchant Shen Wansan. After multiple restorations, it is one of the oldest surviving stone arch bridges in Zhouzhuang. The bridge spans the North-South River in a single arch, about 17 meters long, with a gently arched deck paved in granite slabs. Its most distinctive feature is the four corner buildings — "bridge towers" — that rise from the bridge''s four corners, creating the rare architectural form of "bridge and building as one." The bridge deck remains a thoroughfare, while the towers house shops and teahouses — a design that fuses transportation and commerce, exceedingly rare among Jiangnan water-town bridges. The towers'' upturned eaves reflect in the water; from a distance, they look like pavilions floating on the river. Legend has it that Shen Wansan ran a small stall near the bridge before his fortune was made, and "Fu''an" (literally "wealth and peace") commemorates his rise. Standing on the bridge, one sees the staggered riverside dwellings along both banks, with awning boats gliding slowly beneath the arch — a quintessential water-town tableau. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市昆山市周庄镇南北市河上 / Over the North-South River, Zhouzhuang Town, Kunshan, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 桥本身为公共通道；进入古镇区域需购买联票100元。 / The bridge is a public walkway; entering the town area requires the combined ticket at 100 RMB. - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全天可通行（古镇区域7:30-17:30需验票） / Crossable at all hours; the town area requires ticket entry from 7:30 AM to 5:30 PM. - 交通信息 / Transportation： 进入古镇后沿南北市河方向步行约8分钟可达。 / After entering the town, walk along the North-South River for about 8 minutes to reach the bridge.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_zhouzhuang_ancient_town_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '周庄博物馆',
  name_en = 'Zhouzhuang Museum',
  body = '<p>Zhouzhuang Museum is located within the historic Zhu family residence — a comprehensive museum dedicated to the local history and culture of Zhouzhuang. The building itself is a typical Jiangnan residence with a Qing Dynasty layout: whitewashed walls, dark tiles, courtyards, and sky-wells. Multiple exhibition halls cover the town''s founding, commercial development, folk customs, and notable figures. The collection includes precious Ming and Qing-era contracts, land deeds, merchant account books, ancient coins, and folk implements — with the richest materials relating to Shen Wansan and traditional water-town daily life. Models, photographs, and multimedia displays vividly illustrate how Zhouzhuang grew "from water into a town, and from commerce into prosperity." Visiting the museum is the ideal starting point for understanding Zhouzhuang: build a historical framework here first, then explore the town''s sights — and the experience will be transformed. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市昆山市周庄镇后港街38号 / No. 38 Hougang Street, Zhouzhuang Town, Kunshan, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 包含在周庄古镇联票内（100元）。 / Included in the Zhouzhuang combined ticket (100 RMB). - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30 / 7:30 AM – 5:30 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 进入古镇后沿后港街方向步行约10分钟可达。 / After entering the town, walk along Hougang Street for about 10 minutes to reach the museum.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_zhouzhuang_ancient_town_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '怪楼',
  name_en = 'Guailou (Strange Tower)',
  body = '<p>Guailou is a distinctive attraction within Zhouzhuang themed around optical illusions and interactive experiences. Standing three stories tall, its exterior already differs subtly from the surrounding traditional buildings, hinting at the novelty within. Multiple themed rooms inside use principles of optics, geometry, and perspective to create astonishing visual effects: one room has a sloping floor with level walls, producing a sensation of weightlessness; another uses mirrors and lighting to simulate infinite space; yet another employs 3D murals that make visitors feel they have stepped into a painting. Each space encourages hands-on experience and creative photography, making it tremendous fun. Guailou injects a splash of modern artistic vibrancy into this thousand-year-old town, where tradition and creativity collide to delightful effect. It is especially popular with younger visitors and families — a lighthearted counterpoint to the town''s historical sights. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市昆山市周庄镇西市街 / Xishi Street, Zhouzhuang Town, Kunshan, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 不含在古镇联票内，需单独购票，票价约20元（以现场为准）。 / Not included in the combined ticket; separate admission of approximately 20 RMB (subject to on-site pricing). - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00 AM – 5:00 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 进入古镇后沿西市街方向步行约12分钟可达。 / After entering the town, walk along Xishi Street for about 12 minutes to reach the tower.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_zhouzhuang_ancient_town_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '贞丰桥',
  name_en = 'Zhenfeng Bridge',
  body = '<p>Zhenfeng Bridge is a single-arch stone bridge spanning the Zhongshi River. Its date of original construction is unknown; the current structure dates from a Qing Dynasty rebuilding. "Zhenfeng" derives from Zhouzhuang''s ancient name — "Zhenfeng Li." During the Yuanyou era of the Song Dynasty (1086), a local official named Zhou Digonglang established a manor here and donated farmland to Quanfu Temple. The grateful residents renamed the place "Zhouzhuang" in his honor. The name "Zhenfeng Bridge" is a living fossil of this thousand-year-old renaming. The bridge is modest in length, with an elegant arch, plain stone railings, and stone steps at both ends. Riverside houses rise directly from the water; willows dip their branches toward the river; an occasional sculling boat drifts past with a rhythmic creak of the oar, complementing the ancient bridge''s quiet charm. Fewer tourists gather here than at the Twin Bridges or Fu''an Bridge, making Zhenfeng Bridge a serene spot to sit, slow down, and savor the unhurried rhythms of water-town life. A teahouse once stood by the bridge, and it is said that Southern Society poets gathered here to compose verse, adding a literary luster to its stones. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市昆山市周庄镇中市河上 / Over the Zhongshi River, Zhouzhuang Town, Kunshan, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 桥本身为公共通道；进入古镇区域需购买联票100元。 / The bridge is a public walkway; entering the town area requires the combined ticket at 100 RMB. - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全天可通行（古镇区域7:30-17:30需验票） / Crossable at all hours; the town area requires ticket entry from 7:30 AM to 5:30 PM. - 交通信息 / Transportation： 进入古镇后沿中市河方向步行约8分钟可达。 / After entering the town, walk along the Zhongshi River for about 8 minutes to reach the bridge.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_zhouzhuang_ancient_town_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '全福讲寺',
  name_en = 'Quanfu Temple',
  body = '<p>Quanfu Temple stands on the shore of Lake Bianxian, south of Zhouzhuang Old Town. Founded in 1086 during the Song Dynasty''s Yuanyou era — built on land donated by Zhou Digonglang — it is the oldest Buddhist temple in Zhouzhuang. The temple rises directly from the lake, with its main halls standing at the water''s edge. From a distance, the halls and pavilions appear to float upon the water, earning it the name "Buddhist Kingdom on Water" (水中佛国). The complex faces south, with a gate, main hall, and scripture repository along its central axis. The architecture is grand and solemn — golden walls, dark tiles, layered flying eaves — striking against the blue water and sky. The temple once housed a Song Dynasty bronze bell whose peal carried for miles; "Quanfu Dawn Bell" was one of the historic Eight Scenes of Zhouzhuang. Destroyed and rebuilt multiple times, the current structures are modern reconstructions that nonetheless preserve the layout and dignity of a traditional Buddhist monastery. At dawn, the temple bell rings across the misty lake, its sound blending with the water''s shimmer to instill a deep tranquility. From the upper floors of the scripture repository, one looks out over the vast expanse of Lake Bianxian, with Zhouzhuang''s water-town panorama spread below — one of the few elevated vantage points in the town. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市昆山市周庄镇白蚬湖畔全福路 / Quanfu Road, Lake Bianxian shore, Zhouzhuang Town, Kunshan, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 包含在周庄古镇联票内（100元）。 / Included in the Zhouzhuang combined ticket (100 RMB). - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30 / 7:30 AM – 5:30 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 进入古镇后沿全福路向南步行约15分钟可达白蚬湖畔。 / After entering the town, walk south along Quanfu Road for about 15 minutes to reach the temple on the shore of Lake Bianxian.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_zhouzhuang_ancient_town_sa_10';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '相门入口',
  name_en = 'Xiangmen Entrance',
  body = '<p>Xiangmen, also known as Jiangmen (Craftsman''s Gate), is one of the eight ancient gates of Suzhou, named after the legend that King Helu of Wu ordered swordsmiths to work here. The restored city wall now stands majestically at the southern end of Pingjiang Road, serving as the primary gateway for visitors entering this thousand-year-old historic block. The surrounding city wall heritage park is shaded by lush greenery, and climbing the wall offers panoramic views of the ancient city''s canal-and-alley landscape. It serves both as the starting point of a Pingjiang Road stroll and as a significant landmark for appreciating Suzhou''s city layout and gate culture. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区相门城墙遗址公园（平江路南端） / Xiangmen City Wall Heritage Park, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu (Southern end of Pingjiang Road) - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费 / Free admission - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全天开放 / Open all day - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁1号线相门站步行约5分钟；公交2路、9路、32路相门站 / Metro Line 1 Xiangmen Station, walk ~5 min; Bus Routes 2, 9, 32 Xiangmen Stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_pingjiang_road_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '苑桥',
  name_en = 'Yuan Bridge',
  body = '<p>Yuan Bridge spans the Pingjiang River as a classic stone arch bridge embodying the Jiangnan water-town aesthetic. Its name derives from the royal or private gardens that once graced its vicinity; though those gardens have faded into history, the bridge''s elegant form still evokes the prosperity of bygone eras. Standing on the bridge, one gazes east at whitewashed residences lining the canal and west at the winding flagstone path, where reflections and dwellings create a charming interplay. Yuan Bridge is not only a key node in Pingjiang Road''s dual water-and-land layout but also an ideal spot for photographers and visitors to capture the iconic imagery of "small bridge, flowing water, and humble home." - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区平江路与苑桥弄交汇处 / Intersection of Pingjiang Road and Yuanqiao Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费（街区公共区域） / Free (public area of the block) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全天开放 / Open all day - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁1号线相门站步行约8分钟；公交2路、9路平江路站 / Metro Line 1 Xiangmen Station, walk ~8 min; Bus Routes 2, 9 Pingjiang Road Stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_pingjiang_road_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '思婆桥',
  name_en = 'Sipo Bridge',
  body = '<p>Sipo Bridge is among the oldest bridges on Pingjiang Road. Legend attributes its name—"Sipo" meaning "remembering the granny"—to a kind old woman who offered tea and alms here; another theory links it to "Shipo" (female shaman or nun). Regardless of origin, this single-arch stone bridge has endured centuries of weather, its flagstones polished to a warm sheen by countless footsteps, its low rail blending seamlessly with the modest riverside dwellings. In morning mist or evening lamplight, Sipo Bridge paints a faint ink-wash canal scene, serving as one of the finest windows into Suzhou''s neighborhood philosophy that "bridges are life itself." - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区平江路思婆桥段 / Sipo Bridge Section, Pingjiang Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费（街区公共区域） / Free (public area of the block) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全天开放 / Open all day - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁1号线相门站步行约10分钟 / Metro Line 1 Xiangmen Station, walk ~10 min</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_pingjiang_road_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '丁香巷',
  name_en = 'Dingxiang Lane (Lilac Lane)',
  body = '<p>Dingxiang Lane is a narrow, deeply secluded branch lane east of Pingjiang Road, named after the lilac trees that once filled it. In late spring and early summer, purple petals drift onto flagstones, perfuming the alley with a subtle fragrance. It also houses the former residence of the modern scholar Gu Jiegang, intertwining academic heritage with floral poetry. Old doorways stand half-open, cats dart past, and drying clothes coexist with carved lintels in a vivid neighborhood tableau. With its quietude and scent, Dingxiang Lane becomes the most moving literary corner beyond the bustling main street, drawing writers and wanderers who linger here in search of inspiration. - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区平江路东侧丁香巷 / Dingxiang Lane, east side of Pingjiang Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费（街区公共区域） / Free (public area of the block) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全天开放 / Open all day - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁1号线相门站步行约12分钟 / Metro Line 1 Xiangmen Station, walk ~12 min</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_pingjiang_road_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '中张家巷（评弹博物馆）',
  name_en = 'Zhongzhangjia Lane (Suzhou Pingtan Museum)',
  body = '<p>Zhongzhangjia Lane is intimately tied to Pingtan culture. The Suzhou Pingtan Museum housed here is China''s only museum dedicated to Suzhou Pingtan (storytelling and musical performance). Its collections include extensive historical documents, manuscripts, records, and stage props tracing Pingtan''s evolution from the Qing dynasty to today. The highlight is the regular live performances: visitors can sit in a traditional storytelling house, sip Biluochun tea, and hear authentic Pingtan openings, experiencing the rhythmic cadence of Wu dialect singing and the delicate accompaniment of stringed instruments. This is an essential殿堂 for understanding Suzhou''s "sound culture" and Pingjiang Road''s most vibrant site of living heritage. - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区平江路中张家巷14号 / No. 14 Zhongzhangjia Lane, Pingjiang Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费参观，现场演出需另行购票（约10-30元） / Free museum admission; live performances require separate ticket (~10–30 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 周二至周日9:00-17:00（周一闭馆），演出时间通常为下午 / Tue–Sun 9:00–17:00 (closed Mon); performances typically in the afternoon - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁1号线相门站步行约12分钟；公交2路、9路平江路站 / Metro Line 1 Xiangmen Station, walk ~12 min; Bus Routes 2, 9 Pingjiang Road Stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_pingjiang_road_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '钮家巷（状元博物馆）',
  name_en = 'Niujia Lane (Suzhou Zhuangyuan Museum)',
  body = '<p>The Suzhou Zhuangyuan Museum on Niujia Lane is set within Fengchi Garden, the former residence of Qing dynasty Zhuangyuan Pan Shi''en. Suzhou has produced over fifty Zhuangyuan since the Song dynasty—more than any other city in China—earning the title "Home of Zhuangyuan." Using Pan Shi''en''s life as an entry point, the museum displays exam papers, honor plaques, robes, and daily artifacts, comprehensively illustrating the journey from arduous study to imperial triumph and the profound influence of Zhuangyuan families on Suzhou''s educational traditions. The residence itself is an elegant Suzhou mansion with spacious halls and graceful landscaping, allowing visitors to appreciate the layout aesthetics of Jiangnan scholar-official dwellings alongside the exhibits. It is a cultural hall where scholarly spirit and architectural beauty merge seamlessly. - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区平江路钮家巷3号 / No. 3 Niujia Lane, Pingjiang Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费参观 / Free admission - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 周二至周日9:00-17:00（周一闭馆） / Tue–Sun 9:00–17:00 (closed Mon) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁1号线相门站步行约15分钟；公交2路、9路平江路站 / Metro Line 1 Xiangmen Station, walk ~15 min; Bus Routes 2, 9 Pingjiang Road Stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_pingjiang_road_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '大儒巷',
  name_en = 'Daru Lane (Great Scholar Lane)',
  body = '<p>Daru Lane takes its name from the renowned Ming dynasty scholar Wang Ren—"Daru" (Great Scholar) itself distills Suzhou''s reverence for learning. Several Ming and Qing residences and scholar sites still survive here, their blue-brick gateways and lattice windows hinting at a bygone literary aura. Meanwhile, Daru Lane is also one of Pingjiang Road''s most concentrated artisan branches, dotted with Su embroidery studios, nut-carving workshops, and woodwork shops, where literati ethos and craftsman spirit run parallel. The lane''s intimate scale and sparse foot traffic invite unhurried exploration, allowing visitors to read between doorways and window frames the symbiotic humanistic ecology of Suzhou''s "letters and crafts." - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区平江路大儒巷 / Daru Lane, Pingjiang Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费（街区公共区域） / Free (public area of the block) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全天开放 / Open all day - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁1号线临顿路站步行约8分钟 / Metro Line 1 Lindun Road Station, walk ~8 min</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_pingjiang_road_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '悬桥巷（洪钧故居、船屋）',
  name_en = 'Xuanqiao Lane (Hong Jun''s Former Residence & Boat House)',
  body = '<p>Xuanqiao Lane, named after a suspension bridge that once stood at its entrance, is Pingjiang Road''s most legendary branch. No. 27 is the former residence of late-Qing Zhuangyuan Hong Jun, who served as envoy to several European nations and later lived here with the famous courtesan Sa Jinhua—a story still avidly recounted. The residence''s most distinctive feature is a "boat house"—an entire building constructed in the shape of a boat, with two cabins and orderly hull-style lattice windows, resembling a dry-docked vessel in the lane, standing as Suzhou''s most creative singular example of residential architecture. The lane itself is deep and tranquil, old eaves intertwining with creeping vines; a stroll here feels like walking into a fold of late-Qing turbulence compressed by time. - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区平江路悬桥巷27号 / No. 27 Xuanqiao Lane, Pingjiang Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费参观（故居部分区域不定期开放） / Free admission (some areas of the residence open intermittently) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 街区全天开放；故居开放时间不固定，建议提前咨询 / Lane open all day; residence hours vary, inquire in advance - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁1号线临顿路站步行约10分钟 / Metro Line 1 Lindun Road Station, walk ~10 min</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_pingjiang_road_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '青石桥',
  name_en = 'Qingshi Bridge (Bluestone Bridge)',
  body = '<p>Qingshi Bridge, named for its bluestone construction, is one of Pingjiang River''s most understated yet evocative ancient bridges. The bridge vicinity is Pingjiang Road''s most lived-in stretch, where several canal-side teahouses extend wooden awnings with tables half-reaching over the water. As patrons sip tea and chat, awning boats glide slowly beneath the bridge, composing a living water-town tableau. Qingshi Bridge is also among the most enchanting night scenes on Pingjiang Road: after dark, lantern reflections float on the canal, teahouse warm light mirrors on the water, and the ancient bridge silhouette flickers between brightness and shadow. We recommend lingering at least half an hour—sit in a bridge-side teahouse and, over a cup of Suzhou Biluochun tea, truly read Pingjiang Road''s philosophy that "slowness is beauty." - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区平江路青石桥段 / Qingshi Bridge Section, Pingjiang Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费（街区公共区域） / Free (public area of the block) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全天开放 / Open all day - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁1号线临顿路站步行约12分钟 / Metro Line 1 Lindun Road Station, walk ~12 min</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_pingjiang_road_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '全晋会馆 - 苏州戏曲博物馆',
  name_en = 'Quanjin Guild Hall - Suzhou Chinese Opera Museum',
  body = '<p>Quanjin Guild Hall is Pingjiang Road''s most architecturally stunning landmark. Built with funds raised by Shanxi merchants doing business in Suzhou during the Qianlong era, it served for fellow-provincial gatherings and business deliberations. The hall''s most striking feature is its theater building: above the stage, a caisson ceiling composed of hundreds of carved wooden components stacked into an inverted dome, painted red and gold, stands as one of the finest surviving ancient theater caissons in the Jiangnan region. Today the guild hall has been transformed into the Suzhou Chinese Opera Museum, displaying artifacts and visual materials of Kunqu, Peking Opera, Su Opera, and other genres, with regular Kunqu performances. This building is both a historical imprint of Shanxi merchants in Suzhou and a three-dimensional textbook of Chinese traditional opera art. - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区平江路中张家巷6号 / No. 6 Zhongzhangjia Lane, Pingjiang Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费参观，昆曲演出需另行购票（约50-100元） / Free museum admission; Kunqu performances require separate ticket (~50–100 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 周二至周日9:00-17:00（周一闭馆）；昆曲演出时间请关注官方公告 / Tue–Sun 9:00–17:00 (closed Mon); check official notices for Kunqu performance times - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁1号线相门站步行约12分钟；公交2路、9路平江路站 / Metro Line 1 Xiangmen Station, walk ~12 min; Bus Routes 2, 9 Pingjiang Road Stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_pingjiang_road_sa_10';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '燕誉堂',
  name_en = 'Yanyu Hall (Hall of Swallow''s Honor)',
  body = '<p>Yanyu Hall is Lion Grove Garden''s main hall and the first building visitors encounter. "Yanyu" derives from the Shijing (Book of Odes): "The gentleman has wine, and the guests feast joyfully"—where "Yan" means banquet and "Yu" means delight. The hall''s interior is elegantly appointed, with screen paintings depicting Lion Grove panoramas and poetic inscriptions by masters past. Through the windows, the garden''s lake-stone labyrinth already looms tantalizingly. Yanyu Hall establishes the garden''s tone of festive exploration, signaling that Lion Grove is not merely for contemplation but for a sensory adventure brimming with playfulness. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区园林路23号狮子林内 / Inside Lion Grove Garden, No. 23 Yuanlin Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季40元/淡季30元（含全园游览） / Peak season 40 RMB / Off-peak season 30 RMB (includes full garden access) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 旺季（3月-11月）7:30-18:00；淡季（12月-次年2月）7:30-17:30 / Peak season (Mar–Nov) 7:30–18:00; Off-peak season (Dec–Feb) 7:30–17:30 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约15分钟；公交1路、5路、101路拙政园站 / Metro Line 4 Beisita Station, walk ~15 min; Bus Routes 1, 5, 101 Humble Administrator''s Garden Stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lion_grove_garden_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '小方厅',
  name_en = 'Xiaofang Hall (Small Square Hall)',
  body = '<p>Xiaofang Hall sits directly north of Yanyu Hall—a small yet meticulously designed square hall. The name "Xiaofang" refers both to its regular square plan and to the garden philosophy of "seeing the cosmos within a square inch." Its most ingenious feature is the window design: east and west ornamental windows act as picture frames, precisely cropping different fragments of the rockery group, so that standing inside, visitors preview sections of the stone labyrinth they will soon enter. This framing technique turns the diminutive hall into a visual prelude for the entire rockery. The interior is restrained—simple furnishings and blank walls creating an austere elegance that contrasts brilliantly with the rugged lake stones beyond the windows, a dialogue of softness and strength. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区园林路23号狮子林内 / Inside Lion Grove Garden, No. 23 Yuanlin Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季40元/淡季30元（含全园游览） / Peak season 40 RMB / Off-peak season 30 RMB (includes full garden access) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 旺季（3月-11月）7:30-18:00；淡季（12月-次年2月）7:30-17:30 / Peak season (Mar–Nov) 7:30–18:00; Off-peak season (Dec–Feb) 7:30–17:30 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约15分钟；公交1路、5路、101路拙政园站 / Metro Line 4 Beisita Station, walk ~15 min; Bus Routes 1, 5, 101 Humble Administrator''s Garden Stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lion_grove_garden_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '九狮峰',
  name_en = 'Nine Lion Peak',
  body = '<p>Nine Lion Peak is the rockery group''s most arresting单体 and the most direct visual proof of the garden''s naming origin. Composed of multiple Taihu (lake) stones assembled in their natural forms, its overall silhouette and surface undulations reveal lion shapes—some head-raised, some crouching, some playing, some guarding. Careful observation identifies nine lions in distinct, vivid poses. Lion Grove Garden was built by Yuan dynasty monk Tianru to honor his master Zhongfeng; "lion" refers both to the rockery''s lion-like forms and to the Buddhist metaphor of the "lion''s roar" symbolizing the power of enlightenment preaching. Nine Lion Peak stands at the rockery entrance between Xiaofang Hall and Zhibai Pavilion, serving as both the labyrinth''s landmark and a extraordinary work where Buddhist Chan philosophy and secular stone-appreciation aesthetics intersect. - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区园林路23号狮子林内（小方厅与指柏轩之间假山入口） / Inside Lion Grove Garden, rockery entrance between Xiaofang Hall and Zhibai Pavilion, No. 23 Yuanlin Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季40元/淡季30元（含全园游览） / Peak season 40 RMB / Off-peak season 30 RMB (includes full garden access) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 旺季（3月-11月）7:30-18:00；淡季（12月-次年2月）7:30-17:30 / Peak season (Mar–Nov) 7:30–18:00; Off-peak season (Dec–Feb) 7:30–17:30 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约15分钟；公交1路、5路、101路拙政园站 / Metro Line 4 Beisita Station, walk ~15 min; Bus Routes 1, 5, 101 Humble Administrator''s Garden Stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lion_grove_garden_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '指柏轩',
  name_en = 'Zhibai Pavilion (Point-to-Cypress Pavilion)',
  body = '<p>Zhibai Pavilion is the main viewing hall on the south side of the rockery group. Its name originates from a Chan (Zen) koan: when a monk asked Zhaozhou Congshen, "What is the meaning of the Patriarch''s coming from the West?" Zhaozhou replied, "The cypress tree in the courtyard"—pointing to an ordinary object to expound the dharma''s essence, transcending textual convention. Zhibai Pavilion embodies this Chan spirit in garden architecture: an ancient cypress stands verdant and upright before the hall, rugged lion-shaped rocks behind it; from within, one can survey the entire stone labyrinth while contemplating the Chan insight that "the path is right before your eyes." The pavilion once served as a monk''s meditation space, later transforming into a literati gathering place, with poetic inscriptions on screen panels. It is Lion Grove''s building where Buddhist Chan thought and Jiangnan garden viewing are most tightly interwoven. - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区园林路23号狮子林内 / Inside Lion Grove Garden, No. 23 Yuanlin Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季40元/淡季30元（含全园游览） / Peak season 40 RMB / Off-peak season 30 RMB (includes full garden access) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 旺季（3月-11月）7:30-18:00；淡季（12月-次年2月）7:30-17:30 / Peak season (Mar–Nov) 7:30–18:00; Off-peak season (Dec–Feb) 7:30–17:30 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约15分钟；公交1路、5路、101路拙政园站 / Metro Line 4 Beisita Station, walk ~15 min; Bus Routes 1, 5, 101 Humble Administrator''s Garden Stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lion_grove_garden_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '花篮厅',
  name_en = 'Hualan Hall (Flower Basket Hall)',
  body = '<p>Hualan Hall is an exquisite hall on the south side of Lion Grove''s pool, named after the flower-basket motifs carved on its dangling-lotus columns (short eaves columns). These carved flower baskets demonstrate superb craftsmanship—each basket holds different blooms: peony, lotus, plum, or orchid, with flowing lines and layered depth, representing the finest of Suzhou garden wood-carved ornamentation. The hall is partially built over the water, its base partly submerged in the pool. Sitting inside, one views the pool reflections and the full rockery panorama opposite, where rippling light and rugged peaks converge, creating the uncanny visual experience of "the hall in the water, the mountain in the mirror." Interior displays follow a floral theme, with seasonal vase flowers creating an engaging contrast between "carved flowers" and "real flowers." - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区园林路23号狮子林内 / Inside Lion Grove Garden, No. 23 Yuanlin Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季40元/淡季30元（含全园游览） / Peak season 40 RMB / Off-peak season 30 RMB (includes full garden access) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 旺季（3月-11月）7:30-18:00；淡季（12月-次年2月）7:30-17:30 / Peak season (Mar–Nov) 7:30–18:00; Off-peak season (Dec–Feb) 7:30–17:30 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约15分钟；公交1路、5路、101路拙政园站 / Metro Line 4 Beisita Station, walk ~15 min; Bus Routes 1, 5, 101 Humble Administrator''s Garden Stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lion_grove_garden_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '真趣亭',
  name_en = 'Zhenqu Pavilion (True Delight Pavilion)',
  body = '<p>Zhenqu Pavilion sits beside the pool on the east side of the rockery group, the garden''s building most deeply connected to Emperor Qianlong. During his six southern tours, Qianlong visited Lion Grove each time; on one occasion, lost in delight within the rockery maze, he brush-wrote "Zhen You Qu" (truly interesting). A accompanying minister deemed "You Qu" too colloquial and tactfully suggested keeping "Zhen" and changing to "Qu" (delight), preserving imperial joy while elevating literary refinement—Qianlong gladly agreed. "Zhen Qu" (True Delight) carries both the documentary sense of the emperor''s garden pleasure and the Chan philosophical dimension of "true suchness"—only by playful wandering in the labyrinthine rockery does one attain life''s "true delight." The plaque remains preserved inside the pavilion, one of Lion Grove''s most precious historical artifacts. - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区园林路23号狮子林内 / Inside Lion Grove Garden, No. 23 Yuanlin Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季40元/淡季30元（含全园游览） / Peak season 40 RMB / Off-peak season 30 RMB (includes full garden access) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 旺季（3月-11月）7:30-18:00；淡季（12月-次年2月）7:30-17:30 / Peak season (Mar–Nov) 7:30–18:00; Off-peak season (Dec–Feb) 7:30–17:30 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约15分钟；公交1路、5路、101路拙政园站 / Metro Line 4 Beisita Station, walk ~15 min; Bus Routes 1, 5, 101 Humble Administrator''s Garden Stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lion_grove_garden_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '石舫',
  name_en = 'Stone Boat',
  body = '<p>The Stone Boat is a boat-shaped water structure in Lion Grove''s pool, entirely constructed of stone with realistic bow, cabin, and stern forms, stone railings along the sides, and stone tables and benches inside for resting. Fixed in place, it is called an "untethered boat"—an image derived from Zhuangzi''s philosophical parable of drifting "like an untethered boat," symbolizing spiritual freedom and non-attachment. The stone boat is a highly representative Jiangnan garden building type: it fulfills the desire to linger on water while creating unique aesthetic tension through the static paradox of "a boat that stays, water that moves." Sitting inside the cabin, surrounded by water on all sides, pool reflections and distant rockery compose a framed view—as if truly boating on a lake yet without risk of wind or waves, achieving playful delight between reality and illusion. - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区园林路23号狮子林内 / Inside Lion Grove Garden, No. 23 Yuanlin Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季40元/淡季30元（含全园游览） / Peak season 40 RMB / Off-peak season 30 RMB (includes full garden access) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 旺季（3月-11月）7:30-18:00；淡季（12月-次年2月）7:30-17:30 / Peak season (Mar–Nov) 7:30–18:00; Off-peak season (Dec–Feb) 7:30–17:30 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约15分钟；公交1路、5路、101路拙政园站 / Metro Line 4 Beisita Station, walk ~15 min; Bus Routes 1, 5, 101 Humble Administrator''s Garden Stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lion_grove_garden_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '暗香疏影楼',
  name_en = 'Anxiang Shuying Building (Faint Scent & Sparse Shadows Building)',
  body = '<p>Anxiang Shuying Building sits at the northwest corner of Lion Grove, a two-story pavilion themed around plum appreciation. Its name draws from the Northern Song recluse Lin Bu''s immortal plum verses: "Sparse shadows slant across clear shallow water; faint scent drifts at moonlit dusk"—two lines that virtually defined the plum blossom aesthetic standard in Chinese culture: sparse branches, subtle fragrance. Several ancient plum trees grow before the building; in winter bloom, ascending the upper floor reveals branch shadows reflected in the pool and delicate fragrance drifting through windows, making the poem''s imagery tangibly realized through direct sensory experience. Interior displays include related poetic calligraphy and paintings; window lattice designs deliberately lower the sightline to match plum-viewing angles. From naming to spatial design, the building is tightly bound to the plum theme—an outstanding example of translating poetic imagery into architectural experience at Lion Grove. - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区园林路23号狮子林内 / Inside Lion Grove Garden, No. 23 Yuanlin Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季40元/淡季30元（含全园游览） / Peak season 40 RMB / Off-peak season 30 RMB (includes full garden access) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 旺季（3月-11月）7:30-18:00；淡季（12月-次年2月）7:30-17:30 / Peak season (Mar–Nov) 7:30–18:00; Off-peak season (Dec–Feb) 7:30–17:30 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约15分钟；公交1路、5路、101路拙政园站 / Metro Line 4 Beisita Station, walk ~15 min; Bus Routes 1, 5, 101 Humble Administrator''s Garden Stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lion_grove_garden_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '湖心亭',
  name_en = 'Huxin Pavilion (Lake-Center Pavilion)',
  body = '<p>Huxin Pavilion occupies the exact center of Lion Grove''s main pool—a single-story hexagonal pavilion connected to both banks by stone curved bridges. Though small, it holds the absolute core of the garden''s spatial composition: standing inside with a 360-degree panorama, the rockery group, Zhibai Pavilion, Hualan Hall, Stone Boat, and other major scenes encircle the view like a painting; the pavilion itself becomes a borrowed-view object for other buildings, creating a mutual viewing relationship of "the pavilion as center, every scene seeing every scene." Huxin Pavilion''s design embodies Suzhou garden''s essence of "seeing the vast through the small": the smallest-volume building placed at the center of the largest-scale water surface, the pavilion''s transparency换取 the pool''s sense of expansiveness—inside, one does not feel the pavilion small but the pool vast. Under morning light or evening shadow, the pavilion floats on the water as one of Lion Grove''s most photogenic spots. - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区园林路23号狮子林内 / Inside Lion Grove Garden, No. 23 Yuanlin Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季40元/淡季30元（含全园游览） / Peak season 40 RMB / Off-peak season 30 RMB (includes full garden access) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 旺季（3月-11月）7:30-18:00；淡季（12月-次年2月）7:30-17:30 / Peak season (Mar–Nov) 7:30–18:00; Off-peak season (Dec–Feb) 7:30–17:30 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约15分钟；公交1路、5路、101路拙政园站 / Metro Line 4 Beisita Station, walk ~15 min; Bus Routes 1, 5, 101 Humble Administrator''s Garden Stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lion_grove_garden_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '卧云室',
  name_en = 'Woyun Chamber (Cloud-Reclining Chamber)',
  body = '<p>Woyun Chamber occupies the highest point of Lion Grove''s rockery—the garden''s highest-altitude building and the only Chan meditation space embedded within a stone peak. "Woyun" (Cloud-Reclining) is richly poetic and Chan-inflected: clouds above, the chamber amid the rocks, the person inside seemingly resting on clouds looking down at the mortal world; it also echoes monk Tianru''s "cloud-and-water Chan mind" practice philosophy. The chamber is extremely small, accommodating only a few seated people, austere inside—just meditation cushions and a simple table contrasting with the rough stone walls outside. Gazing outward, rock tunnels, pool ripples, and distant garden walls compose a framed view; the spatial elevation confers a genuine sense of psychological detachment—looking down from the "clouds" upon the "red dust." This is Lion Grove''s most exquisite work of embedding architecture within rockery, and the supreme expression of Chan philosophy merged with garden art. - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区园林路23号狮子林内（假山群最高处） / Inside Lion Grove Garden, highest point of the rockery group, No. 23 Yuanlin Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季40元/淡季30元（含全园游览） / Peak season 40 RMB / Off-peak season 30 RMB (includes full garden access) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 旺季（3月-11月）7:30-18:00；淡季（12月-次年2月）7:30-17:30 / Peak season (Mar–Nov) 7:30–18:00; Off-peak season (Dec–Feb) 7:30–17:30 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约15分钟；公交1路、5路、101路拙政园站 / Metro Line 4 Beisita Station, walk ~15 min; Bus Routes 1, 5, 101 Humble Administrator''s Garden Stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lion_grove_garden_sa_10';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '古木交柯',
  name_en = 'Ancient Trees Interlocking',
  body = '<p>Ancient Trees Interlocking lies at the entrance area of Lingering Garden, greeting visitors as the first scenic vista upon stepping into the garden. An ancient cypress and a camellia intertwine their branches, resembling lovers leaning upon each other, hence the name "Interlocking." This scene embodies the harmonious coexistence of rugged strength and delicate beauty, reflecting the Chinese philosophical concept of yin-yang complementarity. The Ming dynasty painter Wen Zhengming once depicted similar imagery; this living scene in Lingering Garden serves as a vivid re-creation and a superb example of the garden design principle of "seeing the grand in the small." - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区留园路338号 / 338 Liuyuan Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季55元，淡季45元 / Peak season: 55 CNY; Off-peak season: 45 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30（旺季至18:00） / 7:30–17:30 (peak season until 18:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐公交游1路、85路至留园站下车，步行约2分钟即达入口；古木交柯位于留园大门入口内侧，入园后沿主路前行即可看到。 Take Bus Tour Line 1 or Route 85 to Liuyuan Station, walk about 2 minutes to the entrance. Ancient Trees Interlocking is located just inside the main gate along the primary path.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lingering_garden_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '绿荫轩',
  name_en = 'Green Shade Pavilion',
  body = '<p>Green Shade Pavilion sits in the central part of Lingering Garden, adjacent to Hanbi Mountain House. It is a small pavilion-style structure built against a wall and facing the water. Ancient trees before the pavilion cast dense shade; sitting here in summer, one enjoys gentle breezes and faint lotus scents—a uniquely tranquil pleasure. The name "Green Shade" highlights its environmental essence—using tree canopy to create a cooling ambiance, a classic example of Suzhou garden techniques of "borrowed and screened views." With simple furnishings and verdant views beyond the windows, a single table and chair suffice for tea-sipping and scenery appreciation—arguably the most ideal spot for quiet contemplation in Lingering Garden. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区留园路338号 / 338 Liuyuan Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季55元，淡季45元 / Peak season: 55 CNY; Off-peak season: 45 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30（旺季至18:00） / 7:30–17:30 (peak season until 18:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 位于留园中部景区，由古木交柯沿主路向南行约50米即可到达。 Located in the central scenic area of Lingering Garden; walk south along the main path for about 50 meters from Ancient Trees Interlocking.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lingering_garden_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '涵碧山房',
  name_en = 'Hanbi Mountain House',
  body = '<p>Hanbi Mountain House is the principal hall in Lingering Garden''s central scenic area, facing north with three bays wide. It fronts a rippling pond and backs onto artificial hills and floral plantings—one of the garden''s premier vantage points. "Hanbi" derives from the Song dynasty poet Zhu Xi''s line "One water just embraces emerald," meaning water''s radiance contains verdant hues—an imagery of pristine expansiveness. The hall is bright and open, with scenic views both north and south: southward toward hills and ancient trees, northward over a pool mirroring the sky. The name encapsulates the idea that "both mountain and water are embraced within this house." This structure embodies the Suzhou garden design philosophy where hall and landscape are mutually constitutive—one sits indoors while scenery unfolds beyond the windows, interior and exterior seamlessly interwoven. - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区留园路338号 / 338 Liuyuan Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季55元，淡季45元 / Peak season: 55 CNY; Off-peak season: 45 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30（旺季至18:00） / 7:30–17:30 (peak season until 18:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 位于留园中部景区核心位置，从绿荫轩向北步行约20米即达；也可从入园主路直接前往。 Situated at the core of the central scenic area; walk about 20 meters north from Green Shade Pavilion, or directly from the main entry path.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lingering_garden_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '闻木犀香轩',
  name_en = 'Osmanthus Fragrance Pavilion',
  body = '<p>Osmanthus Fragrance Pavilion is located in the western scenic area of Lingering Garden, a pavilion-style structure expressly designed for appreciating the scent of osmanthus. "Muxi" is the classical term for osmanthus; the pavilion name plainly declares its design intent—enriching the garden''s sensory dimensions through olfactory experience. When golden osmanthus blooms in autumn, the pavilion is suffused with intoxicating fragrance; visitors inevitably pause to breathe deeply, marveling at the garden maker''s ingenuity in incorporating scent as scenery. Osmanthus trees are planted all around, complemented by rockery paths, forming a unique aesthetic space in Lingering Garden where olfaction takes precedence—breaking the convention of purely visual garden appreciation, and standing as a classic paradigm of "recognizing scenery through fragrance" in Chinese garden design. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区留园路338号 / 338 Liuyuan Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季55元，淡季45元 / Peak season: 55 CNY; Off-peak season: 45 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30（旺季至18:00） / 7:30–17:30 (peak season until 18:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 位于留园西部景区，从中部涵碧山房向西穿越曲廊约80米可达；秋季桂花开时香气可引路。 Located in the western scenic area; walk west through winding corridors about 80 meters from Hanbi Mountain House. In autumn, the osmanthus fragrance itself can guide your way.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lingering_garden_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '曲溪楼',
  name_en = 'Winding Stream Tower',
  body = '<p>Winding Stream Tower stands in the eastern section of Lingering Garden, a two-story tower-style structure built beside the water. The name draws from the winding course of the garden''s waterway—"Winding Stream" is both descriptive and poetic: the actual winding stream and the metaphorical winding paths of life. The upper floor features open windows and a long railing; ascending for a distant view, the entire eastern water scene unfolds—winding bridges, corridor reflections, ripple layers upon layers. The lower floor has a waterside corridor for close viewing of stream stones and swimming fish. Winding Stream Tower offers the dual experience of "ascending for distant vistas" and "sitting by water to hear ripples," making it one of the most observationally versatile towers in Lingering Garden, and exemplifying the Suzhou garden design ingenuity of "scenery both above and below." - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区留园路338号 / 338 Liuyuan Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季55元，淡季45元 / Peak season: 55 CNY; Off-peak season: 45 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30（旺季至18:00） / 7:30–17:30 (peak season until 18:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 位于留园东部景区，由中部涵碧山房向东穿过月洞门约60米到达。 Located in the eastern scenic area; walk east through the moon gate about 60 meters from Hanbi Mountain House.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lingering_garden_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '五峰仙馆',
  name_en = 'Five Peaks Fairy Hall',
  body = '<p>Five Peaks Fairy Hall is the core building of Lingering Garden''s eastern scenic area and the largest hall in the entire garden, spanning five bays with imposing grandeur. In the courtyard before the hall stand five Taihu stone peaks of varying heights and distinct postures, simulating the imagery of the five divine mountains where immortals dwell—hence the name. The hall''s structural materials are meticulously chosen: nanmu wood frames the beams and columns, with refined carvings that are exquisite yet not excessive, and elegant, dignified furnishings—reflecting the Jiangnan literati aesthetic of "grand yet not extravagant, refined yet not vulgar." This hall served as the garden owner''s principal venue for receiving distinguished guests and hosting elegant gatherings, with spacious yet well-layered interiors, standing as a paradigm of hall design in Suzhou gardens. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区留园路338号 / 338 Liuyuan Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季55元，淡季45元 / Peak season: 55 CNY; Off-peak season: 45 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30（旺季至18:00） / 7:30–17:30 (peak season until 18:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 位于留园东部景区中心位置，由曲溪楼向南步行约30米可达；是东部景区最显著的建筑，易于辨认。 Situated at the center of the eastern scenic area; walk south about 30 meters from Winding Stream Tower. It is the most prominent building in the eastern area, easily identifiable.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lingering_garden_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '林泉耆硕之馆',
  name_en = 'Hall of Elderly Sages in Woodland Springs',
  body = '<p>Hall of Elderly Sages in Woodland Springs is located in the eastern part of Lingering Garden, adjacent to Five Peaks Fairy Hall, and is a distinctive double-facing hall. "Woodland Springs" refers to the reclusive environment of mountains, forests, and spring waters; "Elderly Sages" denotes venerable persons of high virtue and senior age. The hall name expresses the garden owner''s reverence and aspiration for reclusive scholars of distinction. Its architectural form is remarkable: one side faces the courtyard rockery, the other faces the pool and corridor pavilions—north and south scenes are strikingly different while the building remains seamlessly unified, representing the ultimate expression of "one hall, two views" in Suzhou garden design. Inscribed plaques and couplets inside are all by renowned calligraphers, with a strong literary atmosphere—arguably the building that best embodies the literati spirit at the core of Lingering Garden. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区留园路338号 / 338 Liuyuan Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季55元，淡季45元 / Peak season: 55 CNY; Off-peak season: 45 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30（旺季至18:00） / 7:30–17:30 (peak season until 18:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 位于留园东部景区，紧邻五峰仙馆南侧，两馆相距仅约10米，可同时参观。 Located in the eastern scenic area, immediately south of Five Peaks Fairy Hall; the two halls are only about 10 meters apart and can be visited together.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lingering_garden_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '冠云峰',
  name_en = 'Cloud-Capped Peak',
  body = '<p>Cloud-Capped Peak is Lingering Garden''s most celebrated landmark and its crown jewel. Standing approximately 6.5 meters tall and weighing about 5 tons, it is the supreme specimen among Taihu stones, achieving the ultimate expression of the four aesthetic criteria: "slender, perforated, translucent, and wrinkled." The peak''s posture is majestic, its summit soaring like a crown piercing the clouds—hence the name. Legend holds it as a remnant of the Song dynasty''s "Flower and Stone Network" tribute collection; having endured a millennium of wind and rain, it remains standing here—the tallest independent Taihu stone peak surviving in Jiangnan gardens. Surrounded by pools, pavilions, and corridors, the stone''s silhouette reflects in the water, generating an interplay of reality and illusion that enhances its ethereal elegance. Stone appreciation is the essence of Chinese literati garden culture, and Cloud-Capped Peak stands as the pinnacle of this tradition. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区留园路338号 / 338 Liuyuan Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季55元，淡季45元 / Peak season: 55 CNY; Off-peak season: 45 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30（旺季至18:00） / 7:30–17:30 (peak season until 18:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 位于留园东部景区，在林泉耆硕之馆北侧庭院中，从五峰仙馆向北步行约20米即可见到这座巍峨石峰。 Located in the eastern scenic area, in the courtyard north of Hall of Elderly Sages in Woodland Springs; walk about 20 meters north from Five Peaks Fairy Hall to see this towering stone peak.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lingering_garden_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '冠云楼',
  name_en = 'Cloud-Capped Tower',
  body = '<p>Cloud-Capped Tower stands in the eastern part of Lingering Garden, built right beside Cloud-Capped Peak, a three-story tower-style structure. It shares the peak''s name because ascending the tower affords a complete panoramic view of Cloud-Capped Peak. The tower and peak form a classic "tower-peak opposing view"—looking down from the tower, the peak''s majestic upright posture is fully revealed; gazing up from the peak, the tower''s sweeping eaves and corner brackets are entirely displayed. The two resonate in height and complement each other in solidity and void, arguably the most brilliant pairing of architecture and stone peak in Suzhou gardens. Cloud-Capped Tower also houses important inscribed stone tablets and artifacts of Lingering Garden. Windows on the upper floors allow distant views beyond the garden across the Gusu cityscape—it is the scenic high point in Lingering Garden combining both close and distant observation functions. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区留园路338号 / 338 Liuyuan Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 旺季55元，淡季45元 / Peak season: 55 CNY; Off-peak season: 45 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 7:30-17:30（旺季至18:00） / 7:30–17:30 (peak season until 18:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 位于留园东部景区，紧依冠云峰东侧而建，从冠云峰旁拾级而上即可登楼。 Located in the eastern scenic area, built directly east of Cloud-Capped Peak; climb the stairs beside the peak to ascend the tower.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_lingering_garden_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '入口大门',
  name_en = 'Entrance Gate',
  body = '<p>The entrance gate of Wangshi Yuan is located at No. 11, Kuojia Tou Lane, nestled among residential alleyways in the southeastern corner of Suzhou''s old city. The gatehouse follows traditional Jiangnan residential style, with a grey-brick doorframe, black-lacquered wooden doors, and a plaque reading "Wangshi Yuan" above the lintel. The narrow lane approaching the gate is lined with white walls and grey-tiled eaves, giving no hint that a UNESCO World Heritage garden lies at its end. This "hidden within the city" setting is precisely the garden''s defining characteristic—the owner sought not street-facing grandeur, but a tranquil retreat within the bustling city. Pushing open the door reveals the Sedan Chair Hall, offering a glimpse of the garden within, guiding visitors from the mundane alley into a refined garden realm. The interplay of compression and release in spatial design showcases the masterful vision of the garden''s creator. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区带城桥路阔家头巷11号 / No. 11, Kuojia Tou Lane, DaiCheng Bridge Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 淡季（11月—次年3月）30元，旺季（4月—10月）40元；夜花园需另购票（约100元） / Off-season (Nov—Mar) 30 RMB; Peak season (Apr—Oct) 40 RMB; Night Garden requires separate ticket (approx. 100 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 白天 7:30—17:00；夜花园 19:30—22:00（夜花园开放日期请关注官方公告） / Daytime: 7:30 AM — 5:00 PM; Night Garden: 7:30 PM — 10:00 PM (check official announcements for Night Garden dates) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至南门站，步行约15分钟可达；或乘坐公交游2路、202路、204路至网师园北站，步行约3分钟。自驾可导航至网师园停车场（车位有限，建议公共交通出行）。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Nanmen Station, then walk about 15 minutes. Alternatively, take Tourist Bus 2, Bus 202, or Bus 204 to Wangshi Yuan North Station and walk about 3 minutes. By car, navigate to Wangshi Yuan parking lot (limited spaces; public transport recommended).</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_master_of_nets_garden_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '轿厅',
  name_en = 'Sedan Chair Hall',
  body = '<p>The Sedan Chair Hall is the first building in the residential section of Wangshi Yuan and the first interior space visitors enter. The hall spans three bays with a simple, open beam-frame structure. It was originally used for parking sedan chairs: guests would dismount here, and after a servant announced them to the master, they would be received into the inner hall. A plaque inscribed by a Qing Dynasty scholar hangs at the center, flanked by couplets whose texts often relate to fishing and reclusion, echoing the garden''s name "Master of the Nets." The hall contains a large wall mirror and a marble screen—the mirror reflects the courtyard scene behind, creating an illusion of extended space within the compact hall. This is a classic "borrowed scenery" technique in Suzhou gardens. Though merely a transitional space, the Sedan Chair Hall already reveals the owner''s cultural refinement and design philosophy through these carefully curated elements. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区带城桥路阔家头巷11号网师园内 / Inside Wangshi Yuan, No. 11, Kuojia Tou Lane, DaiCheng Bridge Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 淡季30元，旺季40元；夜花园另购票（约100元） / Off-season 30 RMB; Peak season 40 RMB; Night Garden separate ticket (approx. 100 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 白天 7:30—17:00；夜花园 19:30—22:00 / Daytime: 7:30 AM — 5:00 PM; Night Garden: 7:30 PM — 10:00 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至南门站，步行约15分钟；或乘坐公交游2路、202路、204路至网师园北站。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Nanmen Station, walk about 15 minutes; or take Tourist Bus 2, Bus 202, or Bus 204 to Wangshi Yuan North Station.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_master_of_nets_garden_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '万卷堂',
  name_en = 'Wanjuan Hall (Hall of Ten Thousand Scrolls)',
  body = '<p>Wanjuan Hall is the main hall of Wangshi Yuan''s residential quarter and the garden''s most important ceremonial building. The name "Wanjuan Tang" (Hall of Ten Thousand Scrolls) traces back to the Southern Song Dynasty, when Shi Zhengzhi, Vice Minister of Personnel, built a garden here to house his vast book collection—the name embodying the Chinese literati ideal of "reading ten thousand scrolls." When Song Zongyuan rebuilt the garden during the Qianlong reign of the Qing Dynasty, he retained the name in tribute to his predecessor. The hall spans five bays with a lofty, imposing interior, robust timber columns, and blue-stone basin-shaped plinths. A plaque reading "Wanjuan Tang" hangs at the center, featuring calligraphy attributed to Ming Dynasty master Wen Zhengming. The interior follows traditional arrangement: a long narrow table at center, armchairs on either side, and celebrated paintings and calligraphy on the walls. The courtyard before the hall features golden osmanthus and white magnolia, symbolizing "abundance of gold and jade." This was where the owner received distinguished guests, hosted family banquets, and displayed his cultural refinement. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区带城桥路阔家头巷11号网师园内 / Inside Wangshi Yuan, No. 11, Kuojia Tou Lane, DaiCheng Bridge Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 淡季30元，旺季40元；夜花园另购票（约100元） / Off-season 30 RMB; Peak season 40 RMB; Night Garden separate ticket (approx. 100 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 白天 7:30—17:00；夜花园 19:30—22:00 / Daytime: 7:30 AM — 5:00 PM; Night Garden: 7:30 PM — 10:00 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至南门站，步行约15分钟；或乘坐公交游2路、202路、204路至网师园北站。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Nanmen Station, walk about 15 minutes; or take Tourist Bus 2, Bus 202, or Bus 204 to Wangshi Yuan North Station.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_master_of_nets_garden_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '撷秀楼',
  name_en = 'Xiexiu Tower (Gathering Elegance Tower)',
  body = '<p>Xiexiu Tower stands directly north of Wanjuan Hall, serving as the inner residence of Wangshi Yuan where the owner and family conducted daily life. "Xiexiu" means "gathering elegance," derived from the poetry of Xie Lingyun of the Southern Dynasties, expressing the owner''s aspiration for a refined life. The two-story building has a ground floor for living and dining, with bedrooms and a study upstairs. The upper floor features a corridor and windows that open onto views of Rosy Cloud Pool and the garden''s pavilions. The interior once contained rosewood furniture, carved railings, and exquisite latticed windows, all demonstrating superb craftsmanship. A small sky-well connects Xiexiu Tower to Wanjuan Hall, with a planted flower bed featuring camellia and nandina, providing year-round interest. The transition from Wanjuan Hall to Xiexiu Tower marks a shift from public ceremonial space to private domestic space, embodying the traditional residential layout of "front hall, rear tower, inner and outer distinct," while showcasing the refinement of a wealthy Suzhou household''s daily life. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区带城桥路阔家头巷11号网师园内 / Inside Wangshi Yuan, No. 11, Kuojia Tou Lane, DaiCheng Bridge Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 淡季30元，旺季40元；夜花园另购票（约100元） / Off-season 30 RMB; Peak season 40 RMB; Night Garden separate ticket (approx. 100 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 白天 7:30—17:00；夜花园 19:30—22:00 / Daytime: 7:30 AM — 5:00 PM; Night Garden: 7:30 PM — 10:00 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至南门站，步行约15分钟；或乘坐公交游2路、202路、204路至网师园北站。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Nanmen Station, walk about 15 minutes; or take Tourist Bus 2, Bus 202, or Bus 204 to Wangshi Yuan North Station.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_master_of_nets_garden_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '梯云室',
  name_en = 'Tiyun Room (Cloud-Stepping Room)',
  body = '<p>Tiyun Room is located in the northwest of Wangshi Yuan, serving as the owner''s study. "Tiyun" (Cloud-Stepping) derives from a Tang Dynasty tale of Zhou Sheng "climbing clouds to fetch the moon," metaphorically suggesting ascending to lofty heights in pursuit of elevated ideals. The most brilliant feature of this room is its means of access: rather than a conventional wooden staircase, a pathway of Taihu limestone rocks is stacked into a miniature mountain path. One must ascend along the rockery to reach the second-floor study, as if walking on clouds—hence "Tiyun." The rockery serves dual purpose as both staircase and landscape feature, a masterstroke of ingenuity. The interior was once furnished with a writing desk, bookshelves, and the Four Treasures of the Study, in a serene setting. Windows reveal rockeries and verdant bamboo outside, creating the atmosphere of "a study hidden in the mountains." Tiyun Room''s design exemplifies the Suzhou garden principle of "adapting to the terrain and borrowing cleverly," perfectly uniting practical function with aesthetic delight—a classic case of "function as art" in garden architecture. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区带城桥路阔家头巷11号网师园内 / Inside Wangshi Yuan, No. 11, Kuojia Tou Lane, DaiCheng Bridge Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 淡季30元，旺季40元；夜花园另购票（约100元） / Off-season 30 RMB; Peak season 40 RMB; Night Garden separate ticket (approx. 100 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 白天 7:30—17:00；夜花园 19:30—22:00 / Daytime: 7:30 AM — 5:00 PM; Night Garden: 7:30 PM — 10:00 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至南门站，步行约15分钟；或乘坐公交游2路、202路、204路至网师园北站。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Nanmen Station, walk about 15 minutes; or take Tourist Bus 2, Bus 202, or Bus 204 to Wangshi Yuan North Station.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_master_of_nets_garden_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '看松读画轩',
  name_en = 'Kansong Duhua Veranda (Pine-Viewing and Painting-Reading Veranda)',
  body = '<p>Kansong Duhua Veranda stands on the western shore of Rosy Cloud Pool, one of the most literati-spirited buildings in Wangshi Yuan. The name "Kansong Duhua" (Viewing Pines and Reading Paintings) identifies the two refined pursuits associated with this space: admiring ancient pines and contemplating painted landscapes. The veranda has three bays facing south toward the water, with a seated railing at the front for both sitting and viewing. In the courtyard before the veranda grows a Buddhist pine (Podocarpus) estimated to be several centuries old, its weathered branches and ancient silhouette set against Taihu rocks, forming a natural "pine and rock painting." Seated inside, the owner could appreciate the vigor of the pine and the mood of paintings, with nature and art intermingling seamlessly. The interior once held a writing desk and hanging paintings, with delicately patterned latticed windows framing views like picture frames. Looking out from the veranda, Rosy Cloud Pool, the Moon-Arriving Pavilion, and Zhuoying Water Pavilion layer upon one another like an unrolling landscape scroll. This veranda exemplifies the Suzhou garden aesthetic of "still contemplation"—not wandering through scenery, but sitting peacefully and letting the landscape come to you. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区带城桥路阔家头巷11号网师园内 / Inside Wangshi Yuan, No. 11, Kuojia Tou Lane, DaiCheng Bridge Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 淡季30元，旺季40元；夜花园另购票（约100元） / Off-season 30 RMB; Peak season 40 RMB; Night Garden separate ticket (approx. 100 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 白天 7:30—17:00；夜花园 19:30—22:00 / Daytime: 7:30 AM — 5:00 PM; Night Garden: 7:30 PM — 10:00 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至南门站，步行约15分钟；或乘坐公交游2路、202路、204路至网师园北站。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Nanmen Station, walk about 15 minutes; or take Tourist Bus 2, Bus 202, or Bus 204 to Wangshi Yuan North Station.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_master_of_nets_garden_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '殿春簃',
  name_en = 'Dianchun Yi (Late Spring Cabin)',
  body = '<p>Astor Court），成为中国古典园林走向世界的里程碑。殿春簃也因此成为中美文化交流史上的一段佳话。 Dianchun Yi is located in the northwest corner of Wangshi Yuan, a self-contained courtyard of its own. "Dianchun" refers to late spring—herbaceous peonies, the last flowers to bloom in spring, were called "dianchun flowers," and since peonies were originally planted here, the name "Dianchun Yi" was chosen. "Yi" means a small chamber beside a main building. Though the courtyard covers barely a quarter-acre, it integrates architecture, rockery, plantings, and a spring—a "garden within a garden." The main room is a three-bay study with refined furnishings including a writing desk, zither table, and antiquities. Before the study stands a half-pavilion named Lengquan Ting (Cold Spring Pavilion), beside Hanbi Spring, whose crystal-clear water never runs dry. Taihu stone peaks in the courtyard are exquisitely perforated, complemented by peonies, plum trees, and bamboo. In 1980, the Metropolitan Museum of Art in New York created the Astor Court (Ming Studio) based on Dianchun Yi, marking a milestone in the global journey of Chinese classical gardens. Dianchun Yi thus became a celebrated chapter in the history of Sino-American cultural exchange. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区带城桥路阔家头巷11号网师园内 / Inside Wangshi Yuan, No. 11, Kuojia Tou Lane, DaiCheng Bridge Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 淡季30元，旺季40元；夜花园另购票（约100元） / Off-season 30 RMB; Peak season 40 RMB; Night Garden separate ticket (approx. 100 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 白天 7:30—17:00；夜花园 19:30—22:00 / Daytime: 7:30 AM — 5:00 PM; Night Garden: 7:30 PM — 10:00 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至南门站，步行约15分钟；或乘坐公交游2路、202路、204路至网师园北站。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Nanmen Station, walk about 15 minutes; or take Tourist Bus 2, Bus 202, or Bus 204 to Wangshi Yuan North Station.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_master_of_nets_garden_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '月到风来亭',
  name_en = 'Yuedao Fenglai Pavilion (Moon-Arriving and Wind-Coming Pavilion)',
  body = '<p>Yuedao Fenglai Pavilion stands at the center of Rosy Cloud Pool''s western shore, surrounded by water on three sides—the core structure of Wangshi Yuan''s waterscape. The name derives from a line by Song Dynasty poet Shao Yong: "When the moon reaches the heart of heaven, when the wind comes across the water''s surface"—a vision of transcendent beauty: moonlight at zenith bathes all in radiance, and wind on water ripples into endless patterns. The square pavilion has a gable-and-hip roof, open on three sides with one wall. A "beauty''s resting" railing faces the water; seated here, the pool''s surface mirrors the world. This is the garden''s premier moon-viewing spot—on Mid-Autumn night, the bright moon rises in the east and reflects into the pool, one moon above and one below shimmering in tandem, the ultimate Suzhou garden moon-viewing experience. A large mirror hangs inside the pavilion, reflecting the pavilions across the water—virtual and real intertwining, giving the compact pool infinite depth. The pavilion masterfully integrates four elements—moon, wind, water, and mirror—exemplifying the highest ideal of Chinese gardens: "though made by human hands, it seems created by nature itself." - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区带城桥路阔家头巷11号网师园内 / Inside Wangshi Yuan, No. 11, Kuojia Tou Lane, DaiCheng Bridge Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 淡季30元，旺季40元；夜花园另购票（约100元） / Off-season 30 RMB; Peak season 40 RMB; Night Garden separate ticket (approx. 100 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 白天 7:30—17:00；夜花园 19:30—22:00 / Daytime: 7:30 AM — 5:00 PM; Night Garden: 7:30 PM — 10:00 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至南门站，步行约15分钟；或乘坐公交游2路、202路、204路至网师园北站。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Nanmen Station, walk about 15 minutes; or take Tourist Bus 2, Bus 202, or Bus 204 to Wangshi Yuan North Station.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_master_of_nets_garden_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '濯缨水阁',
  name_en = 'Zhuoying Water Pavilion (Tassel-Washing Water Pavilion)',
  body = '<p>Zhuoying Water Pavilion stands on the southern shore of Rosy Cloud Pool, a water pavilion built flush with the surface. "Zhuoying" (washing tassels) derives from the Chu Ci (Songs of Chu) "Yu Fu" chapter: "When the waters of Canglang are clear, I can wash my hat-strings." "Ying" refers to the strings of an official''s cap; "washing the tassels" metaphorically means cleansing oneself of official life and retreating to nature. This naming perfectly echoes Wangshi Yuan''s theme of "fisherman''s reclusion." The pavilion spans three bays with a gable-and-hip roof, open on all sides, supported on stone columns above the water. Inside are stone tables and stools; on summer days, cool breezes sweep through off the pool, dispelling all heat. Looking north from the pavilion, Yuedao Fenglai Pavilion and Kansong Duhua Veranda face each other across the water, reflected in the pool like a symmetrical ink painting. The name plaque was inscribed by a Qing Dynasty scholar, with couplets relating to the themes of fishing and the Canglang River. Zhuoying Water Pavilion uses literary allusion as its inner core and waterscape as its outer expression, seamlessly fusing poetic, pictorial, and garden meaning into one. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区带城桥路阔家头巷11号网师园内 / Inside Wangshi Yuan, No. 11, Kuojia Tou Lane, DaiCheng Bridge Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 淡季30元，旺季40元；夜花园另购票（约100元） / Off-season 30 RMB; Peak season 40 RMB; Night Garden separate ticket (approx. 100 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 白天 7:30—17:00；夜花园 19:30—22:00 / Daytime: 7:30 AM — 5:00 PM; Night Garden: 7:30 PM — 10:00 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至南门站，步行约15分钟；或乘坐公交游2路、202路、204路至网师园北站。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Nanmen Station, walk about 15 minutes; or take Tourist Bus 2, Bus 202, or Bus 204 to Wangshi Yuan North Station.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_master_of_nets_garden_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '竹外一枝轩',
  name_en = 'Zhuwai Yizhi Veranda (A Single Branch Beyond Bamboo Veranda)',
  body = '<p>Zhuwai Yizhi Veranda is located at the northeast corner of Rosy Cloud Pool, a narrow, elongated pavilion built along the water. "Zhuwai Yizhi" (A Single Branch Beyond Bamboo) derives from Su Shi''s poem "He Qin Taixu Meihua": "A single branch slanting beyond bamboo is all the more lovely," originally describing how a plum branch extending beyond a bamboo thicket embodies elegant restraint. The name identifies both the plantings outside the window—bamboo and plum—and the viewing experience itself, which resembles contemplating a literati painting: spare yet resonant. The veranda has three bays running north-south, facing the water to the west and backed by a wall to the east. The western side features a full run of tall latticed windows, each frame like a picture frame capturing the pool scenery. Outside, a few stalks of bamboo and a single plum tree grow; in winter, when a plum branch extends beyond the bamboo, the poem''s imagery comes alive. The narrow interior has a seated railing and small table, ideal for sitting alone with tea and quietly observing the water. Looking out, Yuedao Fenglai Pavilion and Zhuoying Water Pavilion across Rosy Cloud Pool appear like a landscape painting, virtual and real interplaying. This veranda achieves much with little, sees the large within the small—a vivid embodiment of the Suzhou garden philosophy of "a mustard seed holding Mount Sumeru." - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区带城桥路阔家头巷11号网师园内 / Inside Wangshi Yuan, No. 11, Kuojia Tou Lane, DaiCheng Bridge Road, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 淡季30元，旺季40元；夜花园另购票（约100元） / Off-season 30 RMB; Peak season 40 RMB; Night Garden separate ticket (approx. 100 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 白天 7:30—17:00；夜花园 19:30—22:00 / Daytime: 7:30 AM — 5:00 PM; Night Garden: 7:30 PM — 10:00 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至南门站，步行约15分钟；或乘坐公交游2路、202路、204路至网师园北站。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Nanmen Station, walk about 15 minutes; or take Tourist Bus 2, Bus 202, or Bus 204 to Wangshi Yuan North Station.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_master_of_nets_garden_sa_10';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '门厅',
  name_en = 'Entrance Hall',
  body = '<p>The Entrance Hall is the gateway space of Couple''s Garden Retreat—the garden''s first outward-facing aspect. Despite its renown as a Suzhou classic garden, its facade is understated, presented in the style of an ordinary residence, aligning with the Suzhou garden cultural tradition of "great reclusion within the city." The Entrance Hall is simple and unadorned—white walls, black tiles, no decorative carvings—aptly conveying the garden owner''s philosophy of retreating to pastoral life without seeking fame. Only after stepping through the Entrance Hall and past the screen door does the scenic beauty of mountains and water gradually reveal itself. This spatial sequence of "from simplicity to refinement" is a classic embodiment of Suzhou garden design''s "concealed scenery" technique at the entry point. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区小新桥巷6号 / 6 Xiaoxinqiao Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 8元 / 8 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00–17:00 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐公交202路、301路至耦园站下车，沿小新桥巷步行约3分钟抵达门厅；门厅位于藕园最南侧，为唯一入口。 Take Bus Route 202 or 301 to Ouyuan Station, walk about 3 minutes along Xiaoxinqiao Lane to the Entrance Hall. The Entrance Hall is on the southernmost side, serving as the sole entry point.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_ou_garden_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '轿厅',
  name_en = 'Sedan Chair Hall',
  body = '<p>The Sedan Chair Hall sits between the Entrance Hall and the Main Hall, an indispensable transitional architectural space in traditional Suzhou residence-gardens. In former times, when the owner or guests arrived by sedan chair, the conveyance was parked here—hence the name. This hall is both a functional parking and waiting area and a transitional node in spatial rhythm—from the modest Entrance Hall through the Sedan Chair Hall into the Main Hall, building proportions gradually increase and decorations become more refined, forming a spatial progression of "from exterior to interior, from simplicity to splendor." The Sedan Chair Hall is proportionately sized—neither overshadowing nor appearing shabby—perfectly bridging the understated Entrance Hall and the dignified Main Hall, serving as the pivotal connecting link in Suzhou garden architectural sequences. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区小新桥巷6号 / 6 Xiaoxinqiao Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 8元 / 8 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00–17:00 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 位于门厅与大厅之间，入园后穿过门厅屏门即可到达，是从入口通往核心建筑群的必经之路。 Located between the Entrance Hall and Main Hall; upon entering, pass through the Entrance Hall''s screen door to arrive. It is the obligatory passage from the entry to the core building complex.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_ou_garden_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '大厅（涉趣堂）',
  name_en = 'Main Hall (Shequ Hall)',
  body = '<p>The Main Hall, also named Shequ Hall, is the core building of Couple''s Garden Retreat''s residential area, spanning three bays with grand proportions—the principal venue for formal ceremonies and guest reception. "Shequ" derives from Tao Yuanming''s phrase "delving into delights as one goes," meaning following one''s interests and pleasures in exploration and experience—this is precisely the core philosophy of Couple''s Garden Retreat''s entire design: seeking not grand spectacle but rather abundant delight. The interior furnishings are dignified and elegant, with nanmu furniture complemented by paintings and calligraphy by renowned artists; the hall plaque "Shequ Hall" was inscribed by a prominent figure of the era. Courtyards exist both before and behind the hall—the front courtyard is open and square, the rear courtyard secluded and winding—within one hall, two entirely distinct spatial experiences are obtained, reflecting the Suzhou garden layout wisdom of "hall at center, divergent paths on either side." - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区小新桥巷6号 / 6 Xiaoxinqiao Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 8元 / 8 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00–17:00 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 位于藕园住宅区中心，从轿厅向北步行约15米即达，是宅区建筑序列的核心节点。 Located at the center of the residential area; walk north about 15 meters from the Sedan Chair Hall. It is the core node in the residential building sequence.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_ou_garden_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '楼厅（寝居楼）',
  name_en = 'Upper Hall (Residence Tower)',
  body = '<p>The Upper Hall, also called Residence Tower, lies at the rear of Couple''s Garden Retreat''s residential area—a two-story tower-style structure. The lower floor serves as daily living space with a reception room and study; the upper floor is the private sleeping quarters of the garden owner and family. The building''s scale is slightly smaller than the Main Hall, with warmer, more refined decorations, reflecting the transition from public ceremonial space to private living space. Rear windows overlook the garden''s rockery and lotus pool; front windows enjoy courtyard flowers and trees—it is a typical node where residence and garden intermingle. Occupants can experience garden beauty from within the tower without deliberately stepping out. This lifestyle of "living is touring, touring is living" embodies the essence of Suzhou''s integrated residence-garden culture. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区小新桥巷6号 / 6 Xiaoxinqiao Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 8元 / 8 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00–17:00 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 位于藕园住宅区后部，从大厅向北穿过内院步行约20米可达；楼厅后窗即可望见花园景色。 Located at the rear of the residential area; walk north through the inner courtyard about 20 meters from the Main Hall. Rear windows of the tower already offer views of the garden scenery.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_ou_garden_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '书房（含蕊书斋）',
  name_en = 'Study (Hanrui Study)',
  body = '<p>Hanrui Study is the garden owner''s dedicated space for quiet study and contemplation in Couple''s Garden Retreat, situated at the junction between the residential area and the garden area—a small study with a serene environment and elegant furnishings. "Hanrui" means containing flower buds—potential within, yet unreleased—metaphorically referring to the literati practice of nurturing talent and awaiting the right moment, highly congruent with Couple''s Garden Retreat''s overall "reserved and understated" temperament. The study faces the garden side; beyond the windows, rockery and green bamboo are visible. Inside, the book collection is plentiful and writing materials are complete, creating an immersive ideal environment for reading and meditation. This was the daily space where garden owners Shen Bingcheng and his wife composed poetry, painted, sipped tea, and discussed scholarship—also one of the spiritual symbols of Couple''s Garden Retreat as a "couple''s shared reclusion" garden. In the study, the two shared the joy of reading in harmonious companionship. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区小新桥巷6号 / 6 Xiaoxinqiao Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 8元 / 8 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00–17:00 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 位于住宅区与花园区交界处，从楼厅向东步行约15米可达，窗外即可见花园假山。 Located at the junction of residential and garden areas; walk east about 15 meters from the Residence Tower. Garden rockery is visible from the study''s windows.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_ou_garden_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '戏厅（听橹厅）',
  name_en = 'Entertainment Hall (Tinglu Hall)',
  body = '<p>Tinglu Hall is a building space in Couple''s Garden Retreat rich in both everyday vitality and poetic imagination. "Tinglu" (listening to oars) derives from the garden''s unique geographical setting—the east side borders Suzhou''s ancient inner-city canal; sitting in the hall, one can hear the sound of boat sculls paddling through the water, hence the name. This hall served as the venue for the garden owner and his wife to enjoy music and performances, host banquets, and entertain guests—thus also called the Entertainment Hall. The interior is spacious enough for small performances and elegant gatherings. On the canal side, open windows bring the waterway''s sonic landscape indoors, forming a unique "sound scenery entering the room" experience. Suzhou is a water city; oar sounds are its urban auditory signature. Tinglu Hall employs hearing as a landscape design medium, integrating the city''s external living rhythm into the garden''s interior tranquility—a rare example of "constructing scenery through sound" in Suzhou gardens. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区小新桥巷6号 / 6 Xiaoxinqiao Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 8元 / 8 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00–17:00 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 位于藕园东侧，紧临内城河，从含蕊书斋向东步行约20米可达；临河一侧窗户可俯瞰水巷。 Located on the east side of Couple''s Garden Retreat, adjacent to the inner-city canal; walk east about 20 meters from Hanrui Study. Canal-side windows overlook the waterway lanes.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_ou_garden_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '荷花池',
  name_en = 'Lotus Pond',
  body = '<p>The Lotus Pond is the core water feature space in Couple''s Garden Retreat''s garden area, and the visual and ecological center of the entire garden. The name is straightforward yet poetic—"ou" means lotus root; Couple''s Garden Retreat''s name itself is closely connected to the lotus, and the Lotus Pond is the living scenic source of this naming. Lotuses are planted throughout the pond; in summer, lotus leaves stretch to the horizon, red blossoms reflect the sun, and pure fragrance drifts far—harmonizing with the garden''s name. The pond''s banks wind with deliberate irregularity; corridors, bridges, and pavilions line the water, the surface reflecting rockery, pavilions, skylight, and cloud shadows—real and virtual interwoven like a painting. In Chinese culture, the lotus symbolizes purity and integrity. Couple''s Garden Retreat''s lotus theme is both a scenic choice and a spiritual commitment—the garden owners Shen Bingcheng and his wife used the lotus as a moral metaphor, embedding their aspirations for reclusive integrity among mountains, waters, flowers, and trees. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区小新桥巷6号 / 6 Xiaoxinqiao Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 8元 / 8 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00–17:00 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 位于藕园花园区中央，从听橹厅向西步行约30米穿过回廊即达池岸；池周设有多处观景点。 Located at the center of the garden area; walk west about 30 meters through the corridor from Tinglu Hall to reach the pond''s edge. Multiple viewpoints are set around the pond.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_ou_garden_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '假山',
  name_en = 'Rockery',
  body = '<p>The Rockery is the three-dimensional landscape centerpiece of the garden area, located east of the Lotus Pond, constructed from Taihu stones. The mountain body rises and falls in staggered layers, with winding, deep paths forming a three-dimensional landscape scroll that is both explorable and visually appreciable. Though artificially constructed, the rockery pursues the natural ideal of "crafted by humans yet appearing as if created by nature"—stone peaks are rugged and graceful, caves are deep and intriguing, stone paths wind like real mountain stream courses. An observation platform atop the rockery offers panoramic views of the Lotus Pond and garden pavilions, with distant views of Suzhou''s cityscape beyond the walls. Stone caves and chambers beneath provide cool respite in summer—an ideal spot for escaping heat while enjoying scenery. Though not as grandly scaled as Lion Grove Garden''s rockery, Couple''s Garden Retreat''s rockery excels in refinement and subtlety, forming a classic "mountains encircling, waters surrounding" layout with the adjacent pond and pavilions. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区小新桥巷6号 / 6 Xiaoxinqiao Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 8元 / 8 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00–17:00 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 位于花园区荷花池东侧，从池岸沿石径向东攀行即可登上假山；山顶观景平台为俯瞰全园最佳位置。 Located east of the Lotus Pond in the garden area; climb eastward along stone paths from the pond''s edge to ascend the rockery. The summit observation platform offers the best panoramic vantage point for the entire garden.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_ou_garden_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '六角亭（藕香亭）',
  name_en = 'Hexagonal Pavilion (Ouxiang Pavilion)',
  body = '<p>Ouxiang Pavilion is a hexagonal waterside pavilion in Couple''s Garden Retreat''s garden area, situated north of the Lotus Pond and facing the rockery across the water. The name "Ouxiang" (lotus root fragrance) directly highlights its defining feature—when lotus flowers bloom in summer, breezes carry their fragrance into the pavilion; sitting within to admire lotuses and inhale their scent constitutes the garden''s most poetically sensory experience. The hexagonal pavilion''s form is light and elegant, with open views on all six sides—every direction offers scenic entry: southward across the Lotus Pond, eastward to the majestic rockery, westward along winding corridors, northward toward the ancient city wall. Stone table and benches provide resting and tea-sipping spots—an ideal place for visitors to pause and immerse in garden scenery. Ouxiang Pavilion resonates most directly with the garden''s name—"ou" and "he" (lotus) share the same origin, "xiang" (fragrance) is the lotus''s essence—the pavilion name annotates the garden name, making it the garden''s signature thematic work. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区小新桥巷6号 / 6 Xiaoxinqiao Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 8元 / 8 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00–17:00 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 位于荷花池北侧水边，从池岸沿北向小径步行约15米可达；亭中可同时观赏池面荷花与对面假山。 Located on the water''s edge north of the Lotus Pond; walk about 15 meters along the northern path from the pond''s edge. The pavilion offers simultaneous views of lotuses on the pond and the rockery opposite.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_ou_garden_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '回廊',
  name_en = 'Winding Corridor',
  body = '<p>The Winding Corridor is an essential architectural element threading together all scenic points in Couple''s Garden Retreat''s garden area, winding along the Lotus Pond''s edge, organically linking pavilions, terraces, towers, and halls with rockery and water into a complete observation sequence. The corridor is proportionately wide, with water on one side and walls or plantings on the other, forming a dual-view layout of "water on one side, wall on the other" or "scenes on both sides"—every step brings a different visual experience, representing the best practice of Suzhou garden''s "shifting views with each step" principle. The corridor roof follows Suzhou''s traditional corridor-pavilion construction: simple beams and columns, lightly sweeping eave corners. Every few steps, a pierced window opens—each uniquely shaped: round, square, plum blossom, or fan—through which different angles of pond and rockery scenes appear, making the corridor itself a flowing visual artwork. The corridor is not merely a traffic route but a carefully choreographed "visual narrative thread," guiding visitors to experience each garden scene in a designed rhythm. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区小新桥巷6号 / 6 Xiaoxinqiao Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 8元 / 8 CNY - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00–17:00 - 交通信息 / Transportation： 回廊环绕荷花池一周，是花园区的主要步行通道；从藕香亭、假山、听橹厅均可直接进入回廊，沿廊行走可遍览全园主要景点。 The corridor encircles the Lotus Pond, serving as the garden area''s primary pedestrian path. Entry points exist from Ouxiang Pavilion, the rockery, and Tinglu Hall—walking along the corridor enables a tour of all major scenic points.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_ou_garden_sa_10';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '入口宅门',
  name_en = 'Entrance Gate',
  body = '<p>The entrance to Yipu Garden is deliberately inconspicuous, tucked away at the far end of Wenya Lane — a narrow, winding alleyway in Suzhou''s old city. This "hidden within the city" approach is characteristic of Suzhou''s literati gardens, which favor understatement over grandeur. The gate itself is a traditional stone-framed doorway with grey brick and dark tiles, virtually indistinguishable from neighboring residences. First-time visitors can easily walk past without realizing that a UNESCO World Heritage garden lies within. Stepping through the gate, the noise of the city falls away instantly, replaced by a serene courtyard — a spatial transition from bustle to tranquility that is Yipu''s first gift to every guest. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区文衙弄5号 / No. 5 Wenya Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 包含在艺圃门票内，成人票10元，学生半价。 / Included in Yipu Garden admission: 10 RMB for adults, half price for students. - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00（全年开放） / 8:00 AM – 5:00 PM (open year-round) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 可乘坐苏州公交1路、101路至"养育巷"站下车，步行约10分钟经文衙弄抵达；或乘坐地铁4号线至"察院场"站，步行约15分钟。 / Take Suzhou Bus Route 1 or 101 to "Yangyuxiang" stop, then walk about 10 minutes through Wenya Lane; or take Metro Line 4 to "Chayuanchang" station and walk about 15 minutes.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_yi_garden_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '世纶堂',
  name_en = 'Shilun Hall',
  body = '<p>Shilun Hall is the first main hall along Yipu Garden''s central axis, facing south with three bays. Its architectural style is plain and dignified — no painted beams, no gilded columns — preserving the hallmark simplicity of Ming Dynasty construction. The name "Shilun" derives from "经纶世务," reflecting the owner''s aspiration to engage meaningfully with worldly affairs. A stone-paved courtyard precedes the hall, graced by an old tree whose dappled shade plays against whitewashed walls and dark tiles. Originally adorned with calligraphic plaques, the hall served as a gathering place for receiving guests, sipping tea, and scholarly discussion. The intimate scale and absence of ostentation embody the Ming-era literati ideal: "seek not grandeur, but refinement and cleanliness." - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区文衙弄5号艺园内 / Within Yipu Garden, No. 5 Wenya Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 包含在艺圃门票内，成人票10元。 / Included in Yipu Garden admission: 10 RMB for adults. - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00 AM – 5:00 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 与艺圃入口相同，经文衙弄步行进入即可到达。 / Same as the garden entrance — accessible on foot through Wenya Lane after entering the garden.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_yi_garden_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '东莱草堂',
  name_en = 'Donglai Thatched Cottage',
  body = '<p>Situated behind Shilun Hall, Donglai Thatched Cottage is the second building along the garden''s central axis. The name "Donglai" is believed to reference the garden owner''s ancestral homeland, carrying a note of nostalgia, while "thatched cottage" (草堂) is a humble term Chinese scholars have long favored to signal a life of reclusion, free from worldly ambition. The interior is simply furnished — a writing desk, calligraphy brushes, and inkstones neatly arranged. Light filters through latticed windows where bamboo shadows sway, creating a serene reading environment. This is where the garden owner spent his days reading, entertaining close friends, and composing poetry. From the cottage window, the central pond and rockery unfold in full view — a perfect demonstration of the Suzhou gardening principle of "seeing the universe within a small space." - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区文衙弄5号艺圃内中路第二进 / Second courtyard along the central axis, Yipu Garden, No. 5 Wenya Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 包含在艺圃门票内，成人票10元。 / Included in Yipu Garden admission: 10 RMB for adults. - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00 AM – 5:00 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 进入艺圃后沿中路建筑序列前行，经世纶堂即可到达。 / After entering the garden, proceed along the central axis past Shilun Hall to reach this cottage.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_yi_garden_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '思嗜轩',
  name_en = 'Sishi Pavilion',
  body = '<p>Sishi Pavilion sits on the southern bank of Yipu''s central pond — a delicately proportioned waterside structure. The name "Sishi" means "to reflect upon one''s passions and loves," revealing the garden owner''s devotion to a particular way of life and spiritual pursuit. The pavilion opens directly onto the water, offering sweeping views of Yanguang Pavilion, rockeries, and waterside towers to the north — making it one of the finest vantage points in the garden. Inside, a single table and chair suffice; the minimalism perfectly suits the literati ideal of solitary contemplation. On misty mornings or golden-hour evenings, when warm light bathes the whitewashed walls, this corner becomes the most poetic spot in the entire garden — a place to brew tea, open a book, listen to leaping fish, and watch blossoms unfold and fall. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区文衙弄5号艺圃内水池南侧 / South side of the central pond, Yipu Garden, No. 5 Wenya Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 包含在艺圃门票内，成人票10元。 / Included in Yipu Garden admission: 10 RMB for adults. - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00 AM – 5:00 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 进入艺圃后，沿中路行至水池区域，轩在水池南侧。 / After entering the garden, proceed to the pond area; the pavilion is on the south side of the pond.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_yi_garden_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '乳鱼池',
  name_en = 'Ruyu Pool',
  body = '<p>Ruyu Pool is the heart of Yipu Garden''s landscape — a central pond of just over one mu (roughly 670 square meters) that, though modest in size, offers richly layered views. The name "Ruyu" (literally "nursling fish") is poetically drawn from a classical verse describing tiny fish moving across the water''s surface like freshly formed ice marks — a delicate, almost imperceptible animation. The water is clear, with koi gliding lazily beneath the surface. The pond''s irregular shoreline is edged with yellow stones laid in a naturalistic style. To the south, Sishi Pavilion rises at the water''s edge; to the north, Yanguang Pavilion stretches along the shore; rockeries and towers frame the east and west — together forming the classic garden layout of "water at the center, architecture encircling." Standing at the pond''s edge, sky and clouds reflect in the water, dissolving the boundary between reality and reflection, and the world beyond seems to vanish. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区文衙弄5号艺圃中心区域 / Central area of Yipu Garden, No. 5 Wenya Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 包含在艺圃门票内，成人票10元。 / Included in Yipu Garden admission: 10 RMB for adults. - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00 AM – 5:00 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 进入艺圃后沿主路前行，池在园中心区域，各建筑均环池而建。 / Enter the garden and follow the main path; the pool is at the center, with all major buildings arranged around it.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_yi_garden_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '延光阁',
  name_en = 'Yanguang Pavilion',
  body = '<p>Yanguang Pavilion is Yipu Garden''s most iconic structure, perched on the northern shore of Ruyu Pool. Five bays wide with a single-eave gable roof, it is one of the largest waterside pavilions in all of Suzhou''s classical gardens. The name "Yanguang" means "extending light" — drawing sunlight and scenery into the interior. True to its name, the building opens on three sides to the water, with latticed windows on the south facade that, when fully opened, frame the entire garden panorama as if the whole landscape were gathered into one''s embrace. The interior is paved with square tiles and simply furnished; today it serves as a tea room where visitors can rest and sip tea. Seated inside with a cup of Biluochun green tea, watching the pond''s reflections tremble in the breeze and listening to raindrops tap the eaves, one truly understands the ancient wisdom that "a room need not be grand to be elegant." Yanguang Pavilion is also the finest vantage point for the garden''s seasonal pageant: tender green in spring, lotus breezes in summer, crimson leaves in autumn, and silent snow in winter. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区文衙弄5号艺圃内乳鱼池北岸 / North shore of Ruyu Pool, Yipu Garden, No. 5 Wenya Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 包含在艺圃门票内，阁内品茶另收费。 / Included in Yipu Garden admission; tea service inside the pavilion is separately charged. - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00 AM – 5:00 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 进入艺圃后往北行至水池北岸即到。 / After entering the garden, walk north to the northern pond shore to reach the pavilion.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_yi_garden_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '朝爽亭',
  name_en = 'Chaoshuang Pavilion',
  body = '<p>Chaoshuang Pavilion crowns the summit of the rockery on the eastern side of Ruyu Pool — a small, open-sided square pavilion. The name "Chaoshuang" is drawn from a classical phrase meaning "the crisp, refreshing air that comes with morning," signaling that this is the place to ascend, gaze afar, and breathe in the pure mountain-like breeze. Though modest in size, the pavilion is the highest point in the garden. Ascending the winding stone steps and pausing at the top, visitors enjoy a sweeping panorama: the pond, architecture, and plantings of the entire garden spread below like a three-dimensional landscape painting — a masterful demonstration of "seeing the vast within the small." A couplet hangs on the pavilion columns; the roof is simple and unornamented, in keeping with the garden''s unified aesthetic of restrained antiquity. The finest moments to climb are at dawn and dusk: in the early morning, mist clings to the garden like ink wash on paper; at sunset, golden light carpets the water and the pavilion''s silhouette turns into a painting. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区文衙弄5号艺圃内假山东侧高处 / Atop the eastern rockery, Yipu Garden, No. 5 Wenya Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 包含在艺圃门票内，成人票10元。 / Included in Yipu Garden admission: 10 RMB for adults. - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00 AM – 5:00 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 进入艺圃后往东侧假山方向行进，沿石阶上行可至。 / After entering the garden, head toward the eastern rockery and climb the stone steps to reach the pavilion.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_yi_garden_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '碧浪亭',
  name_en = 'Bilang Pavilion',
  body = '<p>Bilang Pavilion occupies the southeastern corner of Ruyu Pool — a slender hexagonal structure with gracefully proportioned eaves. The name "Bilang" (literally "emerald waves") evokes the green ripples that shimmer across the pond when a breeze passes over, so that the pavilion''s name is itself a living picture. Three sides of the pavilion face the water; the fourth connects to the shore. Standing inside, one can look down to see the clear, shallow pond and fish darting among lotus leaves; looking up, Yanguang Pavilion''s flying eaves and Chaoshuang Pavilion atop the rockery create a layered composition of near and far, high and low. Old trees grow beside the pavilion, their branches dipping into the water, swaying gently, mirrored in the pond below. This is the garden''s best spot for simply "sitting still" — not rushing to the next site, not fumbling with a camera, just quietly feeling the breeze and listening to birdsong, experiencing the complete aesthetic of Suzhou gardens where one can roam, dwell, and sit in equal measure. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区文衙弄5号艺圃内水池东南角 / Southeast corner of the pond, Yipu Garden, No. 5 Wenya Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 包含在艺圃门票内，成人票10元。 / Included in Yipu Garden admission: 10 RMB for adults. - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00 AM – 5:00 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 进入艺圃后沿水池东南方向行走即可到达。 / After entering the garden, walk toward the southeast corner of the pond to reach the pavilion.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_yi_garden_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '博雅堂',
  name_en = 'Boya Hall',
  body = '<p>Boya Hall stands at the far northern end of Yipu Garden''s architectural sequence — the deepest hall in the entire compound. The name "Boya" means "broadly learned and upright in heart," reflecting the Confucian ideal of scholarly depth paired with moral integrity. A courtyard precedes the hall, planted with banana palms and heavenly bamboo that change character with each season. The interior is spacious and bright; it originally housed the owner''s collection of rare books, calligraphy, paintings, and bronze-and-stone antiquities, and served as a venue for scholarly gatherings and the connoisseurship of art. The architectural style continues the garden''s signature plainness — unpainted beams, whitewashed walls, square-tile floors — relying on the natural grain of the wood and the purity of line for its quiet authority. As the final stop on the visitor''s route, Boya Hall serves as the coda to a well-crafted book: looking back along the path just walked, the pond, pavilions, rockeries, and flora rise in sequence, leaving a lingering aftertaste and a deepened reverence for this "ultimate expression of the small garden." - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区文衙弄5号艺圃北部 / Northern section of Yipu Garden, No. 5 Wenya Lane, Gusu District, Suzhou - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 包含在艺圃门票内，成人票10元。 / Included in Yipu Garden admission: 10 RMB for adults. - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 8:00-17:00 / 8:00 AM – 5:00 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 进入艺圃后沿主路行至北部末端即可到达，为游览路线终点。 / After entering the garden, follow the main path to the northernmost end; this is the final stop on the tour route.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_yi_garden_sa_10';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '入口大厅',
  name_en = 'Entrance Hall',
  body = '<p>The Entrance Hall serves as the welcoming space of Suzhou Museum''s new wing, masterfully designed by the world-renowned architect I.M. Pei. Clean geometric lines and expansive glass walls create a luminous, airy atmosphere, while natural light streaming through skylights casts shifting shadows across white walls and gray eaves. A guide desk and multimedia displays provide comprehensive visitor information. From the hall, glimpses of the rockery in the main courtyard already reveal a dialogue between ancient and modern aesthetics. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区东北街204号苏州博物馆入口 / Entrance of Suzhou Museum, 204 Dongbei Street, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费（需预约） / Free admission (reservation required) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 9:00-17:00（周一闭馆，16:00停止入馆） / 9:00-17:00 (closed on Mondays, last entry at 16:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约10分钟；公交55路、178路至苏州博物馆站 / Walk about 10 minutes from Beisita Station on Metro Line 4; Bus routes 55 and 178 to Suzhou Museum stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_museum_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '吴地遗珍展厅',
  name_en = 'Wu Region Heritage Gallery',
  body = '<p>The Wu Region Heritage Gallery brings together important archaeological finds from Suzhou, ranging from Shang-Zhou bronze wares to Spring-and-Autumn jade pieces, from Han dynasty pottery figurines to Six Dynasties celadon. Three thematic sections — "Origins of Wu," "Artifacts of Wu," and "Spirit of Wu" — weave a continuous narrative, allowing visitors to experience Suzhou''s deep cultural accumulation through individual objects. Bronze swords and primitive porcelain jars are especially prized, testifying to the extraordinary metallurgical and ceramic skills of Wu''s early inhabitants. This gallery is essential for understanding the roots of Jiangnan culture. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区东北街204号苏州博物馆新馆一层 / First floor, New Wing, Suzhou Museum, 204 Dongbei Street, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费（需预约） / Free admission (reservation required) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 9:00-17:00（周一闭馆，16:00停止入馆） / 9:00-17:00 (closed on Mondays, last entry at 16:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约10分钟 / Walk about 10 minutes from Beisita Station on Metro Line 4</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_museum_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '吴塔国宝展厅',
  name_en = 'Wu Pagoda National Treasures Gallery',
  body = '<p>The Wu Pagoda National Treasures Gallery is one of the museum''s most compelling spaces, concentrating national-treasure-grade artifacts discovered inside Huqiu Yunyan Temple Pagoda and Ruiguang Pagoda. The Yue kiln mise (secret-color) porcelain lotus bowl from Huqiu, its glaze as green as lake water, is widely acknowledged as the pinnacle of late Tang–Five Dynasties secret-color porcelain. The Pearl Relic Stupa from Ruiguang Pagoda, intricately carved from pearls, gems, and sandalwood, astonishes the world with its craftsmanship. These relics not only reveal the depth of Wu''s Buddhist culture but also represent the zenith of Suzhou craftsmanship before the Song dynasty — an unmissable highlight of any visit. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区东北街204号苏州博物馆新馆一层 / First floor, New Wing, Suzhou Museum, 204 Dongbei Street, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费（需预约） / Free admission (reservation required) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 9:00-17:00（周一闭馆，16:00停止入馆） / 9:00-17:00 (closed on Mondays, last entry at 16:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约10分钟；公交55路至苏州博物馆站 / Walk about 10 minutes from Beisita Station on Metro Line 4; Bus route 55 to Suzhou Museum stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_museum_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '吴中风雅展厅',
  name_en = 'Wu Elegance Gallery',
  body = '<p>The Wu Elegance Gallery follows a timeline from the Song dynasty to the Ming-Qing era, using studio implements, tea ware, incense sets, and guqin to vividly recreate the "ya" (refined) lifestyle of Suzhou''s literati class. Sections such as "Study Treasures," "Tea and Zen," and "Qin, Qi, Shu, Hua" allow visitors to glimpse how ancient Suzhou scholars pursued spiritual transcendence and aesthetic perfection in daily life. Each exquisite inkstone, warm tea cup, and understated incense burner speaks to the Wu literati''s ideal of embodying philosophy through objects. The gallery displays not only the beauty of artifacts but also a Jiangnan philosophy of life spanning a millennium. - 详细地址 / Address： 江省苏州市姑苏区东北街204号苏州博物馆新馆二层 / Second floor, New Wing, Suzhou Museum, 204 Dongbei Street, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费（需预约） / Free admission (reservation required) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 9:00-17:00（周一闭馆，16:00停止入馆） / 9:00-17:00 (closed on Mondays, last entry at 16:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约10分钟 / Walk about 10 minutes from Beisita Station on Metro Line 4</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_museum_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '吴门书画展厅',
  name_en = 'Wu School Calligraphy & Painting Gallery',
  body = '<p>The Wu School Calligraphy &amp; Painting Gallery is one of the museum''s most artistically significant spaces, systematically collecting and displaying core works of the Ming-dynasty Wu School. Shen Zhou''s robust and moist brushwork, Wen Zhengming''s refined precision, Tang Yin''s spirited fluidity, and Qiu Ying''s exquisite grace — the four Wu masters each achieved brilliance in their own style, collectively shaping the pinnacle of Ming literati painting. The gallery also features Wu School calligraphy, from Zhu Yunming''s wild cursive script to Wen Zhengming''s small regular script, revealing Wu literati''s talent and character in every stroke. Rotating thematic exhibitions ensure new discoveries on each visit — an essential destination for lovers of calligraphy and painting in Suzhou. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区东北街204号苏州博物馆新馆二层 / Second floor, New Wing, Suzhou Museum, 204 Dongbei Street, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费（需预约） / Free admission (reservation required) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 9:00-17:00（周一闭馆，16:00停止入馆） / 9:00-17:00 (closed on Mondays, last entry at 16:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约10分钟；公交178路至苏州博物馆站 / Walk about 10 minutes from Beisita Station on Metro Line 4; Bus route 178 to Suzhou Museum stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_museum_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '新石器时代玉器展厅',
  name_en = 'Neolithic Jade Gallery',
  body = '<p>The Neolithic Jade Gallery focuses on jade treasures from the Neolithic period in the Lake Tai region, especially the Liangzhu culture. Jade bi discs, cong tubes, axe heads, and huang pendants — these forms carried ancient reverence for heaven and earth and symbolized authority; their finely incised patterns and polished surfaces are awe-inspiring. The gallery restores the archaeological context of these jades, helping visitors understand that they were not mere ornaments but ritual implements for communicating with deities and marking social rank. The god-and-animal mask motif on Liangzhu cong is considered one of the earliest divine emblems of Chinese civilization, holding irreplaceable academic value for exploring East Asian civilizational origins. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区东北街204号苏州博物馆新馆一层 / First floor, New Wing, Suzhou Museum, 204 Dongbei Street, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费（需预约） / Free admission (reservation required) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 9:00-17:00（周一闭馆，16:00停止入馆） / 9:00-17:00 (closed on Mondays, last entry at 16:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约10分钟 / Walk about 10 minutes from Beisita Station on Metro Line 4</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_museum_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '主庭院（片石假山）',
  name_en = 'Main Courtyard (Slice Rockery)',
  body = '<p>The Main Courtyard is the most iconic space in Suzhou Museum''s new wing, conceived and designed by I.M. Pei himself. Using white walls as canvas and sliced rocks as brushstrokes, he transforms Mi Fu''s "Mi-style cloud mountains" from ink painting into a three-dimensional landscape. Gray rock slices, staggered and layered against white walls, appear like distant peaks emerging through mist, breaking from traditional rockery stacking to create an unprecedented "wall-as-canvas, stone-as-painting" modern garden aesthetic. The courtyard''s mirror-like water, sparse bamboo shadows, and views across the wall to the Humble Administrator''s Garden form a natural dialogue between old and new — I.M. Pei''s enduring gift to Suzhou. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区东北街204号苏州博物馆新馆中央庭院 / Central courtyard, New Wing, Suzhou Museum, 204 Dongbei Street, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费（需预约） / Free admission (reservation required) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 9:00-17:00（周一闭馆，16:00停止入馆） / 9:00-17:00 (closed on Mondays, last entry at 16:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约10分钟；公交55路、178路至苏州博物馆站 / Walk about 10 minutes from Beisita Station on Metro Line 4; Bus routes 55 and 178 to Suzhou Museum stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_museum_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '紫藤园',
  name_en = 'Wisteria Garden',
  body = '<p>The Wisteria Garden occupies the transitional zone between the new wing and the忠王府 (Loyal King''s Mansion), the museum''s most poetic small garden space. The wisteria vines originate from centuries-old stock inside the忠王府; I.M. Pei personally grafted them here, enabling this time-spanning life to continue blossoming in the new wing. Each April, wisteria cascades like a waterfall, purple petals swaying in the breeze against white walls and gray tiles in stunning color contrast. Stone paths wind beneath the canopy, light dappling through leaves — a moment''s pause here reveals Pei''s deeper design philosophy using plants as living links: new and old are not severed but share the same roots. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区东北街204号苏州博物馆新馆与忠王府之间 / Between the New Wing and忠王府, Suzhou Museum, 204 Dongbei Street, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费（需预约） / Free admission (reservation required) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 9:00-17:00（周一闭馆，16:00停止入馆） / 9:00-17:00 (closed on Mondays, last entry at 16:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约10分钟 / Walk about 10 minutes from Beisita Station on Metro Line 4</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_museum_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '茶室',
  name_en = 'Tea Room',
  body = '<p>The Tea Room sits on the west side of the new wing, with expansive floor-to-ceiling glass directly facing the Main Courtyard''s slice-rock rockery and water feature — the museum''s most restorative retreat. Suzhou Biluochun is the signature brew, accompanied by local tea snacks, inviting visitors to slow their pace with a cup of clear tea after viewing exhibitions. The design extends Pei''s minimalist aesthetic: gray-white tones with wooden furniture, landscape paintings beyond the glass, tea mist within, merging into a distinctive Zen atmosphere. Whether for a leisurely afternoon sit or a brief inter-exhibition pause, the Tea Room transforms the museum visit into a sensory pleasure. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区东北街204号苏州博物馆新馆一层西侧 / West side, first floor, New Wing, Suzhou Museum, 204 Dongbei Street, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费（需预约），茶饮及点心另行收费 / Free admission (reservation required); tea and snacks are charged separately - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 9:00-17:00（周一闭馆，16:00停止入馆） / 9:00-17:00 (closed on Mondays, last entry at 16:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约10分钟 / Walk about 10 minutes from Beisita Station on Metro Line 4</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_museum_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '太平天国忠王府',
  name_en = 'Taiping Heavenly Kingdom忠王 Mansion',
  body = '<p>The忠王 Mansion is a core component of Suzhou Museum, originally the Suzhou residence of the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom''s Loyal King Li Xiucheng, built around 1860. It is one of the best-preserved Taiping historical buildings in China, where classical Suzhou palace layout coexists with distinctive Taiping decorative elements — dragon carvings, painted murals, and Taiping inscriptions forming unique layers of historical information. The indoor classical stage inside is a rare large-scale theater in Jiangnan, its caisson ceiling carved with breathtaking finesse. Connected to Pei''s new wing, stepping from the classical halls into the modern space crosses a century in a single stride, giving the tension between history and contemporary its most vivid expression. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市姑苏区东北街204号苏州博物馆忠王府区 / 忠王 Mansion area, Suzhou Museum, 204 Dongbei Street, Gusu District, Suzhou, Jiangsu - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 免费（需预约） / Free admission (reservation required) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 9:00-17:00（周一闭馆，16:00停止入馆） / 9:00-17:00 (closed on Mondays, last entry at 16:00) - 交通信息 / Transportation： 地铁4号线北寺塔站步行约10分钟；公交55路、178路至苏州博物馆站 / Walk about 10 minutes from Beisita Station on Metro Line 4; Bus routes 55 and 178 to Suzhou Museum stop</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_museum_sa_10';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '入口宅门',
  name_en = 'Entrance Gate',
  body = '<p>The entrance gate faces the lanes of Tongli Ancient Town in the traditional stone-arch style, with a brick-carved lintel inscribed "Tuisi Garden." The gatehouse is constructed of finely ground grey bricks with tight mortar joints, showcasing exceptional craftsmanship. Unlike the ornate gatehouses of wealthy merchants, Tuisi Garden''s entrance deliberately pursues simplicity—befitting Ren Lansheng''s status as a demoted official returning home, and echoing the humility inherent in the garden''s name. Upon entering, a screen wall temporarily conceals the garden''s scenery, creating a spatial sequence of "suppression before revelation" that guides visitors from the bustling streets into a tranquil world. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇新镇街退思园入口 / Entrance of Tuisi Garden, XinZhen Street, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 含在同里古镇联票内（100元），也可单独购买退思园门票（约20元） / Included in Tongli Ancient Town combo ticket (100 RMB); separate entry to Tuisi Garden also available (approx. 20 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全年开放，7:30—17:30 / Open year-round, 7:30 AM — 5:30 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至同里站，换乘吴江公交725路至同里古镇站，步行约5分钟可达；或从苏州汽车南站乘大巴至同里汽车站后步行约10分钟。自驾可导航至同里古镇停车场。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, transfer to Wujiang Bus 725 to Tongli Ancient Town, then walk about 5 minutes. Alternatively, take a coach from Suzhou South Bus Station to Tongli Bus Station and walk for 10 minutes. By car, navigate to Tongli Ancient Town parking lot.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tuisi_garden_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '轿厅',
  name_en = 'Sedan Chair Hall',
  body = '<p>The Sedan Chair Hall sits between the entrance gate and the main hall, an essential ceremonial transitional space in traditional Jiangnan residences. Its name derives from its original function of parking sedan chairs: arriving guests would dismount, tidy their attire, and rest briefly before being received into the main hall. The hall spans three bays with simple timber framing, modest decoration, and square-tile flooring. Wooden benches once lined both sides for attendants. Though unadorned, the Sedan Chair Hall plays a crucial role in modulating spatial rhythm—from the noise of the street to the formality of the main hall, it acts as a buffer, allowing visitors to prepare visually and psychologically, while embodying the etiquette governing host-guest relations. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇新镇街退思园内 / Inside Tuisi Garden, XinZhen Street, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 含在同里古镇联票内（100元），也可单独购买退思园门票（约20元） / Included in Tongli Ancient Town combo ticket (100 RMB); separate entry also available (approx. 20 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全年开放，7:30—17:30 / Open year-round, 7:30 AM — 5:30 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至同里站，换乘吴江公交725路至同里古镇站，步行约5分钟可达。自驾可导航至同里古镇停车场。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, transfer to Wujiang Bus 725, then walk about 5 minutes. By car, navigate to Tongli Ancient Town parking lot.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tuisi_garden_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '正厅（荫余堂）',
  name_en = 'Main Hall (Hall of Sheltered Abundance)',
  body = '<p>Yinyu Tang is the main hall of Tuisi Garden and the most important ceremonial space in the residential quarter. The name "Yinyu" means "to shelter descendants and leave a lasting legacy," expressing Ren Lansheng''s aspirations for his family''s enduring prosperity. The hall spans three bays with a high, bright interior, fine timber construction, and drum-shaped blue-stine plinths. A plaque inscribed "Yinyu Tang" hangs at the center, flanked by couplets. The interior follows traditional arrangement—a long narrow table at the center, armchairs and side tables on either side, with calligraphy and paintings on the walls. This was the venue for receiving distinguished guests, conducting family councils, and hosting weddings and funerals. The courtyard before the hall features osmanthus and magnolia, symbolizing "abundance of gold and jade." - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇新镇街退思园内 / Inside Tuisi Garden, XinZhen Street, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 含在同里古镇联票内（100元），也可单独购买退思园门票（约20元） / Included in Tongli Ancient Town combo ticket (100 RMB); separate entry also available (approx. 20 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全年开放，7:30—17:30 / Open year-round, 7:30 AM — 5:30 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至同里站，换乘吴江公交725路至同里古镇站，步行约5分钟可达。自驾可导航至同里古镇停车场。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, transfer to Wujiang Bus 725, then walk about 5 minutes. By car, navigate to Tongli Ancient Town parking lot.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tuisi_garden_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '内宅（畹芗楼）',
  name_en = 'Inner Residence (Wanxiang Pavilion)',
  body = '<p>Wanxiang Lou is situated behind the main hall, serving as the inner residence where the owner and family conducted daily life. The name "Wanxiang" means "fragrance of orchids," alluding to Qu Yuan''s Li Sao: "I have nurtured orchids in nine fields," symbolizing the owner''s noble character. The two-story building has a ground floor for daily living and dining, with bedrooms upstairs. The interior once featured rosewood furniture, carved beds, and refined ornaments. A small courtyard before the building holds orchids and banana plants, creating a serene atmosphere. Narrow passageways and courtyard walls separate the inner residence from the public halls, forming the traditional layout of "front hall, rear quarters, inner and outer distinct," ensuring family privacy while reflecting the spatial hierarchy of Confucian propriety. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇新镇街退思园内 / Inside Tuisi Garden, XinZhen Street, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 含在同里古镇联票内（100元），也可单独购买退思园门票（约20元） / Included in Tongli Ancient Town combo ticket (100 RMB); separate entry also available (approx. 20 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全年开放，7:30—17:30 / Open year-round, 7:30 AM — 5:30 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至同里站，换乘吴江公交725路至同里古镇站，步行约5分钟可达。自驾可导航至同里古镇停车场。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, transfer to Wujiang Bus 725, then walk about 5 minutes. By car, navigate to Tongli Ancient Town parking lot.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tuisi_garden_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '退思草堂',
  name_en = 'Tuisi Thatched Hall (Hall of Retreat and Reflection)',
  body = '<p>Tuisi Thatched Hall occupies the central position of the garden section, backing against the compound wall to the north and facing the water to the south—the heart of the entire garden. The hall''s name directly expresses the garden''s theme: "Tuisi" (Retreat and Reflection) reflects both the garden''s name and the inner state of Ren Lansheng, who sought self-examination and self-improvement after his demotion. The hall spans three bays with a single-eave gable-and-hip roof and an unadorned exterior without painted decoration; calling it a "thatched hall" heightens the sense of reclusion. A spacious terrace before the hall projects over the water, offering the finest vantage point. From here, the pond, Shuixiang Pavilion, Red Boat, Sky Bridge, and other scenes unfold in a single panorama. The interior is simply furnished with a writing desk, zither table, and armchairs, with calligraphy and paintings on the walls. The owner once read, played the zither, entertained friends, savored tea, and observed the changing seasons here. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇新镇街退思园内 / Inside Tuisi Garden, XinZhen Street, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 含在同里古镇联票内（100元），也可单独购买退思园门票（约20元） / Included in Tongli Ancient Town combo ticket (100 RMB); separate entry also available (approx. 20 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全年开放，7:30—17:30 / Open year-round, 7:30 AM — 5:30 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至同里站，换乘吴江公交725路至同里古镇站，步行约5分钟可达。自驾可导航至同里古镇停车场。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, transfer to Wujiang Bus 725, then walk about 5 minutes. By car, navigate to Tongli Ancient Town parking lot.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tuisi_garden_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '水香榭',
  name_en = 'Shuixiang Pavilion (Water Fragrance Pavilion)',
  body = '<p>Shuixiang Pavilion stands at the southeast corner of Tuisi Garden''s central pond, a square structure half-cantilevered over the water. The name "Shuixiang" (Water Fragrance) evokes the scent of lotus blossoms drifting across the water in summer. The pavilion is light and airy, open on three sides with only one walled side featuring hexagonal latticed windows. The floor sits nearly flush with the water surface—seated inside, one feels suspended above the ripples. This is the finest spot for summer lotus viewing: the pond is planted with lotus, and in midsummer green leaves stretch to the horizon and pink blooms catch the sun, while a breeze carries the fragrance inward. Golden koi dart beneath, their reflections forming living pictures. Tuisi Garden is renowned for "hugging the water," and Shuixiang Pavilion embodies this feature at its purest—the distance between architecture and water reduced to a minimum, merging human and nature into one. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇新镇街退思园内 / Inside Tuisi Garden, XinZhen Street, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 含在同里古镇联票内（100元），也可单独购买退思园门票（约20元） / Included in Tongli Ancient Town combo ticket (100 RMB); separate entry also available (approx. 20 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全年开放，7:30—17:30 / Open year-round, 7:30 AM — 5:30 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至同里站，换乘吴江公交725路至同里古镇站，步行约5分钟可达。自驾可导航至同里古镇停车场。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, transfer to Wujiang Bus 725, then walk about 5 minutes. By car, navigate to Tongli Ancient Town parking lot.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tuisi_garden_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '琴房与眠云亭',
  name_en = 'Qin Room (Zither Room) and Mianyun Pavilion (Cloud-Resting Pavilion)',
  body = '<p>The Qin Room and Mianyun Pavilion are located in the northwest corner of Tuisi Garden, a pair of structures that ingeniously exploit the terrain''s height difference. The Qin Room sits at the lower level—a small chamber facing the water where the owner played the zither and savored tea. The interior is secluded; across the water from Tuisi Thatched Hall, zither music could travel across the pond surface, lingering in the air. Mianyun Pavilion crowns a stone terrace above, reached by stone steps. "Mianyun" (Cloud-Resting) derives from the classical line "lying down to watch clouds rise," suggesting a restful spot as if reclining among clouds. The diminutive pavilion has walls on three sides and a window on the fourth; from here one can overlook the entire garden. The two structures—one low and one high, one at the water''s edge and one against the hill—create rich spatial layering. Gazing up from the Qin Room, Mianyun Pavilion appears as a pavilion in the clouds; looking down from the pavilion, the Qin Room seems a waterside thatched hut—motion and stillness in perfect harmony. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇新镇街退思园内 / Inside Tuisi Garden, XinZhen Street, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 含在同里古镇联票内（100元），也可单独购买退思园门票（约20元） / Included in Tongli Ancient Town combo ticket (100 RMB); separate entry also available (approx. 20 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全年开放，7:30—17:30 / Open year-round, 7:30 AM — 5:30 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至同里站，换乘吴江公交725路至同里古镇站，步行约5分钟可达。自驾可导航至同里古镇停车场。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, transfer to Wujiang Bus 725, then walk about 5 minutes. By car, navigate to Tongli Ancient Town parking lot.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tuisi_garden_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '菰雨生凉',
  name_en = 'Guyu Shengliang (Coolness from Rain on Water Bamboo)',
  body = '<p>Guyu Shengliang stands on the western shore of the pond, a small waterside chamber built flush with the surface. "Gu" refers to water bamboo (Zizania caduciflora), a common waterside plant; "yu sheng liang" depicts the coolness that comes when rain strikes the broad leaves and a breeze ripples across the pond. The chamber opens to the water on three sides with one wall behind, its low roof and eaves nearly touching the surface. On summer days, cool breezes sweep through off the water while water bamboo sways and lotus leaves glisten, instantly dispelling the heat. In gentle rain, droplets striking the leaves and water create a crystalline murmur—a natural symphony that deepens the sense of coolness. A calligraphic plaque inscribed "Gu Yu Sheng Liang" hangs within. This scene fuses sight, sound, and touch—watching green bamboo sway, hearing rain on rippling water, feeling cool wind on the skin—representing the ultimate expression of Tuisi Garden''s art of atmosphere and a paradigm of the Chinese garden principle of "scene evoking emotion, emotion entering realm." - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇新镇街退思园内 / Inside Tuisi Garden, XinZhen Street, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 含在同里古镇联票内（100元），也可单独购买退思园门票（约20元） / Included in Tongli Ancient Town combo ticket (100 RMB); separate entry also available (approx. 20 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全年开放，7:30—17:30 / Open year-round, 7:30 AM — 5:30 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至同里站，换乘吴江公交725路至同里古镇站，步行约5分钟可达。自驾可导航至同里古镇停车场。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, transfer to Wujiang Bus 725, then walk about 5 minutes. By car, navigate to Tongli Ancient Town parking lot.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tuisi_garden_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '天桥与辛台',
  name_en = 'Sky Bridge and Xintai (Xin Terrace)',
  body = '<p>Sky Bridge and Xintai are located in the northeast of Tuisi Garden, an ingenious three-dimensional architectural composition. Sky Bridge is a covered corridor built against the wall, spanning above the pond to connect Tuisi Thatched Hall with Xintai. The bridge is slender with low railings; walking across it feels like skimming over the water, offering views of koi and lotus below. Xintai stands at the bridge''s northern end—a small square pavilion raised above the surrounding level, where the owner read and reflected. The character "Xin" connotes "hardship" and "diligence," echoing the garden''s theme of "retreating to reflect on one''s faults," reminding the owner to persevere even in reclusion. The bridge and pavilion—one horizontal and one vertical, one in motion and one still—generate rich spatial layering within the compact garden. From the bridge, Xintai appears as a pavilion atop a mountain; from Xintai, the bridge resembles a rainbow skimming the water, lending the small garden the feel of vast mountains and forests within a limited space. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇新镇街退思园内 / Inside Tuisi Garden, XinZhen Street, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 含在同里古镇联票内（100元），也可单独购买退思园门票（约20元） / Included in Tongli Ancient Town combo ticket (100 RMB); separate entry also available (approx. 20 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全年开放，7:30—17:30 / Open year-round, 7:30 AM — 5:30 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至同里站，换乘吴江公交725路至同里古镇站，步行约5分钟可达。自驾可导航至同里古镇停车场。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, transfer to Wujiang Bus 725, then walk about 5 minutes. By car, navigate to Tongli Ancient Town parking lot.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tuisi_garden_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '闹红一舸与九曲回廊',
  name_en = 'Naohong Yige (Red Boat) and Nine-Turn Winding Corridor',
  body = '<p>Naohong Yige and the Nine-Turn Corridor are situated around Tuisi Garden''s central pond, forming the garden''s most picturesque composition. "Naohong Yige" is a stone boat-shaped pavilion with its bow pointing toward the center of the pond, as if a skiff were about to glide into a lotus thicket. "Naohong" (Bustling Red) derives from the image of "a touch of red among ten thousand greens," depicting the lively scene of red lotus blooming in a summer pond. The boat is built of stone with a small cabin above where one can sit and enjoy the water views. The Nine-Turn Corridor winds along the eastern shore of the pond, connecting Tuisi Thatched Hall with various scenic spots. The corridor follows the terrain and shoreline through nine bends, hence its name. Its walls are embedded with calligraphic stone tablets and latticed windows, offering ever-changing views at every step. Walking through the corridor, one moment you lean over the water to watch fish, the next you peer through a window at a framed vista—a richly varied spatial experience. The "movement" of the boat and the "winding" of the corridor complement each other, generating boundless pleasure of exploration within a finite space. - 详细地址 / Address： 江苏省苏州市吴江区同里镇新镇街退思园内 / Inside Tuisi Garden, XinZhen Street, Tongli Town, Wujiang District, Suzhou, Jiangsu Province - 门票信息 / Ticket Information： 含在同里古镇联票内（100元），也可单独购买退思园门票（约20元） / Included in Tongli Ancient Town combo ticket (100 RMB); separate entry also available (approx. 20 RMB) - 开放时间 / Opening Hours： 全年开放，7:30—17:30 / Open year-round, 7:30 AM — 5:30 PM - 交通信息 / Transportation： 乘坐地铁4号线至同里站，换乘吴江公交725路至同里古镇站，步行约5分钟可达。自驾可导航至同里古镇停车场。 / Take Metro Line 4 to Tongli Station, transfer to Wujiang Bus 725, then walk about 5 minutes. By car, navigate to Tongli Ancient Town parking lot.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_tuisi_garden_sa_10';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '小河直街历史文化街区入口',
  name_en = 'Xiaohe Straight Street Historical and Cultural Block Entrance',
  body = '<p>The entrance of Xiaohe Straight Street Historical and Cultural Block is located at the intersection of Hushu North Road and Xiaohe Road, adjacent to the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal, and is one of the most completely preserved historical and cultural blocks in northern Hangzhou. A simple stone archway is set up at the entrance of the block, with the four characters "Xiaohe Straight Street" engraved on top, and couplets on both sides depicting the canal customs of the Xiaohe area. Entering the block, underfoot is the main street paved with bluestone slabs, with a large number of wooden residential buildings from the late Qing Dynasty and early Republic of China preserved on both sides, with white walls, dark tiles, and wooden windows and lattices, retaining the original authentic old Hangzhou style. The block is about 300 meters long, with characteristic cafes, handmade workshops, independent bookstores, canal-themed restaurants, and guesthouses along the street. Across the river from Xiaohe Straight Street are Xiaohe Park and Canal Square, where visitors can enjoy the canal scenery and take vintage-style photos. The block is free to open with no admission fee.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xiaohe_street_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '小河直街运河码头遗址',
  name_en = 'Xiaohe Straight Street Canal Pier Ruins',
  body = '<p>The Xiaohe Straight Street Canal Pier Ruins are located at the southern end of Xiaohe Straight Street, at the confluence of the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal and Xiaohe River, and are an important historical witness to Hangzhou''s canal culture. The Xiaohe area, situated at the node where the "Xiaohe" tributary of the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal joins the main canal, has been one of the most important cargo distribution centers in northern Hangzhou since the Ming and Qing dynasties. The existing ruins include the Qing Dynasty stone pier base, mooring stone piles, and old warehouse foundations, among which the deep grooves left by centuries of rope friction on the mooring stone piles are clearly visible, serving as physical witnesses to canal shipping history. The ruins area has now been renovated into an open ruin park, with explanation boards, old photo display walls, and historical maps. An ancient camphor tree over 150 years old is also preserved next to the ruins, which was where dock workers rested in the shade. At dusk, the ruins park is the best location for watching the canal sunset.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xiaohe_street_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '小河直街老邮局',
  name_en = 'Xiaohe Straight Street Old Post Office',
  body = '<p>The Xiaohe Straight Street Old Post Office is located in the middle section of the block and is a post office building constructed in the early Republic of China period, also one of the most completely preserved modern post office buildings in Hangzhou. The building is a two-story brick-wood structure with blue brick exterior walls, wooden floors, and lattice windows, featuring a distinct public building style of the Republic of China period. Although the post office no longer handles traditional postal services, it completely preserves historical facilities such as service counters, post boxes, sorting tables, and old-style telephone switchboards, and has added a postal history exhibition area displaying the development from the late Qing private letter bureaus to modern postal services. The old post office building now houses a cultural creative shop themed "Canal Post Station," selling characteristic products such as Hangzhou-themed postcards, canal scenery stamp albums, and Xiaohe Straight Street custom postmarks. Visitors can buy postcards and have the exclusive Xiaohe Straight Street postmark stamped on-site. The second floor has a nostalgic book bar.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xiaohe_street_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '小河直街手作工坊集群',
  name_en = 'Xiaohe Straight Street Handmade Workshop Cluster',
  body = '<p>T恤，了解中国传统的印染文化；"木墨工坊"提供小规模木工体验，可制作木勺、木簪、小板凳等实用器物。各工坊均有专业手作人现场指导，无需任何基础，适合亲子家庭和手工爱好者。工坊作品同时也对外出售，价格从几十元到上千元不等，均为独一无二的手工制品。建议提前通过各工坊的微信公众号预约体验课程，周末时段尤为紧俏。 The Xiaohe Straight Street Handmade Workshop Cluster is distributed within the old residential buildings on the east and west sides of the block, and is a creative handmade space transformed from the original residential spaces. Over 20 handmade workshops have now settled in. The most characteristic is "Xiaohe Pottery Studio," hosted by a young couple, providing full-process pottery experience including wheel throwing, glazing, and firing, with works fired on-site for taking away. "The Blacksmith Shop" is a workshop centered on traditional metalwork, where visitors can experience forging simple iron objects. "Zhixia Dyeing Workshop" focuses on indigo dyeing and plant dyeing crafts. "Mokumo Workshop" provides small-scale woodworking experience. Each workshop has professional craftspeople for on-site guidance, requiring no foundation, suitable for families and handicraft enthusiasts. Workshop works are also sold to the public, priced from tens to thousands of yuan, all unique handmade products. Advance reservation for experience courses via each workshop''s WeChat account is recommended.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xiaohe_street_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '小河直街运河主题餐厅',
  name_en = 'Xiaohe Straight Street Canal-Themed Restaurants',
  body = '<p>LOGO，是街区最受欢迎的咖啡馆。餐厅大多设有临河座位，游客可边用餐边欣赏运河风光，尤其晚餐时段，在灯光映衬下氛围格外浪漫。建议提前预约周末时段的座位，热门餐厅经常一位难求。 The Xiaohe Straight Street Canal-Themed Restaurants refer to several characteristic dining shops within the block, most of which were converted from old residential buildings, preserving the original wooden structure buildings and courtyard yards, with a simple, elegant, and refined dining environment. The most representative is "Xiaohe Family," specializing in Hangzhou cuisine and canal boat dishes, with signature dishes including West Lake vinegar fish, Longjing shrimp, canal mixed fish pot, and Xiaohe soy sauce duck. "Canal Canteen" is a restaurant with a retro theme, with interior decoration recreating the style of public canteens from the 1960s-70s. "Xiaohe Cafe" was converted from the annex building of the old post office, preserving the original green doors and windows and postal mailboxes. Most restaurants have riverside seats where visitors can enjoy the canal scenery while dining. Reservations for weekend seats are recommended in advance.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xiaohe_street_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '小河公园',
  name_en = 'Xiaohe Park',
  body = '<p>Xiaohe Park is located south of Xiaohe Straight Street, on the west bank of the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal, and is an open urban park converted from the former site of Hangzhou Changzheng Chemical Plant. The park officially opened to the public in 2022, and its design cleverly preserves the original industrial heritage of the chemical plant, including reaction towers, delivery pipes, and oil storage tanks. These facilities and equipment were artistically transformed into visually striking industrial-style landscapes, making it a model case of industrial heritage preservation and reuse in Hangzhou. The park extends along the canal bank line, with waterfront walkways, waterside platforms, viewing pavilions, and leisure lawns. The most famous attraction in the park is the "Eye of the Canal" — a circular viewing platform built on the foundation of an old oil storage tank, from which visitors can get a 360-degree view of the canal and Xiaohe Straight Street. The park seamlessly connects with the Xiaohe Straight Street Historical and Cultural Block. At night, the park lights up, and the industrial heritage is outlined by warm lighting.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xiaohe_street_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '小河直街独立书店',
  name_en = 'Xiaohe Straight Street Independent Bookstore',
  body = '<p>The Xiaohe Straight Street Independent Bookstores refer to several small private bookstores hidden deep within the old residential buildings of the block, unassuming but each with its own characteristics. The most representative is "Xiaohe Study," converted from a two-story wooden structure old residence, with the first floor mainly operating literature, history, art, and Hangzhou local literature, and the second floor equipped with a reading area and small salon space. "Canal Study" is a characteristic bookstore themed on canal culture, collecting a large number of books on the history, geography, and cultural research of the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal. Although these independent bookstores are small in scale, they have high book selection taste and quiet and comfortable reading environment. Most bookstores have tea seats where visitors can order a cup of tea or coffee. Some bookstores also provide accommodation services (bookstore guesthouses).</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xiaohe_street_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '小河直街民宿集群',
  name_en = 'Xiaohe Straight Street Guesthouse Cluster',
  body = '<p>The Xiaohe Straight Street Guesthouse Cluster refers to over ten characteristic guesthouses distributed within the block, all converted from original old residential buildings by the canal. On the basis of preserving the original building structure (wooden beams, blue bricks, courtyards, and decorative windows), modern accommodation facilities and design concepts are integrated, achieving the renovation effect of "repairing the old to look like the old." The most characteristic is "Xiaohe Family Guesthouse," converted from a late Qing Dynasty three-courtyard residence, preserving the complete courtyard and main hall. "Canal Side Youth Hostel" is a cost-effective guesthouse for young tourists. "Xiaohe Moonlight Guesthouse" focuses on a romantic theme. Guesthouse prices range from 200 to 800 RMB, requiring advance reservation on weekends and holidays. Guests can mostly enjoy free breakfast provided by the host and have the opportunity to hear the host tell historical stories and family memories of Xiaohe Straight Street.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xiaohe_street_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '小河直街古桥',
  name_en = 'Xiaohe Straight Street Ancient Bridge',
  body = '<p>The Xiaohe Straight Street Ancient Bridges refer to several ancient stone bridges spanning the Xiaohe River (the tributary that ultimately flows into the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal from Xixi Wetland), among which the most representative are "Xiaohe Bridge" and "Kangjia Bridge." Xiaohe Bridge is a single-arch stone bridge built during the Qianlong period of the Qing Dynasty, with the bridge body constructed of local bluestone, bridge railings carved with simple scroll grass patterns, and the bridge top ground paved with old stone slabs that have become smooth concave surfaces after centuries of pedestrian traffic. Standing on the bridge, visitors can simultaneously see the confluence where Xiaohe River winds into the canal, the Canal Square on the opposite bank, and the distant Gongchen Bridge. Kangjia Bridge is a flat beam stone bridge with a wide and flat deck and stone railings on both sides. The ancient bridge area is free to open all day.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xiaohe_street_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '小河直街夜景',
  name_en = 'Xiaohe Straight Street Night View',
  body = '<p>The Xiaohe Straight Street night view refers to the charming nightscape effect presented by the block after the evening lights are turned on (around 18:00). The block''s nightscape design adopts the concept of "repairing the old to look like the old, seeing light but not lamps," with all lamps hidden within the wooden structures, eaves, and tree clusters of the buildings. Warm yellow light reflects the white walls into soft ivory color, the bluestone pavement surface glows with slight luster, and the red lanterns along the street gently sway in the night breeze. The best viewing route for the night view is walking from the block entrance to Xiaohe Park, passing the old post office, handmade workshops, restaurants, and bookstores. The industrial heritage night view of Xiaohe Park is especially worth seeing. At night, the pedestrian flow on Xiaohe Straight Street is less than during the day, making it more quiet and pleasant. It is recommended to have a canal-themed dinner and then slowly enjoy the night view.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xiaohe_street_sa_10';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '浙江省博物馆之江馆区主入口与大堂',
  name_en = 'Zhejiang Provincial Museum Zhijiang Branch Main Entrance and Lobby',
  body = '<p>The main entrance of the Zhejiang Provincial Museum Zhijiang Branch is located at the center of the Zhijiang Cultural Center building complex and is the main access point for the public. A large plaza is set up in front of the main entrance, with an abstract sculpture in the center of the plaza inspired by the Liangzhu jade cong, implying the long history of Zhejiang civilization. After entering the main entrance, there is a three-story-high central lobby with an area of about 2,000 square meters, with a fully glazed curtain wall design on the top, sufficient natural light, and floor paved with bluestone slabs from Zhejiang. A spiral staircase in the center of the lobby connects the exhibition halls on the first to third floors. The Zhijiang Branch officially opened to the public in 2023, with a construction area of about 100,000 square meters, making it the largest and most advanced comprehensive museum in Zhejiang Province, with a collection of over 100,000 cultural relics, including over 10,000 precious cultural relics. Note: a security check channel is set up at the main entrance.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_zhejiang_museum_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '浙江历史文化陈列厅',
  name_en = 'Zhejiang Historical and Cultural Exhibition Hall',
  body = '<p>AR复原、触摸屏查询等，使观众能够更加直观地了解浙江历史。展览还特别设置了"浙江与世界"板块，介绍了浙江海上丝绸之路的历史和浙江籍华侨华人对世界的贡献。 The Zhejiang Historical and Cultural Exhibition Hall is located on the first and second floors of the Zhijiang Branch, with an exhibition area of about 5,000 square meters, making it the largest and most content-rich permanent exhibition in the Zhijiang Branch. The exhibition is organized by time and divided into six sections: "Dawn of Civilization — Prehistoric Zhejiang," "Zhejiang in the Bronze Age," "Zhejiang in Qin, Han, and Six Dynasties," "Zhejiang in Sui, Tang, and Song," "Zhejiang in Yuan, Ming, and Qing," and "Modern Zhejiang." The most famous exhibits include: Hemudu culture''s artificially cultivated rice remains, Liangzhu culture''s jade cong and bi, bronze swords and ding of the Yue State during the Spring and Autumn Period, Tang Dynasty Yue kiln celadon, a copy of "Along the River During the Qingming Festival" from the Northern Song Dynasty, the remaining section of Huang Gongwang''s "Dwelling in the Fuchun Mountains" from the Yuan Dynasty (on display during special periods), and Ming Dynasty Zhejiang school paintings. The exhibition uses a large number of multimedia interactive facilities.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_zhejiang_museum_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '青瓷文化馆',
  name_en = 'Celadon Culture Hall',
  body = '<p>The Celadon Culture Hall is located on the second floor of the Zhijiang Branch, with an exhibition area of about 2,000 square meters, and is one of the most characteristic thematic exhibitions in the Zhijiang Branch. Zhejiang is the birthplace and main producing area of Chinese celadon. The hall exhibits over 500 celadon masterpieces, spanning from the Eastern Han Dynasty (25-220 AD) to the Ming Dynasty (1368-1644 AD), including over 50 national first-class cultural relics. The most famous exhibits include: Eastern Han Yue kiln celadon jar, Tang Dynasty Yue kiln "mi-se" (secret color) porcelain bowl, Northern Song Ru kiln sky-blue glaze dish, Southern Song Guan kiln vase with tube-shaped ears, Yuan Dynasty Longquan kiln celadon large vase, and Ming Dynasty Chuzhou kiln celadon. The exhibition uses modern display methods such as simulated kilns, dynamic displays of porcelain-making processes, and interactive screens for celadon glaze color comparison.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_zhejiang_museum_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '海洋文化馆',
  name_en = 'Marine Culture Hall',
  body = '<p>AR海底探险、海洋生物识别游戏等互动项目。展览还设有一个360度环幕影院，定期播放海洋主题纪录片，让观众仿佛置身于大海之中。浙江作为海洋强省，该展览对于了解浙江的海洋战略和海洋经济具有重要意义，也是青少年学习海洋知识、培养海洋意识的重要场所。 The Marine Culture Hall is located on the third floor of the Zhijiang Branch, with an exhibition area of about 1,500 square meters, and is a unique new exhibition in the Zhijiang Branch. Zhejiang is one of the provinces with the longest coastline in China, with a long-standing marine culture. The exhibition in the hall is divided into four sections: "Zhejiang Coastline and Islands," "Maritime Silk Road and Zhejiang," "Marine Resources and Ecological Protection," and "Managing the Ocean and Zhejiang''s Future." The most exciting section is "Maritime Silk Road and Zhejiang," which displays the important position of port cities such as Ningbo (Mingzhou), Wenzhou, and Hangzhou in the ancient Maritime Silk Road. The hall also has a 360-degree circular screen cinema that regularly plays marine-themed documentaries. For Zhejiang as a strong maritime province, this exhibition is of great significance for understanding Zhejiang''s marine strategy and marine economy.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_zhejiang_museum_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '书画馆',
  name_en = 'Calligraphy and Painting Hall',
  body = '<p>The Calligraphy and Painting Hall is located on the third floor of the Zhijiang Branch, with an exhibition area of about 1,800 square meters, and is the most important art-themed exhibition in the Zhijiang Branch. Zhejiang is one of the important birthplaces of Chinese calligraphy and painting art, producing countless calligraphy and painting masters throughout history. The collections of the Calligraphy and Painting Hall cover over 1,000 years of history from the Tang Dynasty to modern times, including over 100 national first-class cultural relics. The permanent exhibition displays in chronological order, including: "Tang and Five Dynasties Calligraphy and Painting," "Song and Yuan Calligraphy and Painting," "Ming Dynasty Calligraphy and Painting," "Qing Dynasty Calligraphy and Painting," and "Modern Calligraphy and Painting." The remaining section of Huang Gongwang''s "Dwelling in the Fuchun Mountains" and Zhao Mengfu''s "Autumn Colors on the Qiao and Hua Mountains" (copy) are among the representative works. The exhibition lighting uses professional-grade calligraphy and painting exhibition lighting.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_zhejiang_museum_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '雷峰塔文物馆',
  name_en = 'Leifeng Pagoda Cultural Relics Hall',
  body = '<p>The Leifeng Pagoda Cultural Relics Hall is located on the second floor of the Zhijiang Branch and is a professional exhibition hall established on the basis of the 2002 excavation of the rebuilt Leifeng Pagoda. In 2002, the Zhejiang Provincial Institute of Cultural Relics and Archaeology conducted a scientific excavation of the collapsed Leifeng Pagoda''s underground palace, unearthing over 100 precious cultural relics including a pure silver Ashoka stupa, a gilt dragon-lotus base silver coffin, jade artifacts, agate, crystal, and bronze mirrors, which shocked the archaeological community. The most famous and precious exhibit is the "Pure Silver Ashoka Stupa," 35 cm high and weighing about 1,000 grams, with an openwork body enclosing a gold coffin containing Buddha''s hair relic. It is the only Pure Silver Ashoka Stupa of the Wuyue Kingdom with an exact dated inscription discovered so far. In addition, traditional Buddhist cultural relics such as the gilt dragon-lotus base silver coffin, jade Guanyin statue, and agate prayer beads also have great historical and artistic value. The exhibition comprehensively recreates the entire process of the Leifeng Pagoda underground palace excavation.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_zhejiang_museum_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '之江馆区数字体验馆',
  name_en = 'Zhijiang Branch Digital Experience Hall',
  body = '<p>VR探索区""AR互动区""全息剧场""数字文物修复室""元宇宙文化空间"五大功能区。在"VR探索区"，参观者可以戴上VR眼镜，穿越回到良渚古城、南宋临安城、清代西湖等历史场景之中，以第一视角体验浙江历史上的重要时刻；"AR互动区"则通过AR技术，让静态的文物"活"起来，例如用平板对准一幅古画，画中的人物就会动起来，讲述自己的故事；"全息剧场"采用全息投影技术，无需佩戴任何设备，即可看到立体的历史人物和场景，目前上演的剧目包括"苏东坡在杭州""马可·波罗游杭州"等；"数字文物修复室"让参观者体验文物修复的过程，通过触摸屏完成一件破损文物的"数字修复"，寓教于乐；"元宇宙文化空间"则是一个基于区块链技术的数字艺术展示平台，展示了浙江博物馆推出的数字藏品和NFT作品。数字体验馆特别适合青少年参观，能够激发他们对历史文化的兴趣，同时了解最前沿的科技应用。馆内提供多种语言的语音导览和交互界面，方便外国游客使用。 The Zhijiang Branch Digital Experience Hall is located on the B1 level of the Zhijiang Branch, with an area of about 1,000 square meters, and is the most innovative and technology-rich exhibition space in the Zhijiang Branch. The experience hall is divided into five functional areas: "VR Exploration Zone," "AR Interaction Zone," "Holographic Theater," "Digital Cultural Relics Restoration Room," and "Metaverse Cultural Space." In the "VR Exploration Zone," visitors can put on VR glasses and travel back to historical scenes such as Liangzhu Ancient City, Southern Song Lin''an City, and Qing Dynasty West Lake. The "AR Interaction Zone" uses AR technology to bring static cultural relics to "life." The "Holographic Theater" uses holographic projection technology to display three-dimensional historical figures and scenes without wearing any equipment. The "Digital Cultural Relics Restoration Room" lets visitors experience the process of cultural relic restoration. The "Metaverse Cultural Space" is a digital art display platform based on blockchain technology. The Digital Experience Hall is especially suitable for teenagers.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_zhejiang_museum_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '之江馆区文创商店',
  name_en = 'Zhijiang Branch Cultural Creative Shop',
  body = '<p>U盘、充电宝、首饰、摆件等）、"青瓷"系列（茶杯、茶具、香薰、灯具等）、"雷峰塔阿育王塔"系列（首饰盒、开瓶器、钥匙扣等）。其中"富春山居图"折扇和"良渚玉琮"U盘是店内销量最高的两款产品，极具浙江文化特色，是送礼和自用的佳品。商店还设有"之江书房"角落，出售浙江历史、文化、艺术类的精品图书和期刊，以及博物馆研究成果的学术出版物。所有商品均配有精美的包装，部分产品提供刻字和定制服务。商店支持移动支付、刷卡等多种支付方式，境外游客还可享受免税购物服务（需满足一定金额）。对于想要把"浙江文化带回家"的游客来说，这里是必到之地。 The Zhijiang Branch Cultural Creative Shop is located on the right side of the museum''s main lobby, with an area of about 500 square meters, and is the official cultural creative product retail space of the Zhejiang Provincial Museum Zhijiang Branch. The shop''s products are designed with the concept of "bringing cultural relics to life," drawing inspiration from the museum''s collection of over 100,000 cultural relics. Over 20 series and more than 1,000 cultural creative products have been developed. The best-selling products include: the "Dwelling in the Fuchun Mountains" series (folding fans, bookmarks, notebooks, phone cases, silk scarves, etc.), the "Liangzhu Jade Cong" series (USB drives, power banks, jewelry, ornaments, etc.), the "Celadon" series (tea cups, tea sets, aromatherapy, lamps, etc.), and the "Leifeng Pagoda Ashoka Stupa" series (jewelry boxes, bottle openers, keychains, etc.). The "Dwelling in the Fuchun Mountains" folding fan and "Liangzhu Jade Cong" USB drive are the two highest-selling products. All products come with exquisite packaging.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_zhejiang_museum_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '之江馆区特展厅',
  name_en = 'Zhijiang Branch Special Exhibition Hall',
  body = '<p>The Zhijiang Branch Special Exhibition Hall is located on the north side of the first floor of the Zhijiang Branch, with an exhibition area of about 3,000 square meters, and is the core space for the Zhijiang Branch to host high-level temporary special exhibitions from China and abroad. The special exhibition hall is constructed to world-class standards, equipped with advanced facilities including adjustable professional exhibition lighting, constant temperature and humidity systems, security monitoring systems, and multimedia guide equipment. Since the opening of the Zhijiang Branch in 2023, the special exhibition hall has successfully hosted several influential special exhibitions including "Silk Road Rainbow Costumes — Dunhuang Clothing Art Exhibition," "Song Charm — Song Dynasty Cultural Relics Grand Exhibition," "Longquan in the World — Longquan Celadon Special Exhibition," and "Impressionist Masters — Monet and His Friends." Special exhibitions usually last 2-3 months. During the opening period of some special exhibitions, supporting activities such as academic seminars, expert guided tours, family workshops, and cultural creative markets are also held.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_zhejiang_museum_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '之江文化中心整体参观指南',
  name_en = 'Zhijiang Cultural Center Overall Visiting Guide',
  body = '<p>Zhijiang Cultural Center is located in the Zhijiang area of Hangzhou''s Xihu District and officially opened to the public in 2023 in its entirety. With a total construction area of about 320,000 square meters, it is the largest cultural infrastructure project in Zhejiang Province''s history in terms of investment, specification, and functionality. The cultural center consists of four large cultural buildings in a "four-leaf clover" layout: Zhejiang Provincial Museum Zhijiang Branch (located in the center, largest in scale), Zhejiang Library Zhijiang Branch (located on the east side, the largest public library in Zhejiang), Zhejiang Intangible Cultural Heritage Museum (located on the south side, displaying Zhejiang''s intangible cultural heritage), and Zhejiang Literature Museum (located on the west side, displaying the development history of Zhejiang literature). The four buildings are connected to each other via an underground commercial street and aerial walkways. The cultural center also has supporting facilities such as Zhiduo Book House (24-hour bookstore), cultural creative markets, dining streets, and family activity areas. Recommended visiting route: visit Zhejiang Provincial Museum Zhijiang Branch in the morning, dine in the dining street at noon, visit Zhejiang Library and Intangible Cultural Heritage Museum in the afternoon.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_zhejiang_museum_sa_10';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '西湖文化广场主雕塑',
  name_en = 'West Lake Cultural Square Main Sculpture',
  body = '<p>The main sculpture of West Lake Cultural Square is located at the center of the square and is one of the most important public art landmarks in northern Hangzhou. Inspired by Hangzhou''s history and culture, the sculpture integrates elements such as the Qiantang River tide, West Lake landscapes, and Liangzhu jade, with a majestic design that embodies Hangzhou''s spirit of embracing tradition while pioneering the future. The sculpture stands approximately 20 meters tall, using a combination of stainless steel and stone materials that shine brilliantly in the sunlight. A circular walkway and leisure seats surround the sculpture, making it a popular gathering place for citizens to walk, dance, and relax. At night, the sculpture appears even more spectacular under lighting, complementing the illuminated facades of the surrounding Zhejiang Provincial Science and Technology Museum, Zhejiang Natural History Museum, and Zhejiang Provincial Museum. During festivals such as Lantern Festival and National Day, themed flower displays and light shows are arranged around the sculpture, attracting numerous citizens and visitors.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_west_lake_cultural_plaza_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '浙江省科技馆',
  name_en = 'Zhejiang Provincial Science and Technology Museum',
  body = '<p>VR太空舱、模拟飞行、机器人对战、4D影院等项目深受青少年喜爱。馆内还定期举办科普讲座、科学实验秀、科技夏令营等活动，是杭州中小学生学习科学的第二课堂。科技馆建筑外观以银蓝色为主调，充满未来感，内部空间宽敞明亮，动线设计合理，适合全年龄段游客。特别提醒：周末及节假日人流较大，建议提前在线预约，并预留至少3小时参观时间。 The Zhejiang Provincial Science and Technology Museum is located on the east side of West Lake Cultural Square, with a construction area of approximately 30,000 square meters, making it the largest science education base in Zhejiang Province. The museum features eight permanent exhibition halls: Universe Exploration, Ocean Journey, Earth Home, Life Science, Information Technology, Materials Science, Man and Nature, and Technology and Life, with a total of over 1,000 exhibits, more than 90% of which are interactive. Popular attractions include the VR space capsule, flight simulator, robot battles, and 4D cinema, which are especially loved by teenagers. The museum regularly hosts science lectures, experiment shows, and tech summer camps, serving as a "second classroom" for elementary and middle school students in Hangzhou. The museum''s exterior features a silver-blue futuristic design, with spacious and bright interior spaces and well-planned visitor flow, suitable for visitors of all ages. Note: it gets crowded on weekends and holidays; advance online reservation is recommended, with at least 3 hours needed for a full visit.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_west_lake_cultural_plaza_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '浙江自然博物院（杭州馆）',
  name_en = 'Zhejiang Natural History Museum (Hangzhou Branch)',
  body = '<p>D科普影院和互动探索区，适合亲子家庭。博物院建筑外观以石材和玻璃为主，沉稳大气，与广场整体风格协调统一。 The Zhejiang Natural History Museum (Hangzhou Branch) is located on the west side of West Lake Cultural Square, with a construction area of approximately 26,000 square meters, and is one of the three major provincial-level cultural venues on the square. The museum features permanent exhibitions including the Story of Earth Life, the Rich and Bizarre World of Living Things, Green Zhejiang, and the Wild Places — Kenneth Behring World Wildlife Exhibition, with a collection of over 200,000 specimens. The most striking exhibit is the massive Mamenchisaurus fossil skeleton standing in the central hall, one of Hangzhou''s most recognizable natural science symbols. The Biological World exhibition hall on the second floor displays rare animal specimens from around the world, including Siberian tigers, golden snub-nosed monkeys, African elephants, and penguins, all exquisitely mounted. The Green Zhejiang hall on the third floor uses immersive scenes to recreate Zhejiang''s forest, wetland, and marine ecosystems. The museum also has a 4D science cinema and interactive exploration area, ideal for families.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_west_lake_cultural_plaza_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '浙江省博物馆（武林馆区）',
  name_en = 'Zhejiang Provincial Museum (Wulin Branch)',
  body = '<p>The Wulin Branch of Zhejiang Provincial Museum is located on the south side of West Lake Cultural Square, facing the main sculpture across the square, with a construction area of approximately 20,000 square meters. The museum''s permanent exhibitions include "Zhejiang Historical and Cultural Exhibition," "Highlights of Celadon — Special Exhibition of Ancient Zhejiang Celadon," and "Painting and Calligraphy Masterpieces from the Collection," systematically presenting the development of Zhejiang''s history and culture from prehistoric times to modern times. Famous exhibits include Hemudu culture pottery, Liangzhu culture jade artifacts, Song Dynasty Longquan celadon, the remaining section of Huang Gongwang''s "Dwelling in the Fuchun Mountains" (on display during special periods), and Zhejiang school paintings from the Ming and Qing dynasties. Although smaller than the Zhijiang Branch, the Wulin Branch is centrally located with convenient transportation, making it an important venue for citizens to visit cultural and museum exhibitions. The museum also has a temporary exhibition hall that regularly hosts high-level cultural relic and art exhibitions from China and abroad.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_west_lake_cultural_plaza_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '西湖文化广场音乐喷泉',
  name_en = 'West Lake Cultural Square Music Fountain',
  body = '<p>LED，可呈现红、蓝、绿、紫等多种色彩变化，与周围浙江省科技馆、浙江自然博物院的建筑灯光交相辉映，营造出绚丽的都市夜景。表演曲目涵盖中外经典名曲，包括《梁祝》《茉莉花》等中国名曲以及西方古典音乐片段，每逢整点演奏不同曲目。喷泉池周围设有环形观景台和休闲座椅，是市民夏季纳凉、休闲聚会的热门去处。最佳观赏位置为广场南侧台阶及主雕塑周边。周末和节假日期间观众较多，建议提前15分钟占位。如遇大风或维修等特殊情况，喷泉可能暂停开放，出行前建议关注"西湖文化广场"相关公告。 The West Lake Cultural Square Music Fountain is located in the water pool area south of the main sculpture at the center of the square, and is one of the most popular night scenes in northern Hangzhou. The fountain performance combines background music with water column variations, with water patterns rising and falling with the melody, and the highest water column reaching up to 30 meters. The lighting system uses multi-color LEDs that can display various color changes including red, blue, green, and purple, complementing the architectural lighting of the surrounding Zhejiang Provincial Science and Technology Museum and Zhejiang Natural History Museum, creating a brilliant urban nightscape. Performance repertoire includes Chinese and international classic pieces, such as "Butterfly Lovers" and "Jasmine Flower" as well as Western classical music segments. A different piece is played on the hour. A circular viewing platform and leisure seats surround the fountain pool, making it a popular gathering spot for citizens to cool off in summer. The best viewing positions are the south side steps of the square and areas around the main sculpture. It gets crowded on weekends and holidays; arriving 15 minutes early is recommended.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_west_lake_cultural_plaza_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '运河魂雕塑与亲水平台',
  name_en = 'Canal Soul Sculpture and Waterside Platform',
  body = '<p>The Canal Soul Sculpture Group is located on the west bank of the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal on the east side of West Lake Cultural Square, forming the core of the square''s riverside landscape belt. With the cultural connotation of the canal as its theme, the sculpture group uses a combination of abstract and realistic techniques to depict scenes such as trackers pulling boats, merchants coming and going, and boats shuttling back and forth, vividly recreating the prosperous scene of the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal as the major north-south transportation artery in ancient times. The sculpture group extends along the river bank for about 100 meters, made of bronze and stone, and has been well preserved through the years. The waterside platform extends about 5 meters into the canal with safety railings, where visitors can get close to the canal water and watch boats passing by and historic buildings on the opposite bank. Willow trees and peach trees are planted around the platform; the scene is especially beautiful in spring when the peach blossoms bloom. This is an excellent spot for photographing canal sunsets.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_west_lake_cultural_plaza_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '西湖文化广场地下商业街',
  name_en = 'West Lake Cultural Square Underground Commercial Street',
  body = '<p>The West Lake Cultural Square Underground Commercial Street is located on the B1 level beneath the square, seamlessly connected to the West Lake Cultural Square Station of Metro Line 1 and 3, and was one of the first metro-above commercial projects in Hangzhou. The commercial street extends about 300 meters, connecting the underground entrances of the metro station hall, Zhejiang Provincial Science and Technology Museum, Zhejiang Natural History Museum, and Zhejiang Provincial Museum Wulin Branch, allowing visitors to move between venues without going above ground. The street brings together various dining brands, coffee shops, convenience stores, bookstores, and cultural creative product shops, making it a popular choice for citizens to rest and dine while visiting the museums. Featured shops include Hangzhou local snack brands, canal-themed cultural creative shops, and children''s toy stores. The commercial street operates in sync with the metro, warm in winter and cool in summer. A small activity stage in the center of the commercial street regularly hosts cultural performances, public welfare exhibitions, and interactive experience activities.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_west_lake_cultural_plaza_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '西湖文化广场七夕灯会会场',
  name_en = 'West Lake Cultural Square Qixi Lantern Festival Venue',
  body = '<p>West Lake Cultural Square is one of the core venues for large-scale lantern festivals held annually during the Qixi Festival (the seventh day of the seventh lunar month) in Hangzhou. The lantern festival usually lasts 7-10 days, with the entire square decorated as a lantern world themed on the love story of "The Cowherd and the Weaver Girl." Large themed lantern installations are set up around the main sculpture, a romantic light corridor is arranged along the canal, and fluorescent Qixi patterns are embedded on the square ground, creating a dreamy and beautiful festival atmosphere. During the lantern festival, supporting activities include matchmaking events, love song concerts, Hanfu parades, and floating river lanterns, making it an annual grand event for singles and couples in Hangzhou. In addition to the Qixi Lantern Festival, the square also features themed lantern decorations and flower displays during Lantern Festival, Mid-Autumn Festival, and National Day; the Lantern Festival scale is second only to West Lake scenic area. The square''s open space and complete supporting facilities make it one of the ideal venues for festival events in Hangzhou.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_west_lake_cultural_plaza_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '西湖文化广场城市观景台',
  name_en = 'West Lake Cultural Square Urban Viewing Platform',
  body = '<p>The West Lake Cultural Square Urban Viewing Platform is located on a high terrace at the northwest corner of the square, south of North Huancheng Road, and is a lesser-known urban viewing spot in northern Hangzhou. The platform is about 3 meters above the square ground, with wooden railings and leisure seats, offering an open view of Wulin Square, Hangzhou Tower, high-rise office buildings around West Lake Cultural Square, and the distant Precious Stone Hill and Baochu Pagoda. At dusk, the sunset glow falls on the city buildings, creating excellent lighting effects, making it a favorite shooting spot for photography enthusiasts. Tall trees are planted around the platform, providing good shade in summer. Compared with famous urban viewing spots, there are fewer tourists here, with a quieter and more leisurely atmosphere. The platform is connected to the main square area by a gentle slope walkway with barrier-free access. Public toilets and drinking water stations are available nearby.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_west_lake_cultural_plaza_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '西湖文化广场银杏大道',
  name_en = 'West Lake Cultural Square Ginkgo Avenue',
  body = '<p>The West Lake Cultural Square Ginkgo Avenue refers to the ginkgo tree array planted along the square''s perimeter, along North Zhongshan Road and North Huancheng Road, with a total of about 200 ginkgo trees, most over 20 years old, with thick trunks and dense crowns. Every year from mid-to-late November to early December, the ginkgo leaves turn from green to yellow, and the entire avenue resembles a golden corridor, forming a sharp contrast with the modern architectural complex of the square, making it one of the most popular free autumn viewing spots in Hangzhou. The best shooting time is 9-10 am when the sunlight hits at an angle, with golden leaves appearing translucent and dazzling in the sun, creating a highly layered composition with the square''s main sculpture and provincial cultural venue buildings as background. During autumn weekends, the avenue gathers numerous photography enthusiasts, Hanfu enthusiasts, and wedding photographers. The ginkgo leaf falling period is mid-to-late December, when the fallen leaves covering the ground create an equally beautiful scene.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_west_lake_cultural_plaza_sa_10';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '西溪国家湿地公园北门入口',
  name_en = 'Xixi National Wetland Park North Gate Entrance',
  body = '<p>The North Gate Entrance of Xixi National Wetland Park is located on Tianmu Mountain Road and is the main access point for visitors entering Xixi Wetland. A large visitor service center is set up at the entrance, providing comprehensive services including ticket sales, tour guide reservation, wheelchair borrowing, stroller rental, umbrella borrowing, and first-aid kits. Ticket windows support various payment methods including cash, card, and mobile payment; advance ticket purchase via the official WeChat account with QR code entry is also available. The north gate entrance plaza is spacious, with luggage storage lockers, vending machines, public toilets, and barrier-free facilities. After entering from the north gate, visitors first arrive at the Lotus Pond Leisure Area, and can follow the main walking trail to major attractions such as Qiuxue Nunnery, Shentankou, and Hezhu Street. The north gate is also the starting station for the park''s battery-powered sightseeing carts, from which visitors can take a cart tour of about 1 hour. Multiple parking lots are available around the entrance, but spaces are tight during holidays; taking Metro Line 3 to Xixi Wetland South or North Station and then transferring to bus or walking is recommended.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xixi_wetland_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '秋雪庵',
  name_en = 'Qiuxue Nunnery',
  body = '<p>Qiuxue Nunnery is located on an island in the central area of Xixi National Wetland Park, first built during the Song Dynasty, and is one of the oldest and most culturally profound attractions in Xixi Wetland. The nunnery is surrounded by water on all sides and can only be reached by wooden boat, with a quiet and secluded environment that feels like a hidden paradise. Every deep autumn (November), the reed marshes around the nunnery turn completely white, and when the breeze blows, the reed catkins fly like snow — hence the name "Qiuxue" (Autumn Snow) Nunnery. The main buildings in the nunnery include the Great Buddha Hall, Guanyin Hall, and Sutra Pavilion, with a simple and elegant architectural style that harmonizes with the natural wetland environment. The nunnery is also the best location for viewing the panorama of Xixi Wetland; ascending the building provides a view of thousands of acres of reed marshes, crisscrossing waterways, and quaint stone bridges. A wooden boardwalk and viewing platform are set up outside the nunnery for visitors to walk and enjoy close-up views of wetland plants and birds. Note: reaching Qiuxue Nunnery requires taking a rowing boat or battery boat within the park; boat tickets must be purchased separately.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xixi_wetland_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '深潭口与河渚街',
  name_en = 'Shentankou and Hezhu Street',
  body = '<p>Shentankou is the liveliest area within Xixi National Wetland Park and became famous after being featured in the movie "If You Are the One." Surrounded by water on all sides with ancient camphor trees providing shade, it is the area where the traditional water town character of Xixi is best preserved. Hezhu Street is the main pedestrian street at Shentankou, built along the river, with buildings in Ming and Qing style on both sides, now converted into various specialty shops including Xixi Wetland reed paintings, Xixi fish balls, "Dingsheng" cakes, sugar painting, and dough figurine making. The street also features free folk performances including Yue opera, shadow puppetry, and folk martial arts, staged daily on the ancient stage at scheduled times. Shentankou Pier is the largest cruise boat transfer station in Xixi Wetland, from which visitors can take boats to Qiuxue Nunnery, Zhoujia Village, and Qianjin Yang. During the Dragon Boat Festival, the Xixi Wetland Dragon Boat Racing is held at Shentankou, one of Hangzhou''s most traditional festival events. Several waterside teahouses and restaurants are located around the block.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xixi_wetland_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '西溪梅墅',
  name_en = 'Xixi Plum Villa',
  body = '<p>Xixi Plum Villa is located in the southeast of Xixi National Wetland Park and is a thematic scenic area centered on plum blossom viewing within the park. Xixi has enjoyed the reputation of "Xixi Plums" since ancient times, and together with Gushan plum blossoms and Lingfeng plum blossoms, is known as one of the three major plum blossom viewing destinations in Hangzhou. The Plum Villa area has more than 5,000 plum trees of dozens of varieties including Jiangmei, Gongfen, Zhusha, Lü''e, and Yudie, with the oldest trees being over a hundred years old. Every year during the plum blossom season (February-March), the entire Plum Villa resembles a natural ink painting, with pink-white, deep red, and light green blossoms adorning the branches, filling the air with fragrance, attracting numerous photography enthusiasts and citizens. The Plum Villa also preserves a group of Qing Dynasty-style ancient buildings, now the Plum Blossom Culture Exhibition Hall, which systematically introduces the historical origin, variety classification, and cultivation techniques of Xixi plum culture. Plum forest trails, plum viewing pavilions, and photography platforms are set up within the scenic area.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xixi_wetland_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '莲花滩观鸟区',
  name_en = 'Lianhuatan Bird Watching Area',
  body = '<p>The Lianhuatan Bird Watching Area is located in the west of Xixi National Wetland Park and is the area with the most complete ecosystem protection and richest bird resources in Xixi Wetland. With dense vegetation, crisscrossing waterways, and interlaced shallow and deep water areas, it provides an ideal foraging, breeding, and habitat environment for various wetland birds. Three hidden bird watching huts are set up within the bird watching area, built with environmentally friendly wood, with exteriors simulating natural rocks and shrubs, and equipped with telescopes, bird field guides, and interpretation signs inside, allowing visitors to observe at close range without disturbing the birds. Over 190 bird species have been recorded in Xixi Wetland, including national first-class protected birds such as Oriental Stork, White-tailed Sea Eagle, and Hooded Crane, and national second-class protected birds such as Eurasian Spoonbill, Tundra Swan, and Mandarin Duck. Every winter (December-February) is the best season for bird watching, when flocks of overwintering migratory birds arrive at Xixi Wetland. Spring is the bird breeding season, when various bird courtship, nesting, and chick-rearing behaviors can be observed.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xixi_wetland_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '西溪草堂',
  name_en = 'Xixi Thatched Cottage',
  body = '<p>Xixi Thatched Cottage is located in the central part of Xixi National Wetland Park and is a reconstructed ancient building complex modeled after the original Xixi Thatched Cottage of Feng Mengzhen, a literatus of the Ming Dynasty. Feng Mengzhen was a famous writer and dramatist of the Ming Dynasty who lived in seclusion in Xixi, wrote books here, and left a large number of poems and essays describing the beauty of Xixi. The cottage complex includes a main hall, study, bedroom, kitchen, and garden, all constructed using traditional wooden structure craftsmanship, with thatched roof and wooden plank walls, simple and natural, blending perfectly with the wetland environment. The interior of the cottage recreates the furnishings of a Ming Dynasty literati''s study, including a writing desk, the Four Treasures of the Study, a guqin, and ancient books. A teahouse is also set up in the cottage, where visitors can enjoy tea and experience the pleasure of "stealing half a day''s leisure from a busy life." This is one of the scenic spots with the richest cultural connotations in Xixi Wetland. Every autumn, the cottage also hosts Xixi cultural lectures and ancient poetry recitation activities.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xixi_wetland_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '西溪龙舟陈列馆',
  name_en = 'Xixi Dragon Boat Exhibition Hall',
  body = '<p>The Xixi Dragon Boat Exhibition Hall is located next to Hezhu Street in Xixi National Wetland Park and is a thematic museum with the theme of dragon boat culture. The Xixi Wetland Dragon Boat Race has a history of over a thousand years and is one of the most representative traditional festival activities in the Hangzhou area. The "Xixi Dragon Boat Racing" held annually during the Dragon Boat Festival has been included in the National Intangible Cultural Heritage List. The exhibition hall systematically displays the historical origin of Xixi dragon boats, dragon boat making craftsmanship, dragon boat race rules, and the grand occasions of previous dragon boat festivals. The collection includes various dragon boat models, dragon boat paddles, gongs and drums, and traditional costumes, among which a full-scale replica of a Qing Dynasty Xixi dragon boat is the biggest highlight. A multimedia interactive area is also set up in the hall, where visitors can learn about the entire dragon boat making process via touch screen and watch exciting videos of previous dragon boat races. A dragon boat experience pool is set up outside the hall.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xixi_wetland_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '西溪湿地生态科普馆',
  name_en = 'Xixi Wetland Ecological Science Popularization Hall',
  body = '<p>The Xixi Wetland Ecological Science Popularization Hall is located in the east of Xixi National Wetland Park and is a modern exhibition hall with the core mission of popularizing wetland ecological system scientific knowledge. The museum''s permanent exhibitions include six sections: "What is a Wetland," "Formation of Xixi Wetland," "Wetland Plant Kingdom," "Wetland Animal World," "Wetlands and Humans," and "Protection of Xixi Wetland," which systematically introduce the definition, types, functions, and global distribution of important wetlands, as well as the geological origin, biodiversity, and protection achievements of Xixi Wetland through various forms including graphic panels, physical specimens, scene restorations, and multimedia interactions. The most attractive area for children is the "Wetland Animal World" interactive zone, featuring a touch pool (where safe aquatic organisms can be touched), bird call identification games, and wetland food chain puzzles. The science hall also regularly hosts characteristic educational activities such as "Wetland Little Guardian" family activities, wetland plant adoption, and bird watching training camps.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xixi_wetland_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '西溪湿地摇橹船体验',
  name_en = 'Xixi Wetland Rowing Boat Experience',
  body = '<p>The rowing boat is the most characteristic transportation and touring method in Xixi Wetland, with a history of over a thousand years. Unlike the painted pleasure boats of West Lake, Xixi''s rowing boats are smaller and slower, with the boatman standing at the stern and propelling the boat forward by stepping on the scull and holding the scull handle, with elegant movements full of ancient charm. Each rowing boat can seat 2-4 people, with a sunshade and cushioned seats for comfortable riding. The boat route covers the core protected area of Xixi Wetland, including Qiuxue Nunnery, Shentankou, Zhoujia Village, and Lianhuatan, with a total duration of about 1.5-2 hours. Sitting on the rowing boat, visitors can enjoy close-up views of reeds, camphor trees, and tallow trees along the wetland banks, watch water birds such as egrets, mallards, and kingfishers, and feel the Xixi artistic conception of "one bend of stream, one wisp of smoke." The boatman is usually also a narrator who introduces attractions along the way and Xixi''s historical stories in Hangzhou dialect or Mandarin. The rowing boat experience at sunset is the most romantic.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xixi_wetland_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '西溪洪园',
  name_en = 'Xixi Hong''s Garden',
  body = '<p>Courts钱塘书院、清平山堂等，建筑风格典雅古朴，园内遍植梅花、桂花、荷花等花卉，四季皆有景致。洪昇纪念馆详细介绍了这位《长生殿》作者的生平和创作历程，馆内还收藏有《长生殿》的各种版本和相关研究文献，是戏曲爱好者必访之地。洪园的设计将明清园林艺术与西溪湿地自然景观完美结合，园内有大片水塘，种满了荷花，夏季荷花盛开时景色尤为壮观，有"西溪荷花园"之美誉。园中还设有茶室和文创商店，游客可品洪园特色茶点、购买洪氏文化主题纪念品。每年梅花盛开时节，洪园还会举办"洪园梅花节"，汇集文人雅集、古琴演奏、茶道表演等活动。 Xixi Hong''s Garden is located in the southwest of Xixi National Wetland Park and is the core scenic area of the second-phase development of Xixi Wetland, themed on the cultural heritage of the Hong family of Hangzhou during the Ming and Qing dynasties. The Hong family was one of the most influential cultural families in Hangzhou''s history, producing historical celebrities such as Hong Sheng (famous dramatist and author of "The Palace of Eternal Youth") and Hong Yixuan (famous scholar). The main buildings in Hong''s Garden include the Hong Clan Ancestral Hall, Hong Sheng Memorial Hall, Qiantang Academy, and Qingping Mountain Hall, with elegant and simple architectural styles. The garden is planted with plum blossoms, osmanthus, lotus, and other flowers, offering scenery in all seasons. The Hong Sheng Memorial Hall introduces the life and creative journey of the author of "The Palace of Eternal Youth" in detail. The design of Hong''s Garden perfectly combines Ming and Qing garden art with the natural landscape of Xixi Wetland. A large pond in the garden is full of lotus, which is especially spectacular when the lotus blooms in summer, earning it the reputation of "Xixi Lotus Garden." The garden also hosts the "Hong''s Garden Plum Blossom Festival" every plum blossom season.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'hangzhou_xixi_wetland_sa_10';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '海关大楼',
  name_en = '海关大楼 / Customs House (Shanghai)',
  body = '<p>Joyce &amp; Co.钟厂铸造，每十五分钟报时一次，浑厚的钟声曾响彻黄浦江两岸，被称为"亚洲第一钟"。大楼至今仍为上海海关办公使用，是外滩"万国建筑博览会"的灵魂坐标。</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'the_bund_shanghai_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '和平饭店',
  name_en = '和平饭店 / Peace Hotel (Fairmont Peace Hotel)',
  body = '<p>Sir Victor Sassoon）投资，公和洋行设计，建成于1929年，原名沙逊大厦，曾为"远东第一高楼"。建筑为装饰艺术风格，高十层，外立面以花岗岩贴面，顶部冠以标志性的绿色铜金字塔尖顶，在阳光下格外醒目。大楼内设华懋饭店（Cathay Hotel），曾是20世纪上半叶远东最顶级的酒店，卓别林、萧伯纳等名流曾下榻于此。1952年更名为和平饭店，2007年至2010年完成大规模修缮，现由费尔蒙酒店集团管理运营，拥有标志性的茉莉酒廊与九国特色套房。</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'the_bund_shanghai_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '外滩牛',
  name_en = '外滩牛 / Bund Bull (Shanghai Financial Bull)',
  body = '<p>Arturo Di Modica）创作，于2010年上海世博会期间正式揭幕。迪莫迪卡正是纽约华尔街铜牛的原作者，因此外滩牛与华尔街铜牛为"姊妹之作"。铜像采用铸铜工艺，通体呈暗红色，重约2.5吨，体量略大于华尔街铜牛。公牛呈低头蓄力、昂首挺角之姿，肌肉线条饱满，充满向前冲击的力量感，寓意"牛市"繁荣与上海金融市场的稳健发展。雕塑落成后迅速成为外滩热门打卡地标，游客常以触摸牛角祈求财运。</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'the_bund_shanghai_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '中文：上海城市历史发展陈列馆',
  name_en = 'English: Shanghai History Development Exhibition Hall',
  body = '<p>- "Ten-Mile Foreign Settlement" Street Scene: 1930s Bund Nanjing Road recreation with bronze carriages, vintage trams, and calendar posters - Lilong Lane Scene: Restored Shikumen life in old Shanghai - Pudong Development Sandbox: 1:500 dynamic scale model of Lujiazui core area - Interactive Photo Spots: Pose with 1930s calendar girls and qipao-clad beauties - VR Experience: Free 5-minute "Time Travel to 1930" VR walkthrough - Recommended visit duration: 60–90 minutes, can be flexibly split before and after the tower climb</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'oriental_pearl_radio_television_tower_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '一楼-Kate&Kevin定制工坊',
  name_en = 'Kate&Kevin定制工坊',
  body = '<p>Kate&amp;Kevin定制工坊坐落在一层东翼靠门厅一侧，是市场内最早以"全英文沟通+全定制流程"对外运营的工作室之一。店内陈列着真丝礼服、缎面旗袍、香云纱外套、蕾丝婚纱与晚装样衣，墙上挂满意大利、英国、日本进口面料的样卡。创始人Kate与Kevin坚持"一人一版"立裁：先以英式手法在模特上直接修剪胚布，再根据客户肩颈、胸腰、臀围比例做半成品试衣，最后以手工锁边、盘扣、隐形拉链收尾。工坊擅长礼服、旗袍、婚嫁系列，也承接中式立领与西式礼服的中西合璧设计。定制周期通常为7—14天，旺季（3月、5月、9—10月）建议提前预约。工坊与四楼黄浦邮政服务台联动，可直接将成衣寄送至全球170多个国家和地区。 The Kate &amp; Kevin bespoke studio sits in the east wing of the first floor, near the entrance lobby, and is one of the earliest studios in the market to operate fully in English with an end-to-end bespoke workflow. Sample gowns hang throughout the room—silk evening dresses, satin qipao, Xiangyunsha outerwear, lace bridal gowns, and cocktail dresses—while the walls display swatch cards of imported fabrics from Italy, the United Kingdom, and Japan. Founders Kate and Kevin follow a "one person, one pattern" draping method, beginning with British-style toile work on the form, then a basted fitting that respects the client''s shoulder, neck, bust, waist, and hip proportions, and finishing with hand-stitched hems, pankou knots, and concealed zippers. The studio specializes in evening gowns, qipao, and bridal collections, as well as fusion pieces that combine Chinese standing collars with Western silhouettes. Lead time is usually 7–14 days, and appointments are recommended in peak seasons (March, May, and September–October). In partnership with the Huangpu Post Office counter on the fourth floor, finished garments can be shipped directly to more than 170 countries and regions.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'south_bund_fabric_market_commonly_known_as_dongjiadu_fabric_market_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '宋庆龄故居（武康路 393 号）',
  name_en = 'Former Residence of Soong Ching-ling (No. 393 Wukang Road)',
  body = '<p>Located at No. 393 Wukang Road, the residence was moved into by Soong Ching-ling in 1948 and remained her home until her death in 1981 — her longest-tenured Shanghai residence and the place where she received the most Chinese and foreign guests. After Shanghai''s liberation in 1949 it also served as a state guest parlor. Converted into a memorial museum after her death in 1981, the residence officially opened to the public in 1982. The collection holds over 15,000 items — photographs with Sun Yat-sen, Chongqing-era wartime clothing, post-1949 diplomatic gifts, late-life manuscripts, and personal effects. The main building is a 1920s Western garden residence; the front and rear gardens remain open and simple, with the dining room and parlor preserved as Soong Ching-ling kept them — one of Shanghai''s most important "celebrity residence + state parlor" complexes.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'wukang_road_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '周璇旧居（武康路 391 弄 1 号）',
  name_en = 'Former Residence of Zhou Xuan (No. 1, Lane 391, Wukang Road)',
  body = '<p>Located at No. 1, Lane 391 of Wukang Road, this is one of 1930s—40s "Golden Voice" singer Zhou Xuan''s several Shanghai residences. The building is a 1920s three-story brick-and-timber Western-style residence with cream-yellow walls, a corner balcony on the second floor, and dormer windows on the third — a simple and understated façade. The lane is a private "new-style lilong," used by Zhou Xuan''s family and peers in the entertainment world. After Zhou Xuan passed away in 1957 the building reverted to private ownership and has never been publicly opened; it remains a private plot. Visitors can view the façade and take photos from the lane entrance, but the interior is not accessible. It is best combined with other celebrity residences along Wukang Road for a "Searching for Socialites Beneath the Plane Trees" themed walk.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'wukang_road_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '意大利总领事馆旧址（武康路 390 号）',
  name_en = 'Former Italian Consulate-General Residence (No. 390 Wukang Road)',
  body = '<p>Located at No. 390 Wukang Road, this building was designed and built by Credit Foncier d''Extreme-Orient in 1932 as the Italian consul-general''s residence in Shanghai. The site covers about 2,630 m² with a floor area of 612 m², a half-basement + two above-ground-floor brick-and-stone mixed structure. The main façade faces south toward the garden; the east, south, and west sides of the ground floor are all open arcades, with red barrel-tile pitched roofs combined with semicircular and square window openings — one of Shanghai''s rare surviving Mediterranean-style garden residences. After 1949 it served as offices for Shanghai''s machinery and electrical systems; from 1995 it was assigned to SAIC Motor. After renovation, from 2024 it has operated as the "Mediterranean Lifestyle Hall" with reservation-based public access to the building, garden, and small art exhibitions.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'wukang_road_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '巴金故居（武康路 113 号）',
  name_en = 'Former Residence of Ba Jin (No. 113 Wukang Road)',
  body = '<p>Located at No. 113 Wukang Road, this was Ba Jin''s residence from 1955 — when he moved here from Huaihai Lane — until his death in 2005, a span of nearly half a century and his longest-tenured Shanghai home with the highest output. The building is a three-bay two-story detached garden villa built in the 1920s, with simple gray-brick façades, a modest gate, and a garden preserving the magnolia and cherry trees Ba Jin himself planted. From 1958—2003, here he completed Random Thoughts (five volumes, 150 essays), True Words, In Sickness, and other major works, and hosted many Chinese and overseas scholars of his writing. Officially opened to the public in 2011, the interior retains the original arrangement of Ba Jin''s furniture, desk, bookcases, and phonograph. Exhibits include manuscripts, letters, photographs, books, and personal items of Ba Jin and his wife Xiao Shan.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'wukang_road_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = 'M50创意园（翠绿色）',
  name_en = 'M50创意园（翠绿色） / M50 Creative Park (Emerald-green)',
  body = '<p>M50创意园位于上海市普陀区莫干山路50号，是上海最早的创意产业集聚区之一，也是世界十大艺术区之一、苏州河畔保留最完整的民族工业建筑群。其前身为上海春明粗纺厂等纺织厂房，2004年9月被上海市文化工作会议规划为"莫干山路视觉艺术特色街区"。园内沿街涂鸦密布，云集上百家画廊、艺术工作室、设计公司与创意店铺，被《TIME》杂志亚洲版列为推荐前往的上海文化地标。翠绿色对应其常春藤与新生的工业文艺气质，是"苏州河十二国色"12种国色的第4种。</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_creek_twelve_nations_colors_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '创享塔（木槿色）',
  name_en = '创享塔（木槿色） / The X Tower Chuangxiangta (Hibiscus)',
  body = '<p>THE X TOWER）位于上海市普陀区叶家宅路100号，地处长寿路商圈，紧邻苏州河畔。前身为1938年由德国人设计建造的宝成纱厂，曾作为日本人在华东最重要的军服缝制基地，留有标志性的瞭望塔。2018年改造升级为以"共享、开放"为理念的创意园区，总建筑面积约29000平方米，集创意工作站、联合办公、餐饮休闲、网红市集与生活体验于一体。木槿色对应其粉紫渐变、温柔且富生命力的春日气息，是"苏州河十二国色"12种国色的第5种。</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'suzhou_creek_twelve_nations_colors_sa_12';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '四川汉代陶石艺术馆（成都博物院一楼）',
  name_en = 'Sichuan Han Dynasty Ceramic & Stone Art Gallery (Chengdu Museum, 1F)',
  body = '<p>Located on the museum''s 1F core, this is China''s only gallery dedicated to Sichuan Han-dynasty pictorial bricks and carved stones. Hundreds of masterpieces from Pengshan, Xinjin, Pixian, and Xindu are organized into four zones: manor-farming and archery-harvest, markets and salt-wells, mythic auspiciousness, and chariots-banquets. The iconic "Archery and Harvest" brick captures a hunter, startled wild geese, and rippling rice fields; the "Salt Well" brick documents the deep-well brine extraction at Linqiong (home of Zhuo Wenjun), the world''s earliest visual record of salt production. Smiling storytellers, drummers, and qin-players in the pottery zone are evidence of Han-era Sichuan''s cheerful, secular folk spirit. Multimedia stations let visitors zoom into brick details and hear expert commentary.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'sichuan_museum_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '远古四川·史前时期展厅（成都博物院二楼）',
  name_en = 'Ancient Sichuan – Prehistoric Era Hall (Chengdu Museum, 2F)',
  body = '<p>This hall is the prologue of the "Hua Chong Jin Guan Cheng" chronological exhibition. The trail begins with the 2.04-million-year-old Wushan Man tooth fossil, moves through Ziyang Man (Palaeolithic), Gaoshan Ancient City, the Baodun culture, and culminates in the Sanxingdui–Jinsha sites—revealing how the Chengdu Plain nurtured China''s earliest, largest, and most imaginative ancient Shu civilization. Highlights include a section model of Baodun''s city wall (~2700 BCE), 4,500-year-old paddy-field remains, and replicas of face-painted pottery pots, bird-head ladle handles, and jade yazhang ritual blades. Immersive projections let visitors "enter" ancient Shu sacrificial grounds, understanding Sanxingdui–Jinsha not as alien imports but as the indigenous pinnacle of Sichuan''s own civilizational arc.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'sichuan_museum_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '古代四川·先秦至秦汉三国展厅（成都博物院二楼）',
  name_en = 'Ancient Sichuan – Pre-Qin to Qin-Han-Three Kingdoms Hall (Chengdu Museum, 2F)',
  body = '<p>This hall is Chapter 2 of the "Hua Chong Jin Guan Cheng" chronological exhibition. The narrative moves from the legendary Twelve Shu Kings (Cancong, Du Yu, Kaiming) to the Qin conquest of Ba and Shu (316 BCE), the "colonization of Shu" policies, Li Bing''s construction of Dujiangyan (256 BCE), Wen Weng''s schools, and Han-era artifacts—the Li Bing stone statue, storyteller figurines, and cliff-tomb models. A Dujiangyan sand-table with dynamic water projection reveals the engineering genius of Yuzui, Feishayan, and Baopingkou. The finale explores Three Kingdoms Shu—Shu brocade, Zhuge crossbow, and the zhi-bai coin—showing how the "Land of Abundance" moved from periphery to center stage in the Han–Three Kingdoms era. Allow at least 40 minutes for the dense exhibits.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'sichuan_museum_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '巴蜀青铜器馆（成都博物院二楼）',
  name_en = 'Ba-Shu Bronze Ware Gallery (Chengdu Museum, 2F)',
  body = '<p>D铜壶模型、放大纹饰、对比三星堆青铜面具的造型差异，看懂巴蜀青铜与中原青铜"同源异流"的关系。 This is one of the most academically rich galleries in the museum. The collection focuses on late Warring States to early Western Han Ba-Shu bronzes, organized into ritual, weapon, musical, daily-use, and coin categories. The headline piece—the "Inlaid Bronze Pot with Banquet, Music, Water and Land Battle Scenes"—stands ~40 cm tall and uses metal inlay to depict five scenes (mulberry-picking, archery, feasting, water battle, land battle) with nearly 200 miniature figures, hailed as "the earliest bronze War and Peace." Tiger-pattern ge-daggers, willow-leaf swords, and boat-coffin bronze plaques reflect Ba-Shu''s tiger worship and fishing-hunting culture. Multimedia stations let visitors rotate 3D models, zoom inlay details, and compare the lineage differences between Ba-Shu and Central Plains bronzes.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'sichuan_museum_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '陶瓷馆（成都博物院二楼）',
  name_en = 'Ceramics Gallery (Chengdu Museum, 2F)',
  body = '<p>Located on 2F East Wing, the gallery chronologically presents ~400 representative pieces: Han green-glazed pottery, Tang Qingyao tri-colors, Song-Yuan Jingdezhen bluish-white porcelain, Ming-Qing blue-and-white and wucai, and late-Qing/Republic qianjiang enamels. The Qionglai (Qingyao) kiln takes center stage—China''s largest southwestern folk kiln system, whose oil-saving lamps, stamped stem-cups, and flambé-glaze bowls were praised by Lu You''s "Laoxue''an Notes." A multimedia reconstruction of the Shifangtang kiln site lets visitors follow clay-purifying, throwing, glazing, firing, and unloading steps. The finale showcases "export porcelain" from Chengdu customs and the Ya''an Tea-Horse Road, revealing Chengdu''s role as a tea-horse corridor and Southern Silk Road hub in East-West ceramic trade.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'sichuan_museum_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '张大千书画馆·大风堂（成都博物院二楼）',
  name_en = 'Zhang Daqian Painting & Calligraphy Gallery – Dafengtang (Chengdu Museum, 2F)',
  body = '<p>Zhang Daqian (1899–1983) is one of the 20th century''s most internationally influential Chinese painters. The museum—located in his long-time creative base of Chengdu—hosts the Dafengtang memorial hall, displaying his artistic evolution in three phases. Early works like "Lotus" and "Imitation of Shitao Landscape" reveal literati elegance; the mid-period features 1:1 copies of Dunhuang Mogao frescoes and previously unpublished sketch drafts from his 1941–43 pilgrimage; the late-period showcases splash-ink and splash-color masterpieces such as "Ten-Thousand Li of the Yangtze," "Peach Blossom Spring," and "Love-Traces Lake." The gallery''s vitrine also displays Daqian''s personal brushes, seals, palette, and Panama hat—primary sources for biographical research.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'sichuan_museum_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '书画馆（成都博物院二楼）',
  name_en = 'Painting & Calligraphy Gallery (Chengdu Museum, 2F)',
  body = '<p>Echoing the Zhang Daqian hall, this gallery is organized into four themes: Song academic style, Yuan literati, Ming-Qing Ba-Shu masters, and modern Shu-connected artists. Highlights include rubbing-and-original editions of Su Shi''s "Gongfu Tie," Wen Tong''s "Huzhou Bamboo School" ink-bamboos, Yang Shen''s running-script, works by Tang Yin, Wen Zhengming, Dong Qichang, plus modern masters with Shu ties—Kang Youwei, Liang Qichao, Yu You-ren, Guo Moruo, Xu Beihong, Qi Baishi, and Huang Binhong. Museum-grade temperature-controlled vitrines rotate exhibits seasonally: Spring Festival couplets, Duanwu fan paintings, and an autumn Ba-Shu master show. Digital kiosks allow searching the museum''s full calligraphy and painting archive by dynasty, author, or theme.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'sichuan_museum_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '藏传佛教文物馆（成都博物院三楼）',
  name_en = 'Tibetan Buddhist Artifacts Gallery (Chengdu Museum, 3F)',
  body = '<p>Located on 3F West Wing, this hall reflects Sichuan''s role as a Sino-Tibetan cultural hub. The collection centers on Ming-Qing gilt-bronze statues, thangkas, mandalas, ritual implements, dharma bells, gyaling horns, and Tibetan sutra woodblocks, organized by five major schools: Tsongkhapa lineage, Gelug, Nyingma, Sakya, and Kagyu. The highlight is an ~80 cm Yongle-era (Ming) imperial gilt-bronze Buddha of extraordinary craftsmanship; alongside a set of 13 ~1.5m × 1m thangkas depicting the Life of Shakyamuni, still vibrant after five centuries. An interactive "mani wheel" wall lets visitors spin carved wooden prayer wheels and experience daily Tibetan Buddhist practice. The hall is the best window into western Sichuan Tibetan-region culture and history.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'sichuan_museum_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '万佛寺石刻馆（成都博物院三楼）',
  name_en = 'Wanfo Temple Stone Sculpture Gallery (Chengdu Museum, 3F)',
  body = '<p>Wanfo Temple, near Tongjin Bridge outside Chengdu''s west gate, was one of the city''s most important official temples from the Southern Dynasties through the Tang. Excavated in four campaigns between 1882 and 1953, the site yielded hundreds of sculpture fragments—the most important Southern Dynasties Buddhist stone-carving discovery in southern China after Yungang and Longmen. The gallery is organized into five periods: Liang, Northern Zhou, Sui, Early Tang, and High Tang. Highlights include a 523 CE Liang Pingtong-4 statue, Ashoka-style pagodas, a Sui Daye Amitabha, an Early Tang yab-yum Buddha, and a High Tang guardian figure. Wanfo carvings uniquely merge the "Cao Yi Chu Shui" (Cao-style flowing-drapery) and "Wu Dai Dang Feng" (Wu-style fluttering-ribbon) styles—key evidence for the "Southern Dynasties sinicization" of Chinese Buddhist sculpture.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'sichuan_museum_sa_10';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '四川民族文物馆（成都博物院三楼）',
  name_en = 'Sichuan Ethnic Cultural Relics Gallery (Chengdu Museum, 3F)',
  body = '<p>This gallery is the museum''s premier window into the "diverse yet unified" Chinese nation on Sichuan soil. Sections cover Tibetan (Jiarong, Amdo, Khampa), Qiang, Yi (Liangshan), Miao, Tujia, Naxi, Lisu, Mongol, Hui, and Manchu groups. Costumes are the highlights: Jiarong Tibetan women''s colorful robes with turquoise-coral-amber headdresses, Liangshan Yi men''s "chaerwa" woolen cloaks and "tianbaba" hero-knot, Qiang cross-stitch embroidery and silver plaques, Miao pleated skirts and batik, and Tujia "Xilankapu" brocade. The gallery also displays ethnic musical instruments (Qiang flute, mouth harp, long-necked qin, mabu), ritual objects (Bon-buddhist butter flowers, Bimo divining cylinders, Dongba scriptures), tools, and wedding items. The closing "ethnic unity" relief wall embodies the vision of a Chinese national community.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'sichuan_museum_sa_11';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '工艺美术馆（成都博物院三楼）',
  name_en = 'Arts & Crafts Gallery (Chengdu Museum, 3F)',
  body = '<p>Located at the end of 3F East Wing, the gallery brings together over ten Ba-Shu craft genres: Shu brocade, Shu embroidery, Chengdu lacquerware, silver filigree, bamboo weaving, porcelain-bamboo composite, ivory and jade carving, gold-silver inlay, paper-cut, shadow puppetry, and masks. The center stage replicates a late-Qing Shu-brocade "great-flower-loom" wooden machine—heritage inheritors demonstrate "picking-and-tying pattern cards" at scheduled times, letting visitors watch "wanzi" and "bing-mei" patterns take form. The double-sided Shu-embroidered panda won the Hundred Flowers Gold Award; the silver-filigree showcase displays "flat-fill" filigree of intricate complexity; the porcelain-bamboo pieces wrap hairlike bamboo strips around thin porcelain. The closing "Intangible Heritage Experience Zone" offers Shu-embroidered fans, silver filigree, and paper-cut classes—reserve at the service desk.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'sichuan_museum_sa_12';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '刘备殿——汉昭烈庙正殿（成都武侯祠）',
  name_en = 'Liu Bei''s Hall — Main Hall of Han Zhao Lie Miao (Chengdu Wuhou Shrine)',
  body = '<p>Liu Bei''s Hall is the 3rd bay of the central axis, ~12m high, hung with the plaque "Ye Shao Gao Guang." Centered is the gilded seated statue of Emperor Zhaolie Liu Bei—robed, holding the jade tablet, dignified—the shrine''s principal deity. Flanking the emperor are Guan Yu''s three generations (Guan Ping, Guan Xing, Zhang Zun) and Zhang Fei''s three generations (Zhang Bao, Zhang Zun); the side walls display 14 Shu Han elite statues (Zhuge Liang, Pang Tong, Zhao Yun, Ma Chao, Huang Zhong). The stone balustrade is finely carved, and the hall houses historic plaques including Zhuge Liang''s "Collection" plaque and Lu You''s poetry stele. Liu Bei''s birthday celebration is held on the 26th day of the 6th lunar month.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chengdu_wuhou_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '惠陵——蜀汉昭烈帝刘备与甘、吴二皇后合葬陵',
  name_en = 'Hui Ling — Joint Burial Tomb of Emperor Zhaolie Liu Bei and Empresses Gan & Wu',
  body = '<p>Hui Ling is located at the northwest of the heritage zone, distributed in a "reverse pinwheel" layout with Han Zhao Lie Miao and Wuhou Shrine. The burial mound is ~12m high, 180m in circumference, ~3,000 sqm. Liu Bei was entombed here after his death at Baidi City in 223 AD—the tomb has never been looted in 1,780 years, protected by both the people''s loyalty and the Ming-Qing tomb guardians. The 1953 excavation of the tomb passage revealed gold, jade, swords, and horse-and-chariot artifacts. The mound, tomb passage, que-fang, and corner towers form a complete imperial-tomb architectural group.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chengdu_wuhou_shrine_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '灵祖殿',
  name_en = '灵祖殿 / Lingzu Hall (Patriarch Hall)',
  body = '<p>The Lingzu Hall is located after the Mountain Gate and before the Hunyuan Hall, and is the first main hall on the central axis of Qingyang Palace, as well as the first large hall that visitors see after entering the core sacrificial area of Qingyang Palace. The Lingzu Hall is a single-eave Xieshan-style brick and wood structure, with gray tiles, red walls, flying eaves, five bays wide, and a solemn atmosphere. The main worship in the hall is the Taoist "Sanqing" one of the "Lingbao Tianzun" (Heavenly Worthy of Spiritual Treasure), also known as "Shangqing Lingbao Tianzun", one of the highest deities in Taoism. The two sides of the Lingzu Hall are often accompanied by Taoist Dharma protector generals, with various shapes and exquisite painted statues. In front of the hall, there is a large incense burner, where pilgrims and visitors burn incense to worship and pray for blessings. The Lingzu Hall plays a transitional role in the overall architectural pattern of Qingyang Palace - it not only continues the "separation of secular and sacred" of the mountain gate, but also paves the way for the rituals of the Hunyuan Hall, Sanqing Hall and other main halls behind. The plaques and couplets inside and outside the hall are mostly written by famous Qing dynasty calligraphers, containing rich Taoist cultural connotations. The Lingzu Hall has been bustling with incense all year round, and is an important place to experience the Taoist atmosphere of Qingyang Palace and understand Taoist etiquette.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'area_lingzu_hall';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '混元殿',
  name_en = '混元殿 / Hunyuan Hall (Primordial Chaos Hall)',
  body = '<p>The Hunyuan Hall is located after the Lingzu Hall and before the Bagua Pavilion, and is the second main hall on the central axis of Qingyang Palace. The Hunyuan Hall was first built in the Ming Dynasty and rebuilt during the Kangxi period of the Qing Dynasty. It is one of the oldest and most historically valuable halls in Qingyang Palace. The word "Hunyuan" comes from the Taoist classic "Dao De Jing" (Tao Te Ching) "The Tao gives birth to one, one gives birth to two, two gives birth to three, three gives birth to all things" cosmology, symbolizing the original state of heaven and earth not yet divided and chaos at the beginning. The main deity in the hall is the "Dao De Tianzun" (Heavenly Worthy of the Way and its Virtue), one of the "Sanqing" in Taoism, i.e. Laozi Li Er, the philosopher of the Spring and Autumn Period. In the center of the hall, a bronze statue of Laozi is enshrined, holding a ruyi in his left hand and pressing his knee with his right hand, looking peaceful. The statue of Laozi is one of the treasures of Qingyang Palace, and it is said that on the 15th day of the second lunar month, the birthday of Laozi, a grand birthday ceremony will be held in the palace. The Hunyuan Hall is a single-eave Xieshan-style building, with exquisite Taoist ridge beasts on the roof, and the wood carvings, brick carvings and stone carvings inside and outside the hall are exquisite, integrating the architectural aesthetics of the Ming and Qing dynasties. In front of the Hunyuan Hall, Taoists often chant sutras and confess here, which is an important place to experience the core connotation of the Taoist culture of Qingyang Palace.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'area_hunyuan_hall';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '八卦亭',
  name_en = '八卦亭 / Bagua Pavilion (Eight Trigrams Pavilion)',
  body = '<p>The Bagua Pavilion is located after the Hunyuan Hall and before the Sanqing Hall, and is one of the most iconic buildings in Qingyang Palace, as well as a perfect combination of the architectural art and Taoist philosophy of Qingyang Palace. The Bagua Pavilion is a double-eave octagonal pyramidal building, and the body of the pavilion is mainly decorated with green glazed tiles - the eight sides of the pavilion roof and the eight sides of the pavilion body correspond to the eight trigrams of Qian, Kun, Zhen, Xun, Kan, Li, Gen and Dui. The center of the pavilion roof is a black and white Taiji diagram, with the Yin and Yang fish of the Taiji embracing and rotating, symbolizing the cosmic evolution of "The Tao gives birth to one, one gives birth to two, two gives birth to three, three gives birth to all things". The whole Bagua Pavilion has a unique shape and elegant color, the green glazed tiles shine in the sun, forming a sharp contrast with the surrounding red walls and gray tiles, and is a masterpiece of traditional Chinese Taoist temple architectural art. The pavilion originally enshrined a bronze statue of Laozi riding a green ox through Hangu Pass (which was moved to another place during some periods), which is the core cultural symbol of Qingyang Palace. The Bagua Pavilion is not only the visual "commanding height" of Qingyang Palace, but also carries the Taoist cosmology of "the unity of heaven and man" - visitors standing under the pavilion and looking up at the Taiji diagram can intuitively feel the core idea of "Tao follows nature" in Taoism. The square in front of the pavilion often hosts Taoist cultural exhibitions and Tai Chi performances, making it a must-visit place to experience the Taoist culture of Qingyang Palace.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'area_bagua_pavilion';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '三清殿',
  name_en = '三清殿 / Sanqing Hall (Three Pure Ones Hall)',
  body = '<p>The Sanqing Hall is located after the Bagua Pavilion and before the Doumu Hall, and is the largest and most prestigious hall in Qingyang Palace, as well as the core main hall of the entire Qingyang Palace building complex. The Sanqing Hall is a large double-eave Xieshan-style brick and wood structure, with gray tiles, red walls, carved beams and painted rafters, magnificent and solemn. The main deities in the hall are the highest Taoist gods "Sanqing": Yuqing Yuanshi Tianzun (Heavenly Worthy of the Primordial Beginning), Shangqing Lingbao Tianzun (Heavenly Worthy of Spiritual Treasure), and Taiqing Dao De Tianzun (Heavenly Worthy of the Way and its Virtue, i.e. Laozi). The three pure ones sit side by side on a lotus platform, each Tianzun statue is several meters tall, with a peaceful expression and deep eyes. The plaque "Sanqing Hall" in the hall is written by a famous calligrapher in the Qing Dynasty, vigorous and powerful. The stone steps, moon platforms and railings in front of the Sanqing Hall are all carved from white marble, echoing the Taoist statues and painted murals in the hall, forming the most solemn and sacred sacrificial space in Qingyang Palace. Every year during major Taoist festivals such as the Spring Festival and the birthday of the Sanqing, a grand Zhaijiao ceremony will be held in front of the Sanqing Hall, which is the most concentrated place for Taoist cultural activities in Qingyang Palace. The Ming and Qing wood carvings, stone carvings and paintings inside and outside the hall are of high artistic value, and are precious objects for studying the history of Chinese Taoist architecture and art. The Sanqing Hall is the core place for visitors to understand Qingyang Palace and the highest deity system of Taoism. Visitors are advised to keep quiet and respect religious etiquette when visiting.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'area_sanqing_hall';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '斗姥殿',
  name_en = '斗姥殿 / Doumu Hall (Mother of the Big Dipper Hall)',
  body = '<p>The Doumu Hall is located after the Sanqing Hall and before the Jade Emperor Hall, and is one of the core halls on the central axis of Qingyang Palace. The Doumu Hall is a single-eave Xieshan-style brick and wood structure, with gray tiles, red walls, and a solemn atmosphere. The main deity in the hall is Doumu Yuanjun, also known as "Doumou Yuanjun", the highest goddess in the Taoist star worship system, who is in charge of the constellations in the sky, fertility and longevity in the mortal world. The image of Doumu Yuanjun is unique, with three faces and four heads, or three faces and eight heads, holding the sun and moon in her hands or holding the sun and moon beads, symbolizing her supreme divine power over the stars of the heavens. On both sides of the Doumu Hall are often accompanied by the "Big Dipper Seven Star Lords" - the statues of the seven star lords Tianshu, Tianxuan, Tianji, Tianquan, Yuheng, Kaiyang and Yaoguang. The Doumu Hall has a very high status in folk beliefs, and it is said that Doumu Yuanjun is one of the incarnations of the "Goddess of Child Giving", and pilgrims often pray here for offspring, health and longevity. Every year on the ninth day of the ninth lunar month, the birthday of Doumu, a grand blessing ceremony will be held in front of the hall. The Taoist statues and painted murals in the Doumu Hall are exquisite, and the stone and wood carvings outside the hall are exquisite. The Doumu Hall is a representative place to experience the Taoist star worship and female deity belief in Qingyang Palace, and is also a popular hall for visitors to pray and make wishes.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'area_doumu_hall';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '茶园与老庄书院',
  name_en = '茶园与老庄书院 / Tea Garden and Laozhuang Academy (Lao-Zhuang Academy)',
  body = '<p>The Tea Garden and Laozhuang Academy are located in the middle and rear of the Qingyang Palace building complex, near the back gate of Qingyang Palace, and are the most leisurely characteristic cultural space in Qingyang Palace. The Tea Garden is a typical Sichuan-Western folk-style teahouse building, with green bricks, gray tiles, rattan chairs, bamboo tables, and green plants. The tea garden provides authentic Chengdu gaiwan tea (Bitan Piaoxue, Zhuyeqing, etc.), Sichuan-Western snacks (San Da Pao, Zhong Dumplings, Lai Tangyuan, Fuqi Feipian, etc.), Sichuan-style cold dishes and health tea. Visitors can rest in the tea garden after visiting the halls, brew a pot of tea, taste some snacks, listen to a section of Sichuan opera Qingyin, watch a tea art performance, and experience the most authentic "teahouse culture" in Chengdu. The Laozhuang Academy is adjacent to the tea garden and is a special academic space for displaying, researching and disseminating Taoist culture in Qingyang Palace. The academy is named after the two representative figures of Taoism - Laozi (Li Er) and Zhuangzi (Zhuang Zhou). The academy has a collection of Taoist classic versions such as the "Tao Te Ching" and "Zhuangzi", Taoist calligraphy stone inscriptions and rubbings from past dynasties, and books on Taoist culture research. The cloister outside the academy often has calligraphy exhibitions, displaying calligraphy works of famous Taoist articles. The Tea Garden and the Laozhuang Academy together form a "dynamic-static" combination of leisure and cultural system in Qingyang Palace - the halls are "dynamic" religious and cultural spaces, and the tea garden and academy are "static" cultural leisure spaces, allowing visitors to find a quiet place in the hustle and bustle of the city after pilgrimage and worship, and experience the "Taoist slow life".</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'area_tea_garden';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '藏经楼（宸经楼）',
  name_en = 'Sutra-Preservation Pavilion — Imperial Sutra Hall (Chenjing Hall)',
  body = '<p>The Canon Library, also called "Chenjing Lou," is the fifth hall on the central axis—originally built by Chan Master Cidu and rebuilt by Abbot Benyuan in 1824. Standing 15.84 m tall in two stories, it is the monastery''s central repository for sutras and treasures. The name "Chenjing" comes from Kangxi''s imperial calligraphy. Beyond the Ming and Qing Buddhist canons (Long, Pingqia, Taisho, Qianlong Da Zangjing and continuations), the library preserves Kangxi''s "Konglin" hand and his Mi Fu-style "Hai Yue" calligraphy, Song dragon ink paintings, late-Ming and Qing calligraphy by Poshan and Zhangxue, paintings by Biyan and Zhuchan, and works by He Shaoji, Zheng Banqiao, Zhang Daqian, and Feng Zikai. To the left rests a portion of the cranial relic of Master Xuanzang, transferred from Nanjing in the 1940s—the monk was ordained in Chengdu and lived here for five years; to the right rests a Buddha Śarīra brought from Bodh Gaya by the monk Nenghai in the 1920s. The "Tian Yi Xuan Cai" qipao embroidered with 248 Buddha figures by Ming consort Tian, the Qing hair-embroidered Water-Moon Guanyin, four blood-written sutras, and the Diamond Sutra pagoda painting—all part of the "Eight Views of Konglin"—are also housed here.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'area_sutra_preservation_pavilion_imperial_sutra_hall_chenjing_hall';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '茶园与香斋堂',
  name_en = 'Tea Garden and Vegetarian Hall',
  body = '<p>The Tea Garden sits inside the monastery''s east garden, opened in 1988 alongside the Thousand-Buddha Peace Pagoda, and operates as a "Chan-monastery teahouse" in old-Chengdu style. Bamboo roofs, blue-brick paving, square tables, covered-bowl tea, and long-spouted copper kettles recreate a classic "bada cha" open-air teahouse serving Bi Tan Piao Xue, Zhu Ye Qing, Mao Feng, Tie Guan Yin, and Pu''er teas at around RMB 10–30 per person, with free hot-water refills and outside snacks allowed. The Xiangzhai Hall vegetarian restaurant sits next to the Tea Garden and is separate from the monks'' Wuguan Hall. The menu emphasizes Sichuan-style vegetarian cuisine: vegetarian Mapo tofu, vegetarian twice-cooked pork, sweet rice cake, monastery pickles, and full vegetarian set meals at RMB 20–60 per person, plus luohan noodles and mushroom wonton. Together they create a "worship, tea, dine" loop, expressing the monastery''s "humanistic Buddhism" approach. Just outside the gate, Wenshu Yuan Street hosts Chengdu classics such as Long Chaoshou (Wenshu Yuan main branch), Yan Taipo Guokui, and Zhong Sui Jiao, making the visit a combined temple-and-old-streets experience.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'area_tea_garden_and_vegetarian_hall';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '大雄宝殿',
  name_en = 'Mahavira Hall (Great Buddha Hall / Precious Hall of the Great Hero)',
  body = '<p>The Mahavira Hall is the third hall on the central axis, originally built by Chan Master Cidu and rebuilt by Abbot Zhangbai. Standing 10.56 m tall in single-eaved Xieshan style, it is the largest and highest-ranked hall in the monastery. The central glass shrine houses a bronze Sakyamuni Buddha cast in 1829, flanked by bronze Kasyapa and Ananda figures—the most important Qing-dynasty bronze trio in the monastery and part of the "Eight Views of Konglin." Two Burmese jade Buddhas brought back in 1923 and 1938 by monks Xinglin and Dengyun sit in the shrine ("Burmese Jade in the Shrine"). Two ancient fir trees, each 15 m tall, stand behind the hall: descendants of the firs that flanked the old gate and under which Master Cidu took shelter ("Twin Firs Auspicious"). Free incense is provided—one stick per person, taken with both hands.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'area_mahavira_hall_great_buddha_hall_precious_hall_of_the_great_hero';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '千佛和平塔与碑廊',
  name_en = 'Thousand Buddha Peace Pagoda and Stele Corridor',
  body = '<p>The Thousand-Buddha Peace Pagoda stands in the eastern courtyard between the Canon Library and Wenshu Pavilion. Built in 1988, it was inscribed and coupleted by Zhao Puchu, then president of the Buddhist Association of China. The six-sided, eleven-story iron pagoda rises 21 meters and bears 1,000 cast Buddha images. Six dragons crown the spire with bells that ring in the wind. The east, west, and north sides are lined with stele corridors displaying dozens of stone tablets—Qing imperial and official inscriptions, poems by the monastery''s abbots Cidu, Benyuan, Xuanlin, Nenghai, Biannen, and Weixian, and Buddhist maxims. The two-tiered surrounding walls are decorated with four-season floral motifs and bas-reliefs of the Journey to the West, symbolizing the two-way transmission of dharma along the Silk Road. Ginkgo, camphor, plum, and magnolia trees frame the pagoda, making it the monastery''s most contemplative garden.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'area_thousand_buddha_peace_pagoda_and_stele_corridor';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '三大士殿（观音殿）',
  name_en = 'wenshuyuan sub area 01',
  body = '<p>The Hall of the Three Great Beings, also called the Hall of Guanyin, is the second hall on the central axis and the only one of the six that retains its original 1697 Kangxi-period structure. Three principal statues stand on a central platform: Manjushri on a blue lion (wisdom), Guanyin holding a willow branch and pure-water vase (compassion), and Samantabhadra on a white elephant (vow and action). Side bays house Wenchang Dijun and Saintly Lord Guan, reflecting the late-imperial Sichuanese fusion of Buddhist, Daoist, and Confucian popular devotion. Behind the hall stands the bronze Weituo guardian, cast by Abbot Benyuan in 1829. The lintel couplet by late-Qing Chengdu literatus Fang Hezhai—"What is done let be done, what is let go let be let go, what ends, ends; wisdom is born of awakening, awakening is born of ease, what arises, arises and yet does not arise"—expresses the Chan spirit of resolving the matter at hand.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'wenshuyuan_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '山门（天王殿）',
  name_en = 'Mountain Gate — Heavenly Kings Hall (Tianwang Hall)',
  body = '<p>The Main Gate / Hall of Heavenly Kings is the first hall on the central axis, originally built by Chan Master Cidu and rebuilt by Abbot Benyuan, facing south with a five-bay facade in classic Kangxi–Daoguang Sichuanese style. The gate and hall are combined: the two Heng-Ha guardians stand at the door, Maitreya is enshrined at the center (with Weituo behind), and the Four Heavenly Kings—Dhṛtarāṣṭra, Virūḍhaka, Virūpākṣa, and Vaiśravaṇa—flank the hall, each holding a sword, pipa, parasol, or serpent/dragon to symbolize favorable weather. The pillars bear the couplet by Qing abbot Fu Wenjiwei. In front, the three-story Drum and Bell towers face each other: the bell tower houses a 4,500+ kg Qing-dynasty bronze bell, the drum tower its great drum. Their morning bell and evening drum mark the monastic schedule and ritual calendar.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'area_mountain_gate_heavenly_kings_hall_tianwang_hall';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '说法堂（药师殿）',
  name_en = 'Dharma Preaching Hall — Medicine Master Hall (Bhaisajyaguru Hall)',
  body = '<p>The Dharma Hall, also called the Hall of Bhaisajyaguru, is the fourth hall on the central axis and is said to occupy the site of the original Tang-era Xinxiang Monastery. A double-eaved Xieshan Qing-dynasty building, it contains a brick ordination platform used for precepts ceremonies, lay refuge, and sutra lectures. At center, beneath a jeweled canopy, sits Bhaisajyaguru, the Medicine Buddha of the eastern Lapis Lazuli world, flanked by the twelve yakṣa generals—each guarding one of the twelve时辰 hours and zodiac animals. The back wall bears the Kangxi Emperor''s 1702 inscription "Konglin" (Empty Forest)—the calligraphic origin of the monastery''s alternate name "Konglin Tang" and the first of the "Eight Views of Konglin." The Sichuanese-style Buddhist chanting preserved here was inscribed on Chengdu''s seventh intangible cultural heritage list in 2021.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'area_dharma_preaching_hall_medicine_master_hall_bhaisajyaguru_hall';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '文殊阁',
  name_en = 'Wenshu Pavilion',
  body = '<p>Wenshu Pavilion stands at the northernmost end of the central axis. Built in 1997 under the 17th abbot Xuanlin, it occupies about 1,000 square meters in a three-story Qing-style double-eave structure. The first floor, the "Konglin Lecture Hall," seats several hundred for dharma talks, meditation, and Chan practice. The second floor houses the "Konglin Buddhist Library," with sutras, modern Buddhist scholarship, and journals for both laypeople and researchers. The third floor, the "Ten-Thousand-Buddha Hall," enshrines the central principal Buddha surrounded by a thousand Buddhas on the four walls, creating the monastery''s most contemplative space. The pavilion closes the central axis and complements the five earlier historic halls, forming a "front-court, rear-market" plan that joins devotional and cultural functions.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'area_wenshu_pavilion';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '园林与放生池',
  name_en = 'Garden and Life-Releasing Pond',
  body = '<p>The Wenshu Monastery gardens center on the east and west gardens flanking the central axis and the Release Pond—landscaped together with the Thousand-Buddha Pagoda in 1988. The Release Pond sits between the Hall of Heavenly Kings and the Mahavira Hall in an irregular L shape, home to koi, goldfish, and turtles, with water lilies, calamus, and willows along the banks; a Qing-era "Release Pond" stele stands on the north bank in Manchu and Chinese. The Tingsong Waterside Pavilion on the west bank responds visually to the Bell and Drum towers. The east garden ("Hearing and Reflecting") and west garden ("Cultivating and Realizing") flank the central axis, with Taihu rocks, ginkgo, camphor, plum, magnolia, crepe myrtle, and paths of bamboo. Covered corridors tie the halls, gardens, and the Peace Pagoda into a single meandering composition. The two ancient firs at the rear of the Mahavira Hall, said to mark Master Cidu''s hermitage, are the "Twin Firs Auspicious" of the "Eight Views of Konglin."</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'area_garden_and_life_releasing_pond';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '正门（照壁）',
  name_en = 'Main Gate — Screen Wall',
  body = '<p>The front gate and spirit wall stand at the south end of the Wenshu Monastery central axis, the first visual anchor before visitors reach the main gate. About 8 meters high and shaped like the character "pin" (品) in brick and stone, the wall is inscribed with the three characters "Wénshū Yuàn" and the couplet "Ruìzé shēn tiāndì, zōngfēng yuè gǔjīn" (Wisdom deep as heaven and earth, lineage surpassing past and present), said to be in the hand of Chan Master Cidu of the Kangxi reign. The wall faces the city street on one side and the temple gate on the other—a classic Chinese monastic gesture of modesty and containment. Two side gates flank the central entrance, and the temple itself is open and free, with the public transit and city road reaching right up to the wall.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'area_main_gate_screen_wall';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '九街标志牌坊',
  name_en = 'Jiujie Gateway Archway',
  body = '<p>The Jiujie Gateway Archway stands at the entrance of Guanyinqiao Jiujie, serving as the symbolic portal of this renowned nightlife district. Built in traditional Chinese architectural style with upturned eaves, painted beams, and the characters "Jiujie" inscribed at the center, it exudes grandeur. By day, the archway appears stately and classical; by night, illuminated lights blend with surrounding neon, creating a striking fusion of old and new. As the landmark of Jiujie, it is a must-visit photo spot for tourists and the starting point for exploring the area''s vibrant nightlife. Surrounded by shops and restaurants ranging from traditional hotpot to trendy bars, it is the perfect gateway to experience Chongqing''s urban night culture.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_jiujie_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '九街高屋',
  name_en = 'Jiujie High House',
  body = '<p>KTV和live house等娱乐场所，是年轻人夜间社交的热门聚集地。高屋内还设有多个主题露台，可俯瞰整个九街繁华夜景。无论是品尝创意料理、欣赏现场音乐，还是与朋友畅饮小聚，九街高屋都能提供一站式的都市夜生活体验，是感受重庆不夜城魅力的必访之地。 Jiujie High House is one of the most iconic commercial complexes in the Guanyinqiao Jiujie business district, renowned for its distinctive high-rise facade and diverse mix of businesses. The building features a modern glass curtain wall exterior with dazzling nighttime lighting, forming a brilliant highlight in the Jiujie skyline. Inside, it houses popular internet-famous restaurants, trendy boutique shops, KTV venues, and live houses, making it a hotspot for young people''s nightlife socializing. Multiple themed terraces offer panoramic views of the bustling Jiujie nightscape. Whether enjoying creative cuisine, live music, or drinks with friends, Jiujie High House provides a one-stop urban nightlife experience and is a must-visit destination to feel the charm of Chongqing''s sleepless city.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_jiujie_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '鲤鱼池42号文创园',
  name_en = 'Liyuchi No. 42 Cultural and Creative Park',
  body = '<p>Liyuchi No. 42 Cultural and Creative Park was formerly an old industrial factory in Chongqing. After careful renovation, it has been revitalized into a cultural space combining art exhibitions, creative design, specialty dining, and leisure entertainment. The park preserves the rugged framework of the original industrial architecture, with red brick walls and steel structures complementing each other. Weathered traces of time blend ingeniously with modern art installations, creating a unique retro-artistic atmosphere. The park houses numerous independent designer studios, handicraft workshops, boutique cafés, and niche art galleries, and regularly hosts creative markets and art salons. Large-scale graffiti murals on weathered walls are popular photo backdrops for young visitors. Away from the bustle of Jiujie, it offers a quiet, inspiration-filled haven for art and creativity lovers.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_jiujie_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '九街后街',
  name_en = 'Jiujie Back Street',
  body = '<p>Jiujie Back Street refers to the alleyway area behind Jiujie''s main street, offering a stark contrast to the neon-lit bustle of the main thoroughfare with a more authentic taste of everyday Chongqing life. Narrow alleys are lined with small food shops serving local delicacies—from steaming bowls of hot and sour noodles and soft glutinous rice cakes to sizzling skewers and fragrant tofu noodles—gathering the most genuine flavors of Chongqing''s streets. There are no upscale restaurants here, only the most down-to-earth tastes and the warmest proprietors. Many locals'' late-night favorites are hidden in these alleys, where an unassuming shop may have been passed down for decades. Walls are adorned with lively graffiti and old-Chongqing-themed murals. Strolling through feels like stepping into a vivid scroll painting of Ba-Yu street life, making it the perfect place to experience authentic Chongqing food culture and neighborhood charm.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_jiujie_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '十八梯大牌坊',
  name_en = 'Shiba Ti Grand Archway',
  body = '<p>The Shiba Ti Grand Archway stands at the southern entrance of the Shiba Ti Traditional Heritage District, serving as the first landmark for visitors entering this century-old street. Built from blue stone in a four-pillar, three-bay sky-reaching style, it stands over ten meters tall—imposing yet refined and elegant. The central plaque is inscribed with three gold-leaf characters reading "Shiba Ti," while the crossbeams feature relief carvings of bats, auspicious clouds, and ruyi patterns. The stone-drum pillar bases are finely carved, combining the robustness of Ba-Yu stone carving with the gracefulness of southern Chinese archways. A small plaza surrounds the archway with faux-antique stone paving, ficus bonsai, and decorative lamp posts. After dark, warm yellow lights illuminate the stone structure, creating a rich atmosphere of old Yuzhou charm. Looking north from here, the main street of Shiba Ti unfolds in cascading stone steps descending the hillside, with stilt-house-style shops lining both sides, and modern skyscrapers in the distance overlapping with tiled eaves nearby. A guide map and electronic touch screen beside the archway mark all attractions and recommended routes, making it an essential stop for planning visits and taking photos.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_shibati_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '善果巷与山城记忆馆',
  name_en = 'Shanguo Lane and Mountain City Memory Hall',
  body = '<p>Shanguo Lane is a historic stone-step alley within the Shiba Ti Heritage District. Its name originates from the Shanguo Temple that once stood here during the Qing Dynasty, carrying forward the spirit of charity and goodwill. The alley is about two meters wide, bordered by old brick walls and stone embankments intertwined with ficus tree roots, covered in moss and draped with vines—walking through it feels like traveling back to the slow-paced old Chongqing. Within the lane sits the Mountain City Memory Hall, a micro-museum converted from a traditional residence. With its grey tiles, white walls, and wooden windows, the exterior is understated, yet stepping inside reveals a hidden world. The hall uses "Upper City and Lower City" as its theme, presenting through old photographs, vintage objects, oral history videos, and interactive installations the century-long evolution of Shiba Ti—from the bustling pier trade of the late Qing and early Republic, through the wartime capital''s population surge, to modern urban renewal. Exhibits include old kerosene lamps, bamboo-woven thermos flasks, hand-written street signs, and yellowed household registers—everyday objects full of warmth that bear authentic witness to ordinary Chongqing residents'' lives. A "sound wall" features recordings of street hawker cries, work chants, and riverboat whistles—put on the headphones and listen to the vanishing sounds of the mountain city.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_shibati_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '月台坝（山地院落）',
  name_en = 'Yuetai Ba (Mountain Courtyard)',
  body = '<p>Yuetai Ba is located mid-way along Shiba Ti—a cluster of terraced courtyard residences naturally formed by the hillside gradient, and one of the nodes that best embodies Chongqing''s mountain architecture within the entire heritage district. The name "Yuetai" (Moon Platform) comes from the broad, flat stone platform in front of the courtyards, shaped like a moon terrace. In the past, residents gathered here to cool off, chat, dry laundry, and let children play—it was the heart of neighborhood social life. The courtyard complex features timber frame structures with blue brick and stone walls, stepping down the slope in successive terraces. Looking up from below, rows of grey-tiled eaves rise like steps; looking down from above, courtyards, skylights, and stone stairs interlock in rich spatial layers. After renovation, Yuetai Ba retains its original architectural bones and spatial fabric, with damaged components restored using traditional craftsmanship, while new businesses—creative shops, teahouses, and craft workshops—have been introduced. Narrow stone-step alleys connect the courtyards, with stone water vats and ficus bonsai at corners, revealing the old Chongqing philosophy of "climbing slopes and turning corners" everywhere. Sitting in a bamboo chair on the moon platform with a bowl of covered tea, overlooking the half-cityscape and distant river views, is the most authentic way to experience the slow life of the mountain city.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_shibati_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '大隧道遗址',
  name_en = 'Great Tunnel Relics',
  body = '<p>The Shiba Ti Great Tunnel Relics are a vital part of Chongqing''s WWII air defense engineering. After the Nationalist Government relocated the capital to Chongqing in 1937, Japanese forces conducted indiscriminate strategic bombing of the city for five and a half years. To protect civilian lives, Chongqing mobilized the entire city to excavate a massive network of air-raid shelter tunnels. The Shiba Ti Great Tunnel was one of these, approximately 2 km long, carved by hand into sandstone hillside. The interior stands about 2 meters high and 2–3 meters wide, capable of sheltering thousands simultaneously. The tunnel was equipped with ventilation shafts, drainage channels, rest areas, and rudimentary medical stations—crude conditions that nonetheless saved countless lives during the darkest years. The now-open section has been safety-reinforced and scenically restored. Chisel marks and smoke stains from the era remain visible on the walls. Information panels and multimedia installations inside detail the historical background of the Chongqing Bombing, the tunnel construction process, and civilian shelter life. Walking through, one hears simulated air-raid sirens and infants'' cries, creating a profound sense of the resilience and survival spirit of the Chongqing people during those fiery years—a historically educational immersive site.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_shibati_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '宝顶山',
  name_en = 'Baoding Mountain',
  body = '<p>U 字形马蹄形山湾，长约 500 米、高 8—15 米的崖壁上环列 31 组大型造像，题材前后连接、起承转合，将佛教教义、世俗生活与民间故事融为一体，被誉为"中国晚期石窟艺术集大成之作"和"中国石窟艺术史上最后一座丰碑"。1999 年 12 月，宝顶山摩崖造像作为"大足石刻"的组成部分被联合国教科文组织列入《世界遗产名录》。</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_dazu_rock_carvings_sa_01';

